Alif Lam Mim (A.L.M.).
|30|2|
The Greeks have been defeated,
|30|3|
in a neighbouring land; but they, after their defeat, shall gain victory,
|30|4|
in a few years; to God belongs the affair before and after; and on that day the Believers shall rejoice
|30|5|
in God's help; He helps whom He will; and He is the Mighty, the Merciful;
|30|6|
it is God's promise; God shall not fail His promise, but most men do not know.
|30|7|
They know what is apparent in the worldly life, but they are unaware of the End.
|30|8|
Have they not pondered within themselves that God has not created the heavens and the earth and what between them is but on truth and for a stated term? Yet many men disbelieve in the meeting with their Lord.
|30|9|
And have they not journeyed in the land and seen how was the end of those before them? They were stronger than these in might, and they ploughed the land and cultivated it more than these cultivated it, and their Messengers came to them with the Clear Signs; and God was not such as would wrong them, but themselves they wronged.
|30|10|
Then, the end of those who did evil was evil, for that they gave lies to the Signs of God and used to mock at them.
|30|11|
God begins the creation, then repeats it, then to Him you shall be returned.
|30|12|
And on the day the Hour comes, the sinners shall despair.
|30|13|
And there shall be no intercessors for them among their associate-gods, and they shall deny their associate-gods.
|30|14|
And on the day the Hour comes, that day they shall be divided.
|30|15|
Then as for those who believed and did righteous deeds, they shall rejoice in a green meadow.
|30|16|
And as for those who disbelieved, and gave lies to Our signs and to the meeting of the Hereafter, they shall be arraigned in the punishment.
|30|17|
Glory be to God, when it is your evening and when it is your morning.
|30|18|
And His is the praise in the heavens and the earth, and at sunset and when it is your noontime.
|30|19|
He brings forth the living from the dead, and brings forth the dead from the living, and revives the earth after it is dead; and like that shall you be brought forth.
|30|20|
And of His Signs is that He created you of dust; then, lo, you are men spreading wide.
|30|21|
And of His Signs is that He created for you mates, out of yourselves, that you might repose in them, and He put love and mercy between you; in that are surely Signs for a people who ponder.
|30|22|
And of His Signs are the creation of the heavens and the earth, and the diversity of your languages and colours; in that are surely Signs for the men of knowledge.
|30|23|
And of His Signs is your sleeping and your seeking of His bounty by night and day; in that are surely Signs for a people who hear.
|30|24|
And of His Signs is that He shows you lightning for fear and hope, and sends down water from the heaven, with which He revives the earth after it is dead; in that are surely Signs for a people who understand.
|30|25|
And of His Signs is that the heaven and the earth stand firm by His command; then, when He gives you a call (to come) out of the earth, lo, you shall come forth.
|30|26|
And to Him belongs whosoever is in the heavens and the earth; all are obedient to Him.
|30|27|
And it is He who begins the creation, then repeats it, and it is easy for Him. And His is the loftiest example in the heavens and the earth; and He is the Mighty, the Wise.
|30|28|
He describes for you a similitude from yourselves: do you have among those that your right hands own, any associates in that We have provided for you, so that you are equal in it, fearing for them as you fear for yourselves? Thus We explain the Signs for a people who understand.
|30|29|
No, but the wrong-doers follow their caprices without any knowledge; now who will guide those whom God has sent astray; and they have no helpers?
|30|30|
So set thy face to the Religion, all-devoted: __ God's original law on which he originated mankind; there can be no change in God's creation; that is the standing Religion __ but most men do not know __
|30|31|
turning to Him, fear Him, and establish the Prayer, and be not of the idolaters,
|30|32|
of those who have divided their religion, and have become sects; every group rejoices in what is with them.
|30|33|
And when some harm touches men, they call to their Lord, turning to Him; then, when He makes them taste mercy from Him, lo, a party of them assigns associates to their Lord,
|30|34|
that they may be ungrateful for what We have given them; `enjoy; you will soon know'.
|30|35|
Or have We sent down upon them any authority which speaks of the things they associate with Him?
|30|36|
And when We let men taste mercy, they rejoice in it; and when an evil afflicts them for that their hands have forwarded, lo, they despair.
|30|37|
But have they not seen that God outspreads and straitens provision for whom He will? In that are surely Signs for a people who believe.
|30|38|
So give the kinsman, the needy, and the traveller his right; that is better for those who desire God's attention; and it is those who shall prosper.
|30|39|
And what you give in usury, that it may increase upon people's wealth, does not increase with God; but what you give in alms, desiring God's attention, shall get the increase manifold.
|30|40|
God is He who created you, then provided for you, then He shall make you dead, then He shall give you life; is there any among your associate-gods who does anything of that? Holy be He, Exalted, above that they associate!
|30|41|
Disorder has prevailed over the land and sea, for what men's hands have earned, that He may make them taste some of that they have done; may be, they return.
|30|42|
Say, `journey in the land then behold, how was the end of those that lived before; most of them were idolators.'
|30|43|
So set thy face to the standing religion before there comes a day from God that will not be turned back, the day when people will be sundered apart.
|30|44|
Whoso disbelieves, on him shall fall his unbelief and whoso does righteousness, for themselves they make preparations,
|30|45|
that He may recompense those who believe and do righteous deeds out of His bounty; surely He does not like the unbelievers.
|30|46|
And of His Signs is that He looses the winds as bearers of good news, and that He may make you taste of His mercy, and that the ships may sail by His commandment, and that you may seek of His bounty, and, may be, that you give thanks.
|30|47|
And indeed We sent Messengers before thee to their people, and they came to them with the Clear Signs, then We took vengeance upon the sinners: and surely it was a duty binding upon Us to help the Believers.
|30|48|
God is He who looses the winds, that stir up the cloud, then He spreads it in the heaven how He will, and He breaks it up, then thou seest the rain coming out of its midst; and when He causes it to fall on whomsoever of His servants He will, they rejoice;
|30|49|
and surely, before it was sent down on them, they were, before that, in despair.
|30|50|
Now see the marks of God's mercy, how He gives life to the earth after it was dead; surely That One is the quickener of the dead, and He is powerful over everything.
|30|51|
But if We loose a wind, and they seeit turning yellow, they will remain, thereafter, unbelievers.
|30|52|
So thou shalt not make the dead to hear, nor make the deaf to hear the call, when they turn back, retreating.
|30|53|
And thou art no guide for the blind in their straying; thou only makes him hear who believes in Our Signs, and so have surrendered.
|30|54|
God is He who made you of weakness, then, after weakness, He gave strength, then, after strength, He gave weakness and grey hairs; He creates what He will, and He is the Knowing, the Powerful.
|30|55|
And on the day when the Hour arrives, the sinners shall swear that they did not stay more than an hour; so were they perverted.
|30|56|
But those, who have been given knowledge and faith, shall say, `you stayed, in God's Book, till the Day of Upraising, and this is the Day of Upraising, but you never knew.
|30|57|
So on that day, their excuse will not profit the wrong-doers, and they will not be allowed to make amends.
|30|58|
And We have indeed described in this Qur'an every type of similitude for the people; yet, even if thou bringest them a Sign, the unbelievers will surely say, `you only follow falsehood.'
|30|59|
Thus does God seal the hearts of those who have no knowledge.
|30|60|
So be thou patient; God's promise is true; and let not those who have no faith make thee unsteady.
|31|1|
Alif Lam Mim (A.L.M.).
|31|2|
These are the signs of the wise Book,
|31|3|
for a guidance and a mercy to the good-doers,
|31|4|
those who establish the Prayer, pay the due__alms, and who have sure faith in the Hereafter.
|31|5|
Those are upon guidance from their Lord, and those are the ones who shall prosper.
|31|6|
And among men is he who takes up a funny story to lead astray from God's way without any he knowledge, and takes it in mockery; for them there shall be a disgraceful punishment.
|31|7|
And when Our signs are recited to him, he turns away in arrogance, as if he did not hear them, as if there was heaviness in his ears; so give him a good news of a painful punishment.
|31|8|
Surely those, who believe and do righteous deeds, shall have gardens of bliss,
|31|9|
to dwell therein forever; it is God's promise in truth: and He is the Mighty, the Wise.
|31|10|
He created the heavens without pillars that you can see, and He cast firm mountains in the earth, lest it should shake with you, and He spread in it all types of creatures. And We sent down water from heaven, then caused to grow therein of every fine kind.
|31|11|
This is God's creation, now show me what those, that are apart from Him, have created. No, but the wrongdoers are clearly astray.
|31|12|
And We gave Lokman wisdom: `be grateful to God; and whoso is grateful, is grateful only for himself; and if any is ungrateful, then God is Self-sufficient, Praiseworthy.'
|31|13|
And when Lokman said to his son admonishing him, `O my son, do not assign associates to God; surely assigning of associates is a mighty wrong.' 
|31|14|
And We have charged man concerning his parents __ his mother bears him in weakness upon weakness, and his weaning is in two years __ `Be thankful to Me and to thy parents; to Me is the destination.'
|31|15|
But if they strive with thee that thou shouldst make associates with Me, of which thou hast no knowledge, then do not obey them, but keep them company desirably in this world, and follow the way of him who turns to Me; then unto Me you shall return, and I shall tell you what you were doing.'
|31|16|
`O my son, if it should be the weight of a grain of mustard seed, and it should be in a rock or in the heavens or in the earth, God shall bring it forth; God is Subtle, Aware.
|31|17|
O my son, establish the Prayer, bid the desirable, forbid the disgusting, and bear patiently what befalls thee; surely that is a matter of great resolution.
|31|18|
And do not turn thy cheek away from men in scorn, nor walk on the earth exultantly; God does not like any proud, boastful man.
|31|19|
And be modest in thy walk, and keep thy voice low; surely the most repulsive of voices is the voice of the ass.'
|31|20|
Have you not seen that God has subjected to you whatever is in the heavens and whatever is in the earth, and He has lavished on you His blessings, both open and hidden; yet there are men who dispute concerning God without any knowledge, or guidance, or an illuminating Book.
|31|21|
And when it is said to them, `follow what God has sent down', they say, `no, but we shall follow what we found our fathers on.' What! Even though the Devil was calling them to the punishment of the burning.
|31|22|
And whoso submits himself to God, and he is a good-doer, has laid hold of the most firm handle; and unto God is the end of all matters.
|31|23|
And whoso disbelieves, let not his unbelief grieve thee; to Us shall they return, then We will tell them what they did; surely God knows the thoughts in the breasts.
|31|24|
We shall let them enjoy a little, then compel them to a harsh punishment.
|31|25|
And if thou askest them, `who created the heavens and the earth,' they will surely say, `God'. Say, `praise be to God'. No, but most of them have no knowledge.
|31|26|
To God belongs whatever is in the heavens and the earth; surely God __ He is the All-sufficient, the Praiseworthy.
|31|27|
And if all the trees in the earth were pens, and the sea, with seven seas thereafter to replenish it (were ink), the Words of God would not be spent; surely God is Mighty, Wise.
|31|28|
Your creation and your upraising are not but as one soul; surely God is Hearing, Seeing.
|31|29|
Hast thou not seen that God makes the night to enter into the day, and makes the day to enter into the night, and has subjected the sun and the moon, all running to a stated term, and that God is aware of what you do?
|31|30|
That is because God is the Truth, and what they call, apart from Him, is false-hood, and that God is the High, the Great.
|31|31|
Hast thou not seen that the ships sail on the sea by God's blessing, that He may show you of His Signs? In that are surely Signs for every steadfast, thankful man.
|31|32|
And when the waves cover them like shadows, they call upon God, making obedience purely His; but when He delivers them to the land, then among them some are lukewarm. And none denies Our Signs except every treacherous, unthankful man.
|31|33|
O mankind, fear your Lord, and dread a day when a father shall not give satisfaction for his child, nor a child shall give satisfaction for his father in the least; God's promise is true, so let not the present life delude you, and let not the Deluder delude you concerning God.
|31|34|
Surely God __ with Him is the knowledge of the Hour; and He sends down the rain; and He knows what is in the wombs; and no soul knows what it shall earn tomorrow, and no soul knows in what land it shall die; surely God is Knowing, Aware.
|32|1|
Alif Lam Mim (A.L.M.).
|32|2|
The sending down of the Book, no doubt about it, is from the Lord of the world.
|32|3|
Or do they say, `he has forged it?' No, it is the Truth from thy Lord, that thou mayest warn a people to whom no warner came before thee, that they may be guided.
|32|4|
God is He who created the heavens and the earth and what between them is in six days, then took over the Throne. You have no protector apart from Him, nor a mediator; so will you not take heed?
|32|5|
He directs the Affair from the heaven to the earth, then it goes up to Him in a day whose measure is a thousand years of your counting.
|32|6|
That is the Knower of the unseen and the visible, the Mighty, the Merciful,
|32|7|
who made everything that He created handsome, and began the creation of man out of clay.
|32|8|
Then He made his progeny of an extraction of a mean water;
|32|9|
then He shaped him, and breathed in him of His Spirit, and made for you ears, eyes, and heart; little thanks you show.
|32|10|
And they say, `when we are lost in the earth, shall we be in a new creation?' No, they disbelieve in the meeting with their Lord.
|32|11|
Say, `the Angel of Death, who has been charged with you, will cause you to die, then you will be returned to your Lord.'
|32|12|
And if thou clouldst see the sinners hanging their heads before their Lord: `Our Lord, we have seen and heard; now return us that we may do righteousness, for we have sure faith.'
|32|13|
And if We had willed, We could have given every soul its guidance, but My Word has proved true that I will certainly fill up Hell with jinn and men all together.
|32|14|
`Now taste, for you forgot the meeting of this your day; We have also forgotten you; and taste the punishment of eternity for that you have been doing!'
|32|15|
Only those believe in Our Signs who, when they are reminded of them, fall down prostrate and celebrate the praise of their Lord, and they do not show arrogance.
|32|16|
Their sides forsake the beds, calling on their Lord in fear and hope, and they expend of that We have provided them.
|32|17|
And no soul knows what coolness of eyes is secretly kept for them, as a recompense for that they have been doing.
|32|18|
Is he who was a believer like him who was a transgressor? They are not equal.
|32|19|
As for those who believe and do righteous deeds, for them shall be gardens of eternal abode, as a hospitality for what they have been doing.
|32|20|
And as for those who transgressed, their abode shall be the Fire; whenever they desire to come out of it, they shall be restored into it, and it shall be said to them, `taste the punishment of the Fire which you have been giving lies to.'
|32|21|
And We shall surely make them taste some smaller punishment, besides the greater punishment, that they may return.
|32|22|
And who does greater wrong than he, who is reminded of the Signs of his Lord, then turns away from them? We will surely take vengeance upon the sinners.
|32|23|
And We gave Moses the Book, so be thou not in doubt of receiving it, and We made it a guidance for the Children of Israel;
|32|24|
and We appointed among them leaders to guide by Our command, when they showed patience; and they had sure faith in Our Signs.
|32|25|
Surely it is thy Lord who shall decide between them on the Day of Resurrection in what theydiffered.
|32|26|
Is it not a guidance to them, how many generations We destroyed before them in whose dwellings they walk? In that are surely Signs; so will they not hear?
|32|27|
And do they not see that We drive water to the barren land, and therewith bring forth crops, which their cattle and themselves eat? So will they not see?
|32|28|
And they say, `when shall be this Decision, if you are truthful?'
|32|29|
Say, `on the Day of Decision, their faith shall not profit the unbelievers, nor shall they be respited.'
|32|30|
So, turn thou away from them, and wait; they too are waiting.
|33|1|
O Prophet, fear God and do not obey the unbelievers and the hypocrites; God is surely Knowing, Wise.
|33|2|
And follow what is revealed to thee from thy Lord; God is surely aware of what you do.
|33|3|
And put thy trust in God; and God suffices as a care-taker.
|33|4|
God has not made for any man two hearts in his body; and He has not made your wives, whom you declare to be your mothers, your mothers; and He has not made your adopted sons your sons; that is your saying, words of your mouths; but God speaks the truth, and He guides to the Way.
|33|5|
Call them after their fathers; it is more just in the sight of God; and if you do not know their fathers, then they are your brothers in religion and your clients; and there is no blame on you in what you did by mistake, but only in what your hearts intended; and God is surely Forgiving, Merciful.
|33|6|
The Prophet is closer to the Believers than their selves, and his wives are their mothers; and the blood relations are closer to one another in the Book of God than the Believers and the Emigrants, except that you should act towards your friends desirably; this is inscribed in the Book.
|33|7|
And when We took from the Prophets their compact and from thee and from Noah, Abraham, Moses, Jasus, son of Mary, and We took from them a solemn compact,
|33|8|
that He might question the truthful concerning their truthfulness; and He has prepared for the unbelievers a painful punishment.
|33|9|
O Believers, remember God's blessing on you when hosts came upon you, and We loosed against them a wind and such hosts that you did not see; and God sees what you do.
|33|10|
When they came upon you from above you and from below you, and when the eyes swerved, and the hearts reached the throats, and you made many guesses about God.
|33|11|
There the Believers were tried and terribly shaken.
|33|12|
And when the hypocrites and those in whose hearts was sickness said, `God and His Messenger promised us not but delusion.'
|33|13|
And when a group of them said, `O people of Yathrib, it is no place for you, so return.' And a party of theirs asked leave of the Prophet, saying, `our houses are exposed'; though they were not exposed; they only desired to flee.
|33|14|
But if they had been invaded from its sides, and then they had been invited to turmoil, they would have surely joined it, and would have not stayed back but a little.
|33|15|
Yet they had made covenant with God before, that they would not turn their backs; and covenant with God shall be questioned.
|33|16|
Say, `flight will not profit you, if you flee from death or from being killed; and, even in that case, you will not enjoy life but little.'
|33|17|
Say, `who is it that shall defend you from God, if He desired evil for you, or desired mercy for you?' And they shall not find for them, apart from God, any friend or helper.
|33|18|
God indeed knows those of you who hinder, and those who say to their brothers, `come to us'; and they do not come to battle but little __
|33|19|
being reluctant to assist you; and when fear comes upon them, thou seest them looking at thee with their eyes rolling like one who faints because of death; then when the fear is gone, they attack you with sharp tongues, being covetous for the riches. Those have never believed, so God has made their works null and void; and that is easy for God.
|33|20|
They think the Confederates are not gone, and if the Confederates come, they would wish if they were desert-dwellers among the Bedouins, asking for the news of you; and if they were among you, they would not fight but little.
|33|21|
Surely you have a good model in God's Messenger, for him who looks forward to God and the Last Day and remembers God much.
|33|22|
And when the Believers saw the Confederates, they said, `this is what God and His Messenger promised us, and God and His Messenger spoke the truth'. And it only increased them in faith and submission.
|33|23|
Among the Believers are men who remained true to the covenant they had made with God; then some of them have fulfilled their vow and some of them are waiting and have not changed in the least,
|33|24|
that God may recompense the truthful for their truth and punish the hypocrites, if he will, or accept their repentance; God is surely Forgiving, Merciful.
|33|25|
And God turned back the unbelievers in their rage, they attained no good; and God sufficed the Believers in the battle; and God is surely Strong and Mighty.
|33|26|
And He brought down those of the People of the Book who supported them from their fortresses, and He cast terror in their hearts, so that some you killed, and some you made captives.
|33|27|
And He made you to inherit their land, their houses, their wealth, and the land you did not tread; and God is surely powerful over every-thing.
|33|28|
O Prophet, say to thy wives, `if you desire the life of this world and its adornment, then come, and I shall give you goods and let you off gracefully.
|33|29|
But if you desire God and His Messenger and the Final Home, then surely God has prepared for the good-doers among you a big wage.
|33|30|
O wives of the Prophet, if any of you commits a flagrant indecency, the punishment shall be doubled for her; and that is easy for God.
|33|31|
PART XXIVAnd whoso of you is obedient to God and His Messenger and does righteousness, We shall give her, her wage twice over, and We have prepared for her a generous provision.
|33|32|
O wives of the Prophet, you are not like any other woman; if you are godfearing, be not soft in speech, lest he, in whose heart is sickness, develops hope, but speak desirable words.
|33|33|
And stay in your houses, and do not display your finery, as it was displayed in the former Days of Ignorance, and establish the Prayer, pay the Due-alms, and obey God and His Messenger; God only desires, O People of the House, to put away from you the abomination, and cleanse you thoroughly.
|33|34|
And remember that which is recited in your houses of the Signs of God and the Wisdom; God is surely Subtle, Aware.'
|33|35|
Men and women who have surrendered, men and women who have believed, men and women who are obedient, men and women who are truthful, men and women who are patient, men and women who are humble, men and women who give in charity, men and women who fast, men and women who guard their private parts, men and women who remember God much __ for them God has prepared forgiveness and a big wage.
|33|36|
And it is not for any Believing man or a Believing woman, when God and His Messenger have decreed a matter, to have the choice in the matter concerning them; and whoso disobeys God and His Messenger has openly gone astray.
|33|37|
And when thou wast saying to him whom God had blessed and thou hadst favoured, `keep thy wife to thyself and fear God', and thou wast concealing in thy heart what God would reveal, and thou wast fearing people, though God had a better right that thou shouldst fear Him. Then, when Zaid had accomplished formalities concerning her, We gave her in marriage to thee, so that there should be no blame on the Believers concerning the wives of their adopted sons, when they accomplish formalities concerning them; and God's command is ever done.
|33|38|
There is no blame on the Prophet in what God has ordained for him; it has been God's tradition with those who have passed away before: __ and God's command is a destiny decreed; __
|33|39|
those who delivered the Messages of God and feared Him and feared none except God; and God suffices as a reckoner.
|33|40|
Muhammad is not the father of any of your men, but he is the Messenger of God and the Seal of the Prophets; and God has knowledge of everything.
|33|41|
O Believers, remember God much,
|33|42|
and extol Him at dawn and in the evening.
|33|43|
He it is who blesses you and also do His angels, to bring you forth from darkness into light; and He is Merciful to the Believers.
|33|44|
Their greeting, on the day they meet Him, will be `Peace'; and He has prepared for them a generous wage.
|33|45|
O Prophet, We have sent thee as a witness, a bearer of good news, a warner,
|33|46|
a summoner to God by His leave, and as an illuminating lamp.
|33|47|
And give thou good news to the Believers, that for them shall be a great bounty from God.
|33|48|
And do not obey the unbelievers and the hypocrites, and overlook hurt given by them, and trust in God; and God suffices as a care-taker.
|33|49|
O Believers, when you marry women, and then divorce them before you have touched them, you have no period to reckon against them; but give them some goods, and let them off gracefully.
|33|50|
O Prophet, We have made lawful for thee thy wives whom thou hast given their dowries; and those whom thy right hand owns out of the spoils of war that God has given thee; and daughters of thy paternal uncle, and daughters of thy paternal aunts, and daughters of thy maternal uncle, and daughters of thy maternal aunts, who have emigrated with thee, and any Believing woman, if she gives herself to the Prophet, provided the Prophet also desires to take her in marriage; it is exclusive for thee, apart from the Believers; We know what We have ordained for them concerning their wives and what their right hands own; it is so that there may be no blame on thee; and surely God is Forgiving, Merciful.
|33|51|
Thou mayest put off whom thou wilt out of them and mayest take to thee whom thou wilt; and if thou seekest any whom thou hast set aside, there is no blame on thee; thus it is likelier that their eyes will be cooled, and they will not be grieved, and all of them will be pleased with what thou givest them; and God knows what is in your hearts; and God is Knowing, Clement.
|33|52|
Women are not lawful to thee after this, nor that thou takest them in exchange for the wives, though their beauty may please thee, except what thy right hand owns; and God is watchful over everything.
|33|53|
O Believers, do not enter Prophet's houses, unless leave is given to you for a meal, without waiting for its cooking; but enter when you are invited; and when you have had the meal, disperse, not seeking to engage in talk; that hurts the Prophet, but he feels shy of you, but God feels not shy of the truth. And when you ask them (his wives) for any object, ask them from behind a curtain; that is cleaner for your hearts and their hearts; and it is not for you to hurt the Messenger of God, nor to marry his wives after him ever; that would be a grave thing in God's sight.
|33|54|
Whether you show a thing or hide it, surely God knows everything.
|33|55|
There is no blame on them (Prophet's wives) concerning their fathers, their sons, their brothers, their brothers' sons, their sisters' sons, their women, and what their right hands own; but fear God (you Prophet's wives); surely God is witness over everything.
|33|56|
God and His angels bless the Prophet; O Believers, bless you him, and pray him peace.
|33|57|
Those who hurt God and His Messenger, God has cursed them in this world and in the Hereafter, and has prepared for them a humiliating punishment.
|33|58|
And those who hurt the Believing men and Believing women, without their having earned it, they have surely taken upon them a calumny and a manifest sin.
|33|59|
O Prophet, say to thy wives, thy daughters and the women of the Believers to draw their veils close to them; that is more likely that they will be known and not hurt; and God is Forgiving, Merciful.
|33|60|
If the hypocrites, and those in whose hearts is sickness, and the agitators in the city do not give over, We shall urge thee against them, and then they will not remain therein as thy neighbours but little;
|33|61|
accursed, they shall be seized wherever they are come upon, and slaughtered all.
|33|62|
It was God's tradition with those who have passed away before, and thou shalt never find God's tradition changing.
|33|63|
They ask thee concerning the Hour. Say, `the knowledge of it is only with God;' and what shall make thee know if the Hour may be near!
|33|64|
God has cursed the unbelievers and has prepared for them a Blaze,
|33|65|
to dwell therein for ever, not finding any protector or helper.
|33|66|
On the day when their faces are turned about in the Fire, they shall say, `Ah, would that we had obeyed God and obeyed the Messenger.'
|33|67|
And they shall say, `our Lord, we obeyed our chiefs and our big ones, and they led us astray from the way.
|33|68|
Our Lord, give them double the punishment, and curse them with a big curse.'
|33|69|
O Believers, be not like those who hurt Moses, but God cleared him ofwhat they said; and he was high-honoured with God.
|33|70|
O Believers, fear God, and speak the words that hit the mark,
|33|71|
He will set right your works and forgive you your sins; and whoso obeys God and His Messenger, has surely achieved a mighty triumph.
|33|72|
We offered the trust to the heavens and the earth and the mountains, and they refused to take it and feared it, but man took it; he was surely wrong-doer and utterly ignorant __
|33|73|
that God may punish the hypocrites, men and women, and idolaters, men and women; and God may turn to the Believers, men and women; and God is surely Forgiving, Merciful.
|34|1|
Praise belongs to God, to whom belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is in the earth, and praise will be His in the Hereafter; and He is the Wise, the Aware.
|34|2|
He knows what enters into the earth and what comes forth from it, what comes down from the heaven and what goes up into it; and He is the Merciful, the Forgiving.
|34|3|
And the unbelievers say, `the Hour shall not come upon us'. Say, `no, by my Lord, who knows the unseen, it will surely come upon you; not the weight of an atom in the heavens or in the earth escapes from Him, and not anything smaller or greater than that is there but it is in a clear Book,
|34|4|
that He may recompense those who believe and do righteous deeds; theirs shall be forgiveness and a generous provision.
|34|5|
And those who strive to frustrate Our signs, theirs shall be punishment of a painful scourge.
|34|6|
And those who are given the knowledge see that what has been sent down to thee from thy Lord is the truth, and guides to the path of the Mighty, the Praiseworthy. 
|34|7|
And the unbelievers say, `shall we point out to you a man who will tell you that when you have been utterly broken into pieces, you shall be in a new creation?
|34|8|
Has he forged a lie against God, or is he possessed?' Not so; those who do not believe in the Hereafter are under punishment and in far error.
|34|9|
But have they not considered what lies before them and what lies behind them of the heaven and earth? If We will, We would make the earth to swallow them, or drop down fragments of the heaven on them; in that is surely a Sign for every penitent servant.
|34|10|
And We gave David bounty from Us: `O mountains and birds, echo God's praises along with him'; and We softened iron for him: 
|34|11|
`make thou coats of mail, and measure thou well the links, and act you right; I see what you do.'
|34|12|
And to Solomon, (We subjected) the wind whose morning course was of a month and evening course of a month, and We made the fount of molten brass flow for him. And of the jinn, some worked before him by the leave of his Lord. And (We said,) `whoso swerved from Our command, We would let them taste the punishment of the Blaze.'
|34|13|
They made for him what he would __ of the arsenals, statues, porringers like water-troughs, and anchored cooking pots: __ `work, O House of David, thankfully,' and few among My servants are thankful.
|34|14|
Then, when We decreed death for him, nothing pointed to them of his death but a creature of the earth that ate his staff; then when he fell down, the jinn realized that if they had known the unseen, they would not have remained in the humiliating punishment.
|34|15|
For Sheba there was a Sign in their dwelling place __ two gardens, one on the right and one on the left: `Eat of your Lord's provision, and give thanks to Him; a good land and a Forgiving Lord.'
|34|16|
But they turned aside, so We loosed on them devastating flood and gave them, in exchange for their two gardens, two gardens bearing bitter fruit and tamarisk, and some few lote-trees.
|34|17|
That We recompensed them for their ingratitude; and do We so recompense any but the ungrateful?
|34|18|
And We had set between them and between the cities that We had blessed visible towns, and We had determined the journey between them: `Journey through them, by night and day, in security.'
|34|19|
But they said, `our Lord, prolong the stages of our travel,' and they wronged themselves; so We made them as tales and broke them utterly to pieces. Surely in that are Signs for every steadfast, thankful man.
|34|20|
And Iblis proved true his opinion about them, and they followed him, except a section of the Believers.
|34|21|
Yet he had no authority over them, except that We might know him who believes in the Hereafter, from him who is in doubt of it; and thy Lord is Guardian over everything.
|34|22|
Say, `call on those you assert apart from God; they do not possess as the weight of an atom in the heavens or in the earth, and they have no partnership in them, and He has no supporter among them'.
|34|23|
And intercession does not profit with Him, except for him to whom He gives leave; till when terror is removed from their hearts, they will say, `what was it that your Lord said?' They will say, `the truth; and He is the High, the Great.'
|34|24|
Say, `who provides for you from the heavens and the earth?' Say, `God, and either we or you are on guidance, or in clear error.'
|34|25|
Say, `you shall not be questioned about the sins we commit, nor shall we be questioned as to what you do.'
|34|26|
Say, `our Lord will bring us together, then decide between us with truth; and He is the All-decider, the Knowing'.
|34|27|
Say, `show me those you have joined to Him as associates? No indeed, He is God, the Mighty, the Wise.'
|34|28|
And We have not sent thee, but to entire mankind, as a bearer of good news and as a warner, but most men do not know.
|34|29|
And they say, `when shall this promise be fulfilled, if you are truthful?'
|34|30|
Say `you have the appointment of a Day that you shall neither put back, nor bring forward by an hour?'
|34|31|
And the unbelievers say, `we will not believe in this Qur'an, nor in what is before it.' Ah, if thou couldst only see when the wrongdoers are stationed before their Lord, casting balance on one another. The oppressed will say to the arrogant, `had it not been for you, we would have been believers.'
|34|32|
The arrogant will say to the oppressed, `was it we who barred you from the guidance after it had come to you? No, rather you indeed were sinners'.
|34|33|
And those that were oppressed will say to the arrogant, `no, but by devising night and day, you bid us to disbelieve in God and to make compeers to Him.' And they will conceal their remorse when they see the punishment; and We put fetters on the necks of the unbelievers. Shall they be recompensed except for what they have been doing? 
|34|34|
And We did not send any warner to a city but its affluent men said, `we disbelieve in the Message you have been sent with.'
|34|35|
And they said, `we are more abundant in wealth and children, and we shall not be punished.'
|34|36|
Say, `surely my Lord outspreads and straitens the provision for whom He will, but most men do not know.'
|34|37|
And it is not your wealth nor your children that shall bring you in nearness to Us, but he who believes and acts right, for them shall be the double recompense for what they did, and they shall be secure in the lofty chambers.
|34|38|
And those who strive to frustrate Our Signs, they shall be arraigned into the punishment.
|34|39|
Say, `my Lord outspreads and straitens the provision for whom he will of His servants; and whatever thing you expend, He will replace it; and He is the best of the providers.'
|34|40|
And on the day when He shall muster them all together, then He shall say to the angels, `was it you that they were serving?'
|34|41|
They shall say, `Holy be Thee! Thou art our Protector, apart from them! No, but they were serving the jinn; most of them were believers in them' __ 
|34|42|
`So to-day, you have no power to profit or hurt one another.' And We shall say to the wrongdoers, `taste the punishment of the Fire which you were giving lies to.'
|34|43|
And When Our clear sings arerecited to them, they say, `this is naught but a man who desires to bar you from that your fathers served'; and they say, `this is only a forged lie'. And the unbelievers say of the truth, when it has come to them, `this is not but a clear sorcery.'
|34|44|
But We gave them no Books to study, and We did not send any warner to them before thee.
|34|45|
And those that were before them also cried lies, and they did not attain a tenth of what We gave them, yet they gave lies to My Messengers; then how was My denial!
|34|46|
Say, `I give you but one admonition, that you stand to God by twos and individually, then ponder; your companion has no madness; he is only a warner to you before a terrible punishment.'
|34|47|
Say, `any wage that I ask of you, that is yours; my wage is only upon God; and He is witness over everything.'
|34|48|
Say, `my Lord hurls the truth __ the All-knowing of the Unseen.' 
|34|49|
Say, `the truth has come, and the falsehood neither begins nor repeats'.
|34|50|
Say, `if I am astray, then I am astray only against myself, and if I am guided, it is due to what my Lord reveals to me; He is Hearing and Near.'
|34|51|
And if thou couldst see when they are terrified, and there is no escape, and they are seized from a place, nearby;
|34|52|
and they say, `we believe in it'; but how can they attain from a place far away,
|34|53|
when they denied it before, and were guessing at the Unseen from a place, far away.
|34|54|
And a barrier is placed between them and what they desire, as was done with their types before; they are surely in a disquieting doubt.
|35|1|
Praise be to God, the Originator of the heavens and the earth, who appoints the angels, as messengers, having wings, two, three and four. He adds to creation as He will; surely God is powerful over everything.
|35|2|
Whatever mercy God opens to mankind, there is none to withhold it, and whatever He withholds, there is none to release it after Him; and He is the Mighty, the Wise.
|35|3|
O mankind, remember God's blessing upon you. Is there any creator, other than God, who provides for you from the heaven and the earth? There is no god but He; how are you then perverted?
|35|4|
And if they give lies to thee, then Messengers before thee were also given lies to; and to God are all matters returned.
|35|5|
O mankind, God's promise is true, so let not the present life delude you, and let not the Deluder delude you regarding God.
|35|6|
Surely the Devil is an enemy to you, so take him as an enemy; he calls his faction only, that they may be among the people of the Blaze.
|35|7|
Those who disbelieve, for them shall be a terrible punishment. And those who believe and do righteous deeds, for them shall be forgiveness and a big wage.
|35|8|
And what of him, whom the evil of his deeds is adorned so that he sees it handsome? But God sends astray whom he will, and guides whom He will; so let not thy soul pass away in regrets for them; surley God knows what they work.
|35|9|
And God is He who looses the winds, and they stir up a cloud, then We drive it to a dead land, and, with it, revive the earth, after it is dead __ thus is the Uprising.
|35|10|
If any desires glory, then glory belongs to God altogether; to Him good words go up, and He uplifts the righteous deeds. And those who devise evil deeds for them shall be a terrible punishment; and their device is a thing to perish.
|35|11|
And God created you of dust, then of a sperm-drop, then He made you pairs. And no female bears nor lays down, but it is in His knowledge. And none, who is given a long life, lives long, nor anything is diminished in his life, but it is in a Book; surely that is easy for God.
|35|12|
And the two seas are not equal; this is sweet, fresh, to pleasant drink, and that is bitter salt; yet from each, you eat fresh flesh, and bring forth ornaments that you wear; and thou seest the ships ploughing through it, that you may seek of His bounty, and perhaps you will be thankful.
|35|13|
He makes the night to enter into the day and makes the day to enter into the night, and He has subjected the sun and the moon, each running to a stated term. That is God, your Lord, to whom belongs the kingdom; and those whom you call upon, apart from Him, do not possess even the skin of a date-stone.
|35|14|
If you call upon them, they do not hear your call; and if they heard, they would not answer you; and, on the Day of Resurrection, they will deny your associating (them with God); and none will tell thee like the One Aware. 
|35|15|
O mankind, you are poor before God, and God __ He is the All-sufficient, the Praiseworthy.
|35|16|
If He will, He will take you away and bring a new creation;
|35|17|
and that is no great matter for God.
|35|18|
And no bearer of load bears the load of another; and if one heavily burdened calls for its load to be carried, not a thing of it will be carried, though he be a near kinsman. Thou warnest only those who fear their Lord, without seeing, and establish the Prayer; and whoso purifies himself, purifies himself for his own good; and to God is the destination.
|35|19|
And the blind and the seeing man are not equal,
|35|20|
nor the darkness and the light,
|35|21|
nor the shade and the torrid heat;
|35|22|
and the living and the dead are not equal; God makes to hear whom he will; and thou shalt not make to hear those who are in the tombs.
|35|23|
Thou art not but a warner.
|35|24|
Surely We have sent thee with the truth, as a bearer of good news and as a warner; and there is no community but a warner has gone among them.
|35|25|
And if they give thee lies, then those before them gave lies too; their Messengers came to them with the Clear Signs, and the Psalms, and the illuminating Book.
|35|26|
Then I seized the unbelievers, so how was My denial!
|35|27|
Hast thou not seen that God sends down water from heaven, and therewith We bring forth fruits of different hues; and in the mountains are streaks, white and red, of different hues and pitch black?
|35|28|
And men, animals and cattle are similarly of different hues; yet among His servants only the men of knowledge fear God; surely God is Mighty, Forgiving.
|35|29|
Those who recite the Book of God, and establish the Prayer, and expend of that We have provided them, secretly and openly, look for a commerce that will never perish,
|35|30|
that He may pay them in full their wages and increase for them out of His bounty; He is Forgiving, Thankful.
|35|31|
And that We have revealed to thee of the Book is the truth, confirming what is before it; God is surely aware of and sees His servants.
|35|32|
Then, We bequeathed the Book on those of Our servants whom We chose; now among them is he who wrongs himself, and among them is the lukewarm, and among them is the outstripper in good works, by the leave of God __ that indeed is the great bounty.
|35|33|
They shall enter Gardens of Eternity, wherein they shall be adorned with bracelets of gold and with pearls, and their dress therein shall be of silk.
|35|34|
And they shall say, `praise be to God, who has taken away all grief from us; surely our Lord is Forgiving, Thankful,
|35|35|
who, out of His bounty, has made us to dwell in the Home of Eternity, wherein no toil touches us, nor fatigue.
|35|36|
And the unbelievers, theirs shall be the Fire of Hell; they shall neither be done with to die, nor its punishment shall be lightened for them; thus We recompense every ungrateful one.
|35|37|
And they shall cry out there, `our Lord, take us out, and we will do righteousness, other than that we have been doing' __ `What! did We not give you life, long enough to pay heed for him who would pay heed, and the warner also came to you? Now taste, and there is no helper for the wrongdoers?'
|35|38|
God knows the unseen of the heavens and the earth; He knows the thoughts in the breasts.
|35|39|
It is He who made you viceroys inthe earth; then whoso disbelieves, his unbelief shall stand against him; and their unbelief increases nothing for the unbelievers but hatred with God, and their unbelief increases nothing for the unbelievers but loss.
|35|40|
Say, `have you seen your associate-gods, whom you call upon, apart from God? Show me what they have created in the earth, or have they any partnership in the heavens; or have We given them a Book so that they are on a Clear Sign from it?' No, but the wrong-doers promise one another nothing but delusion.
|35|41|
God holds the heavens and the earth, lest they move away; and if they moved, none would hold them after Him; surely He is Penitent, Forgiving.
|35|42|
And they swore by God their most earnest oaths that if a warner came to them, they would be more guided than any one of the communities; but when a warner came to them, it increased them in aversion only __
|35|43|
showing arrogance in the earth and devising evil; but the evil device encompasses none except its own people. Now are they waiting only for the tradition of the ancients? And thou shalt never find any change in God's tradition, and thou shalt never find any alteration in God's tradition.
|35|44|
And have they not journeyed in the land and beheld how was the end of those before them, though they were stronger than them in might? And God is not such that anything in the heavens or in the earth can frustrate Him; surely He is Knowing, Powerful.
|35|45|
And if God were to take men to task for what they have earned, He would not leave on the surface (of earth) any creature; but He is deferring them to a stated term; and when their term is come __ then surely God sees His servants.
|36|1|
Ya Sin (Y.S.).
|36|2|
By the Wise Qur'an,
|36|3|
thou art surely one of the Envoys,
|36|4|
on a straight path;
|36|5|
(it is) the sending down of the Mighty, the Merciful,
|36|6|
that thou mayest warn a people whose fathers were not warned, and they are unaware.
|36|7|
The Word has indeed proved true against most of them, so they do not believe.
|36|8|
We have put fetters on their necks, and they are upto the chins, so their heads are raised up.
|36|9|
And We have put a barrier before them and a barrier behind them, so they do not see.
|36|10|
And it is equal for them whether thou warn them or warn them not, they will not believe.
|36|11|
Thou only warnest him who follows the Remembrance and fears the All-merciful without seeing; so give him the good news of forgiveness and a generous wage.
|36|12|
It is We who give life to the dead and write down what they have forwarded and their marks (that they have left behind;); and everything We have numbered in a clear diary.
|36|13|
And strike for them a similitude of the people of the town. When Envoys came to it;
|36|14|
when We sent to them two, and they gave them lies; then We reinforced them with a third, and they said, `we are Envoys to you.'
|36|15|
They said, `you are not but mortals like us, and the All-merciful has not sent down anything; you are only speaking lies.'
|36|16|
They said `our Lord knows, we are surely Envoys to you.
|36|17|
And our duty is not but to deliver the Manifest Message.'
|36|18|
They said, `we augur ill of you; if you do not give over, we will stone you, and there shall befall upon you a painful punishment from us'.
|36|19|
They said, `your augury is with you. Is it because you are being reminded? No, but you are an extravagant people.'
|36|20|
And there came running from the furthest part of the city a man; he said, `my people, follow the Envoys;
|36|21|
follow those who do not ask of you any wage, and who are guided.
|36|22|
And why should not I serve Him who originated me and to whom you shall be returned?
|36|23|
Shall I take, apart from Him, gods whose intercession, if the All-merciful desires to harm me, shall not avail me in the least, nor will they rescue me?
|36|24|
In that case I should indeed be clearly astray.
|36|25|
I believe in your Lord, so hear me.'
|36|26|
It was said, `enter Paradise.' He said, `ah, would that my people knew,
|36|27|
how my Lord has forgiven me and has placed me among the honoured.'
|36|28|
And We did not send down upon his people, after him, any host from the heaven, and We never send down any.
|36|29|
It was only one Cry, and lo, they were silent and still.
|36|30|
Woe for the servants! Never a Messenger comes to them but they mock at him.
|36|31|
Have they not seen how many a generation We destroyed before them, and that they do not return to them?
|36|32|
And all will be arraigned before Us, altogether.
|36|33|
And a Sign for them is the dead land that We quickened and brought forth from it grain, whereof they eat.
|36|34|
And We made therein gardens of palms and vines, and therein We caused fountains to gush forth,
|36|35|
that they may eat of its fruit, and their hands did not make it; so will they not be thankful?
|36|36|
Holy be He, who created all the pairs of what the earth produces, and of themselves, and of what they do not know.
|36|37|
And a Sign for them is the night; We strip off the day from it, and lo, they are in darkness.
|36|38|
And the sun moves on its resting place, that is the ordaining of the Mighty, the Knowing.
|36|39|
And the moon, We have ordained for it stages, till it returns like an old palm bough.
|36|40|
It behoves not the sun to overtake the moon, nor does the night outstrip the day; and all are floating in an orbit.
|36|41|
And a Sign for them is that We carried their offspring in the laden ship,
|36|42|
and We have created for them the like of it whereon they ride.
|36|43|
And if We will, We may drown them, then they have none to cry to, nor are they rescued,
|36|44|
except as a mercy from Us and enjoyment for a time.
|36|45|
And when it is said to them, `fear what is before you and what is behind you, that you may find mercy.'
|36|46|
Yet no Sign of the signs of their Lord comes to them but they turn away from it.
|36|47|
And when it is said to them, `expend of what God has provided you,' the unbelievers say to the Believers, `shall we feed him whom God, if the willed, would have fed? You are but clearly astray!' 
|36|48|
And they say, `when shall this promise come to pass, if you are truthful?'
|36|49|
They are waiting only for one Cry which will seize them, while they will yet be disputing.
|36|50|
Then they will not be able to make a testament, nor will they return to their families.
|36|51|
And the Trumpet shall be blown, then lo, they are sliding down from the tombs to their Lord.
|36|52|
They say, `woe to us! Who has raised us from our sleeping place?' __ `This is what the All-merciful promised, and the Envoys spoke the truth.'
|36|53|
It was only one Cry, then lo, they are all arraigned before Us.
|36|54|
So today no soul shall be wronged in the least, and you shall not be recompensed except for what you have been doing.
|36|55|
Today the inhabitants of Paradise are busy in rejoicing;
|36|56|
they and their wives are in the shades, reclining on couches;
|36|57|
for them therein are fruits and whatever they call for.
|36|58|
`Peace' is the word from a Merciful Lord.
|36|59|
`And, today, get yourselves apart, O Sinners!
|36|60|
Did I not make covenant with you, O Children of Adam, that you shall not serve the Devil; surely he is on open enemy to you;
|36|61|
and that you shall serve Me __ this is a straight path.
|36|62|
And he led astray big multitudes of you; did you not thenunderstand?
|36|63|
Here is Hell, that you were promised.
|36|64|
Enter it today, for you disbelieved.
|36|65|
Today We set a seal on their mouths, and their hands speak to Us, and their feet bear witness to what they have been earning.
|36|66|
And if We will, We would have obliterated their eyes, then they would race to the path, but how would they see?
|36|67|
And if We will, We would have transformed them in their place, then they would not be able to go forward, nor return.
|36|68|
And to whom We give long life, We reverse him in constitution; do they not understand?
|36|69|
And We have not taught him poetry, and it is not becoming of him. It is only a Remembrance and a plain Reading (Qur'an),
|36|70|
that he may warn him who is alive, and that the Word may prove true against the unbelievers.
|36|71|
And did they not see that We have created for them of that Our hands made __ cattle, and now they are their masters.
|36|72|
And We have subdued them to them, so that some of them they ride, and some they eat.
|36|73|
And they have (other) uses in them and also beverages; so will they not be thankful?
|36|74|
Yet they have taken gods, apart from God, that they may be helped.
|36|75|
They are not able to help them, and they will be their hosts that will be arraigned.
|36|76|
So let not their talk grieve thee; We know what they conceal and what they make public.
|36|77|
And has not man seen that We created him of a sperm-drop? Then, lo, he is an open disputant?
|36|78|
And he has struck for Us a similitude, and has forgotten his creation; he says, `who will quicken the bones when they are decayed?'
|36|79|
Say, `He, who originated them the first time, will quicken them; and He knows every creation;
|36|80|
He who made for you, out of the green tree, fire, then lo, from it you kindle'.
|36|81|
Is not He, who created the heavens and the earth, able to create the like of them? Yes indeed; for He is the All-creator, the Knowing.
|36|82|
His command, when He desires a thing, is only to say to it, `Be', and it is. 
|36|83|
So Holy be He, in whose hand is the control of everything, and to whom you shall be returned.
|37|1|
By those that range in ranks,
|37|2|
then scare to terrify,
|37|3|
then recite the Remembrance,
|37|4|
your God is surely One;
|37|5|
the Lord of the heavens and the earth and what between them is, and the Lord of the Easts.
|37|6|
We have adorned the nearer heaven with the adornment of the planets,
|37|7|
and to guard against every rebel devil;
|37|8|
they cannot listen to the High Council, for they are pelted from every side,
|37|9|
to be repelled, and for them is a perpetual punishment,
|37|10|
but any who snatches away a point, a shining flame follows him.
|37|11|
Now ask them to pronounce: `are they stronger in constitution or (others) that We have created? We created them from a sticky clay.
|37|12|
No, but thou wonderest, and they scoff;
|37|13|
and when reminded, do not pay heed;
|37|14|
and when they see a Sign, would scoff;
|37|15|
and they say, `this is not but clear sorcery.
|37|16|
What! When we are dead and become dust and bones, shall we be raised up?
|37|17|
What! and our ancient fathers?'
|37|18|
Say, `yes, and in all lowliness.'
|37|19|
For it shall be only a single scare, then lo, they are watching.
|37|20|
And they say, `woe to us; this is the Day of Recompense.'__ 
|37|21|
`This is the Day of Decision, that you were giving lies to.'
|37|22|
`Muster the wrong-doers, and their wives, and what they were serving,
|37|23|
apart from God, and guide them to the path of Hell.
|37|24|
But halt them, for they are to be questioned: 
|37|25|
`What ails you, that you do not help one another?'
|37|26|
No, today, they have resigned themselves in submission.
|37|27|
And of them some advance on others, asking questions.
|37|28|
They say, `you used to come to us from the right side.'
|37|29|
Those say, `no, but you yourselves were not believers,
|37|30|
and we had no authority over you; no, you were a transgressing people.
|37|31|
Now our Lord's Word is realized against us, we have to taste it.
|37|32|
We did pervert you, for we ourselves were perverts.'
|37|33|
So, on that day, they all will be sharers in the punishment.
|37|34|
Thus We deal with the sinners.
|37|35|
When it was said to them `there is no god but God', they used to show arrogance,
|37|36|
and said `shall we forsake our gods for a mad poet?'
|37|37|
`No, he brought the truth and confirmed the Envoys.
|37|38|
Now you shall be tasting the painful punishment;
|37|39|
and you shall not be recompensed except accordign to what you were doing'.
|37|40|
But God's exclusive servants; __ 
|37|41|
for them shall be a known provision __
|37|42|
fruits; and they shall be high-honoured,
|37|43|
in the gardens of bliss,
|37|44|
sitting upon couches, face to face.
|37|45|
A cup from a fountain, being passed round to them,
|37|46|
white, delicious to the drinkers,
|37|47|
no dizziness in it, nor will they be intoxicated by it.
|37|48|
And with them shall be wide-eyed maidens restraining their glances,
|37|49|
as if they were covered eggs.
|37|50|
Then some of them will advance upon others asking questions.
|37|51|
A speaker out of them will say, `I had a comrade,
|37|52|
who would say, `art thou really among the conformers?
|37|53|
What! When we are dead and become dust and bones, shall we be recompensed?'
|37|54|
He will say, `will you be looking down?'
|37|55|
And he looks and sees him in the midst of Hell.
|37|56|
He says, `by God, thou had almost destroyed me!
|37|57|
And if it were not my Lord's blessing, I would have been among the arraigned.
|37|58|
Is it that we shall not be dying,
|37|59|
except our first death, and we shall not be punished.
|37|60|
Surely this is the mighty triumph.
|37|61|
For the like of this, then, let the workers work.'
|37|62|
Is that better as a hospitality or the tree of cactus?
|37|63|
We have made it a trial for the wrong-doers.
|37|64|
It is a tree that comes forth in the root of Hell;
|37|65|
its spathes are as the heads of the devils.
|37|66|
They shall surely be eating of it, and of it filling the bellies.
|37|67|
Then, on top of it, they will be having a brew of hot water.
|37|68|
Then their return shall be to Hell.
|37|69|
They found their fathers astray,
|37|70|
and they are running on their footsteps.
|37|71|
And, indeed, before them, most of the ancients went astray.
|37|72|
And We had sent among them warners.
|37|73|
Then, behold, how was the end of those that were warned,
|37|74|
except for God's exclusive servants.
|37|75|
And Noah called to Us; then how excellent were the Answerers!
|37|76|
And We delivered him and his family from the great distress,
|37|77|
and We made his offspring the survivors,
|37|78|
and left for him among the later folk:
|37|79|
`Peace be on Noah among all the people!'
|37|80|
Thus We recompense the good-doers.
|37|81|
He was among Our Believing servants.
|37|82|
Then We drowned the others.
|37|83|
And of his party was Abraham.
|37|84|
When he came to his Lord with a pure heart.
|37|85|
When he said to his father and his people, `what do you serve?
|37|86|
Is it a calumny __ gods apart from God __ that you desire?
|37|87|
What guess you then about the Lord of the world?'
|37|88|
And he cast a glance at the stars,
|37|89|
and said, `I am sick.'
|37|90|
Then they turned away from him, turning their backs.
|37|91|
And he quietly went to their gods, and said, `will you not eat?
|37|92|
What ails you, that you do not speak?'
|37|93|
And he turned upon them, striking with the right hand.
|37|94|
Then people advanced to him in all haste.
|37|95|
He said, `do you serve what you hew,
|37|96|
while God created you, and what you make?'
|37|97|
They said, `build a building for him and cast him in the furnace.'
|37|98|
So they desired a guile against him, but We made them the lowest.
|37|99|
And he said, `I am going to my Lord; He will guide me.' __
|37|100|
`My Lord, bestow on me one of the righteous.'
|37|101|
And We gave him good news of a clement boy.
|37|102|
Then, when he reached the age of running with him, he said, `my son, I see a dream that I sacrifice thee; consider what thou thinkest?' He said, `my father, do as thou art bidden; thou shalt, God willing, find me one of the patient.'
|37|103|
So when they had surrendered, and he flung him upon his brow,
|37|104|
We called to him, `Abraham,
|37|105|
thou hast confirmed the vision; thus We recompense the good-doers.
|37|106|
Surely this was the manifest trial.'
|37|107|
And We ransomed him with a mighty sacrifice.
|37|108|
And We left for him among the later folk: 
|37|109|
`Peace be upon Abraham.'
|37|110|
So We recompense be good-doers.
|37|111|
He was among Our Believing servants.
|37|112|
And We gave him good news of Isaac, a Prophet, one of the righteous.
|37|113|
And We blessed him and Isaac. Now among their offspring are (both) good-doers and clear self-wrongers.
|37|114|
And We favoured Moses and Aaron;
|37|115|
and We delivered them and their people from the great distress;
|37|116|
and We helped them, so that they were the victors.
|37|117|
And We gave them the Enlightening Book;
|37|118|
and We guided them to the Straight Path.
|37|119|
And We left for them among the later folk:
|37|120|
`Peace be upon Moses and Aaron!'
|37|121|
Thus We recompense the good-doers.
|37|122|
They were among our Believing servants.
|37|123|
And Elias was among the Envoys.
|37|124|
When he said to his people, `will you not be godfearing?
|37|125|
Do you call on Baal, and forsake the Best of the creators __
|37|126|
God, your Lord, and the Lord of your ancient fathers?'
|37|127|
But they gave lies to him, so they will surely be arraigned, __
|37|128|
except for God's exclusive servants.
|37|129|
And We left for him among the later folk: 
|37|130|
`Peace be upon Elias!'
|37|131|
Thus We recompense the good-doers.
|37|132|
He was among Our Believing servants.
|37|133|
And Lot was among the Envoys.
|37|134|
When We delivered him and his family altogether,
|37|135|
except an old woman among those who stayed behind.
|37|136|
Then We utterly destroyed the others.
|37|137|
And you indeed pass by them in the morning,
|37|138|
and in the night; will you not understand?
|37|139|
And Jonah was among the Envoys.
|37|140|
When he fled to the laden ship,
|37|141|
and he cast lots and was among the rebutted.
|37|142|
Then the whale swallowed him, and he was to blame.
|37|143|
And had he not been of those that celebrate God,
|37|144|
he would have remained in its belly, till the day they shall be raised.
|37|145|
And We cast him on the wilderness, and he was sick;
|37|146|
and we caused to grow over him a plant of gourd.
|37|147|
And We sent him to a hundred thousand or more,
|37|148|
and they believed; so We gave them enjoyment for a time.
|37|149|
Now ask them for a pronouncement: Has thy Lord daughters and they sons?
|37|150|
Or did We create the angels females, and they were witnesses?
|37|151|
Behold, it is out of their calumny that they say,
|37|152|
`God has begotten'; and they are surely liars.
|37|153|
Has He chosen daughters above sons?
|37|154|
What ails you, how do you judge?
|37|155|
Will you not take heed?
|37|156|
Or have you a clear authority?
|37|157|
Then bring your Book, if you are truthful!
|37|158|
And they have set up a kinship between Him and the jinn, while the jinn know that they shall be arraigned __
|37|159|
Holy be God, above that they describe;
|37|160|
except for God's exclusive servants.
|37|161|
Now, you and what you serve,
|37|162|
you cannot tempt any against Him,
|37|163|
except him who shall enter the Blaze.
|37|164|
`And there is none among us but he has a known station;
|37|165|
and surely we are the rangers;
|37|166|
and surely we are those that celebrate Him'.
|37|167|
And they indeed used to say,
|37|168|
`if only we had a Reminder from the ancients,
|37|169|
we would have been God's exclusive servants.'
|37|170|
So they have disbelieved in it, but they will soon know.
|37|171|
And Our Word has already gone forth to Our servants, the Envoys:
|37|172|
`Surely they, only they, shall be helped;
|37|173|
and surely only Our host shall be the victors.'
|37|174|
So turn away from them for a while,
|37|175|
and see them, they shall soon see!
|37|176|
Do they seek to hasten Our punishment?
|37|177|
But when it lands in their courtyard, how evil will be the morning of those that are warned!
|37|178|
And turn thou away from them for a while,
|37|179|
and see; they shall soon see!
|37|180|
Holy be thy Lord, the Lord of Glory, above that they describe;
|37|181|
and peace be upon the Envoys;
|37|182|
and praise be to God, the Lord of the world.
|38|1|
Sad (S)__ by the Qur'an, containing the Admonition;
|38|2|
but the unbelievers are steeped in pride and opposition.
|38|3|
How many a generation We destroyed before them and they cried, but there was no time to escape. 
|38|4|
And they wonder that there has come to them a warner from among them, and the unbelievers say, `this is a sorcerer and a big liar.
|38|5|
Has he made all the gods One God? This is indeed a strange thing.'
|38|6|
And the chiefs among them departed: `move and adhere to your gods; this is a thing to be desired.
|38|7|
We never heard of this in the last creed; this is nothing but an invention.
|38|8|
Has the Admonition been sent down on him out of us?' No, they are in doubt of My Admonition. No, they have not yet tasted My punishment.
|38|9|
Or do they have the treasures of the mercy of thy Lord, the Mighty, the All-bestowing?
|38|10|
Or is theirs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth and what between them is? Then let them go up the cords.
|38|11|
Of all the confederates, the host that is here shall be routed.
|38|12|
Before them, gave lies the people of Noah, Ad, and Pharaoh __ the holder of the pegs,
|38|13|
Thamood, the people of Lot, and the men of the Wood __ those were the confederates.
|38|14|
Everyone gave lies to the Messengers, so my retribution was justified.
|38|15|
And these are not waiting but for a single blast which will have no break.
|38|16|
And they say, `our Lord, hasten to us our share before the Day of Reckoning.'
|38|17|
Bear thou patiently what they say, and mention Our servant, David, the man of might; he was a penitent.
|38|18|
We subjected With him, the mountains to extoll at evening and sunrise,
|38|19|
and also the birds, duly mustered; everyone was penitent to Him.
|38|20|
And We strengthened his kingdom, and gave him wisdom and (power of) decisive speech.
|38|21|
And has the tale of the litigants come to thee? When they scaled the guarded chamber;
|38|22|
when they entered upon David, and he was frightened of them; they said, `fear not; as two litigants, one of us has aggressed the other, so judge between us aright, and do not violate, and guide us to the even path.
|38|23|
This is my brother; he has ninety nine ewes, while I have one ewe; yet he says, `give it to my charge, and he has dominated me in speech.'
|38|24|
He said, `he has wronged thee in demanding thy ewe to be added to his ewes; and surely many of the partners aggress one another, except those who believe and do righteous deeds __ and how few they are!' And David thought that We had tried him, so he sought forgiveness of his Lord, and fell down on knees, and turned to God.
|38|25|
So We forgave him that; and indeed he had with Us a near place and a handsome resort. __
|38|26|
`O David, We have made thee a viceroy in the earth, so judge between men aright, and do not follow caprice, lest it lead thee astray from the way of God; surely those who go astray from the way of God, for them shall be a terrible punishment, for that they forgot the Day of Reckoning'.
|38|27|
And We have not created the heavens and the earth and what between them is in vain; that is the thinking of the unbelievers; so woe to the unbelievers because of the Fire!
|38|28|
Or shall We make those who believe and do righteous deeds as those who cause disorder in the earth, or shall We make the godfearing like the lawbreakers?
|38|29|
A Blessed Book We have sent down to thee, that they may ponder over its signs, and that men of understanding my pay heed.
|38|30|
And We bestowed on David Solomon; how excellent a servant he was! He was a penitent.
|38|31|
When the swift standing steeds were presented to him in the evening,
|38|32|
he said, `I have a liking for the good things more than the remembrance of my Lord' __ till when the sun was hidden behind the veil (he said,)
|38|33|
`return them to me'; and he started stroking their shanks and necks.
|38|34|
And We put Solomon to trials, and We cast a body on his throne, then he turned to God.
|38|35|
He said, `my Lord, forgive me and bestow on me a kingdom that may not befall anyone after me; surely Thou art the All-bestower.'
|38|36|
So We subjected to him the wind, that softly blew at his command wherever he would go,
|38|37|
and also the devils, everyone a builder and a diver,
|38|38|
and others bound in chains.
|38|39|
`This is Our gift so bestow or withhold without reckoning.'
|38|40|
And surely he has a near place with Us and a handsome resort.
|38|41|
And mention Our servant Job; when he called to his Lord, `the Devil has afflicted me with weariness and punishment' __ 
|38|42|
`Stamp thy foot; here is a cool washing place and a drink?'
|38|43|
And We gave to him his family, and the like of them with them, as a mercy from Us, and a Reminder for men of understanding.
|38|44|
`And take in thy hand a bundle of bushes and strike with it, and do not break thy oath.' We found him patient; how excellent a servant he was! he was a penitent.
|38|45|
And mention Our servants Abraham, Isaac and Jacob __ men of might and vision.
|38|46|
We purified them exclusively for the Remembrance of the House.
|38|47|
And surely in Our sight they are among the chosen and the excellent.
|38|48|
And mention Ishmael, Elisha and Dhulkifl; for everyone was among the excellent.
|38|49|
This is an admonition; and surely for the godfearing shall be a handsome resort __
|38|50|
gardens of eternity, the gates whereof will be opened to them;
|38|51|
reclining there they will call therein for abundant fruits and drink;
|38|52|
and with them will be maidens of equal age. who keep their glances restrained __
|38|53|
`This is what you were promised for the Day of Reckoning.
|38|54|
This is Our provision to which there will be no end'.
|38|55|
This for them. And for the insolent, there shall be an evil resort __
|38|56|
Hell, which they shall enter; how evil the cradle!
|38|57|
This, so let them taste it __ boiling water and pus;
|38|58|
and other things, many kinds of its type.
|38|59|
`This is a troop rushing in with you; there is no welcome for them; they shall enter the Fire.'
|38|60|
They will say, `no, it is you for whom there is no welcome; you forwarded it for us; and how evil is the resting place!'
|38|61|
They will say, `our Lord, whosoforwarded this for us, give him a double punishment in the Fire.'
|38|62|
And they will say, `how is it with us, that we do not see men whom we counted among the wicked.
|38|63|
Is it that we took them for a laughing stock, or have the eyes swerved away from them?'
|38|64|
That surely is the truth __ the wrangling of the inhabitants of the Fire.
|38|65|
Say, `I am only a warner, and there is no god but God, the One, the Omnipotent,
|38|66|
the Lord of the heavens and the earth and what between them is, the Mighty, the All-forgiving'.
|38|67|
Say, `it is a big news,
|38|68|
from which you are turning away.
|38|69|
I have no knowledge of the Most High Chiefs, when they dispute.
|38|70|
This only is revealed to me that I am only a clear warner'.
|38|71|
When thy Lord said to the angels, `I am creating a mortal of clay.
|38|72|
And when I have shaped him and breathed in him of My spirit, fall you down to him in prostration'.
|38|73|
So the angels prostrated themselves, all of them, altogether,
|38|74|
except Iblis; he showed arrogance, and was among the unbelievers.
|38|75|
God said, `O Ibis, what prevented thee from prostrating thyself before that I created with My hands? Did you show arrogance or art thou of the high ones?'
|38|76|
He said, `I am better than he; Thou createdst me of fire and createdst him of clay'.
|38|77|
God said, `now get thou out from here, for thou art accursed.
|38|78|
And upon thee shall rest My curse till the Day of Recompense'.
|38|79|
He said, `my Lord, respite me till the Day they shall be raised'.
|38|80|
God said, `thou art among the respited,
|38|81|
until the Day of the Known Time'.
|38|82|
He said, `by Thy glory, I shall pervert them all together,
|38|83|
except Thy exclusive servants out of them.'
|38|84|
God said, `the truth is, and the truth I speak,
|38|85|
I shall certainly fill Hell with thee and with those who among them follow thee, all together.'
|38|86|
Say, `I do not ask of you any wage for it, and I am no pretender.
|38|87|
It is not but a Reminder for all people.
|38|88|
And you shall surely know its news after a while.'
|39|1|
The sending down of the Book is from God, the Mighty, the Wise.
|39|2|
We have sent down to thee the Book with the truth, so serve God, making obedience sincerely His.
|39|3|
Behold, to God is due sincere obedience but those who take protectors apart from Him, (say) `We only serve them that they may bring us in nearness to God.' God shall judge between them concerning that wherein they differ; surely God does not guide any thankless liar.
|39|4|
Had God desired to take to Him a son,He would have chosen, out of what He creates, whatever He willed __ Holy is He. He is God, the One, the Omnipotent.
|39|5|
He created the heavens and the earth with the truth; He wraps the night about the day, and wraps the day about the night, and He has subjected the sun and the moon; everyone runs for a stated term. Behold, He is the Mighty, the All-forgiving.
|39|6|
He created you of one soul, then, from it, He made its mate, and He sent down for you eight kinds of cattle. He creates you in your mothers' wombs, creation after creation, in three sets of darkness. That is God your Lord, to whom belongs the kingdom. There is no god but He; how are you then turned about?
|39|7|
If you are ungrateful, God is All-sufficient, in no need of you, yet He is not pleased with ingratitude in His servants. And if you are grateful He likes it in you. And no laden soul bears the load of another. Then to your Lord shall you return, and He will tell you what you have been doing; He knows the thoughts in the breasts.
|39|8|
And when an affliction touches man, he calls on his Lord turning to Him; then when He confers on him a blessing from Him, he forgets that he was calling to before, and assigns compeers to God to lead astray from His way. Say, `enjoy life with thy unbelief a little; thou art surely of the inhabitants of the Fire.'
|39|9|
Or is he who shows obedience in the watches of the night, prostrating himself and standing, and is afraid of the Hereafter and hopes for the mercy of his Lord? Say, `are those who know and those who do not know equal?' Yet only men of understanding pay heed.
|39|10|
Say, `O My servants who believe, fear your Lord; for those who do good shall be good in this world; and God's earth is vast; the steadfast will surely be paid their wages in full without reckoning.'
|39|11|
Say, `I have been commanded to serve God, making obedience sincerely His;
|39|12|
and I have been commanded to be the first of those who surrender.'
|39|13|
Say, `I fear, if I should disobey my Lord, the punishment of a mighty day.'
|39|14|
Say, `it is God whom I serve, making obedience sincerely His;
|39|15|
and let you serve what you will, apart from Him.' Say, `surely the losers are they who give loss to themselves and their families on the Day of Resurrection. Behold, that is the manifest loss'.
|39|16|
For them shall be shadows of the Fire above them, and shadows underneath them; that it is wherewith God frightens His servants __ `O My servants, fear Me!'
|39|17|
And those who avoid serving the idols and turn to God, for them is a good news; so give thou good news to My servants,
|39|18|
those who listen to the Word, then follow the fairest of it. Those are the ones whom God has guided, and those are the men of understanding.
|39|19|
And he against whom the word of punishment has been realized, shalt thou deliver him who is in the Fire?
|39|20|
But those who fear their Lord, for them shall be lofty chambers, with lofty chambers built above them, rivers flowing underneath them; it is God's promise; God shall not fail the appointment.
|39|21|
Hast thou not seen that God has sent down from heaven water, and has threaded it as springs in the earth, then He brings forth therewith crops of diverse hues, then they wither, and thou seest them turning yellow, then He makes them broken straw? In that is surely an admonition for men of understanding.
|39|22|
Is then he whose breast God has expanded for Surrender (Islam), and he is under a light from his Lord? Woe then to those whose hearts are hardened against the remembrance of God; those are clearly astray.
|39|23|
God has sent down the fairest discourse, a Book with verses resembling and oft-repeated, at which the skins of those who fear their Lord shiver; then their skins and their hearts soften to the remembrance of God. That is God's guidance whereby He guides whom He will; but he whom God sends astray, no guide has he.
|39|24|
Is then he who guards himself with his face against the evil punishment on the Day of Resurrection __ and it is said to the wrong-doers, `taste what you have been earning'.
|39|25|
Those that were before them gave lies, then the punishment came upon them from whence they did not apprehend.
|39|26|
Then God let them taste humiliation in the present life, and the punishment of the Hereafter shall be greater, if they but knew.
|39|27|
And We have described for mankind, in this Qur'an (Reading), every type of similitude, that they may pay heed;
|39|28|
it is an Arabic Reading, not having any crookedness in it, that they may be godfearing.
|39|29|
God describes a similitude: a man in whom disagreeing partners share, and a man wholly belonging to one man; are the two equal in likeness? Praise be to God. No, but most of them have no knowledge.
|39|30|
Thou shalt die and they shall die;
|39|31|
then, on the Day of Resurrection, you shall dispute before your Lord.
|39|32|
Who then, does greater wrong than he who lied against God, and gave lies to the truth when it came to him? Is not in Hell the lodging of the unbelievers?
|39|33|
And he who brought the truth and confirmed it __ those are the godfearing.
|39|34|
They shall have with their Lord whatever they will; that is the recompense of the good-doers,
|39|35|
that God may acquit them of the worst of what they did, and recompense them with their wage for the best of what they have been doing.
|39|36|
Is not God sufficient for His Servant? And they frighten thee with those apart from Him; but he whom God sends astray, there is no guide for him;
|39|37|
and he whom God guides, there is none that shall send him astray; is not God Mighty, Vengeful?
|39|38|
And if thou askest them, `who created the heavens and the earth', they will surely say, `God'. Say, `have you then considered that those whom you call, apart from God __ if God desires any harm for me, shall they remove harm given by Him? Or if He desires to show mercy to me, shall they withhold His mercy?' Say, `God is enough for me; in Him trust those who trust'.
|39|39|
Say, `O my people, act in your place, I am acting too, and you will soon know
|39|40|
as to whom comes a punishment that will disgrace him, and upon whom alights a lasting punishment'.
|39|41|
We have sent down upon thee the Book for mankind with the truth; so whoso follows guidance, it is for himself, and whoso goes astray, he goes astray only against himself; and thou art no caretaker for them.
|39|42|
God closes the souls at the time of their death, and that which has not died, in its sleep; then He withholds that for which He has decreed death, and sends the other till a stated term; in that are surely signs for a people who ponder.
|39|43|
Or have they taken intercessors apart from God? Say, `even though they have no power on anything, and no understanding?'
|39|44|
Say, `God's is the intercession altogether; His is the kingdom of the heavens and the earth; then to Him you shall be returned'.
|39|45|
And when God is mentioned alone, the hearts of those who disbelieve in the Hereafter are seized with aversion; but when those apart from Him are mentioned, they rejoice.
|39|46|
Say, `O God, the Originator of the heavens and the earth, the Knower of the unseen and the visible, Thou alone shalt judge between thy servants in that they differ'.
|39|47|
And if the wrong-doers had all that is in the earth, and the like of it with it, they would offer it to ransom themselves from the evil punishment on the Day of Resurrection; but there would appear to them from God what they never thought of.
|39|48|
And there would appear to them the evils of what they earned, and that which they mocked at would overtake them. 
|39|49|
Now when harm touches man, he calls unto Us; then, when We confer on him a blessing from Us, he says `I have been given it only because of knowledge'. No, it was a trial, but most of them do not know.
|39|50|
Those before them have also said so, but what they had earned did not avail them.
|39|51|
And the evils of what they earned afflicted them; and those who do wrong from among these men, the evils of what they earn shall afflict them too, and they cannot frustrate it.
|39|52|
And do they not know that God outspreads and straitens the provision for whom He will? In that are surely Signs for a people who believe.
|39|53|
Say, `O My servants, who have been prodigal against themselves, do not despair of God's mercy; God forgives the sins altogether; surely He is the Forgiving, the Merciful.
|39|54|
And turn to your Lord and surrender to Him, before the punishment comes upon you, for then you will not be helped.
|39|55|
And follow the fairest of that which has been sent down to you from your Lord, before the punishment comes upon you suddenly, when you do not perceive;
|39|56|
lest a soul should say, `alas for me, in that I neglected duty to God, and I was surely among the scoffers';
|39|57|
or lest it should say, `if God had guided me, I would have been among the godfearing';
|39|58|
or lest it should say, when it sees the punishment, `if I had another turn, I would be among the good-doers'.
|39|59|
`No, My Signs did come to thee, but thou gavest lies to them and showdest arrogance, and wast among the unbelievers'.
|39|60|
And, on the Day of Resurrection, thou shalt see those, who lied against God, their faces blackened __ `Is not in Hell the lodging of the arrogant?'
|39|61|
And God shall save the godfearing with their achievement; evil shall not touch them, nor shall they grieve.
|39|62|
God is the Creator of everything, and He is Caretaker of everything.
|39|63|
With Him are the keys of the heavens and the earth; and those who disbelieve in the Signs of God, those shall be the losers.
|39|64|
Say, `is it other than God, then, that you bid me to serve, O you ignorant ones?'
|39|65|
And it has been revealed to thee, and also to those before thee, `if thou associatest (other gods with God) thy work shall surely fail and thou shalt be among the losers'.
|39|66|
No, but God do thou serve; and be among the thankful.
|39|67|
And they have not estimated God in His true estimation; and the earth, on the Day of Resurrection, shall be in His grip altogether, and the heavens shall be rolled up in His right hand; Holy be He, and High exalted, abovethat they associate.
|39|68|
And the Trumpet shall be blown and whosoever is in the heavens and whosoever is in the earth shall swoon, except whom God will. Then it shall be blown again, and lo, they shall stand beholding.
|39|69|
And the earth shall shine with the light of its Lord, and the Book shall be laid, and the Prophets and the Witnesses shall be brought in, and it shall be decided between them on truth, and they shall not be wronged.
|39|70|
And every soul shall be paid in full for what it did, for He very well knows what they do.
|39|71|
And the unbelievers shall be driven to Hell in companies; till when they have come there, its gates will be opened, and its Keepers will say to them, `did not Messengers from among yourselves come to you, reciting to you the signs of your Lord, and warning you of the meeting of this day of yours?' They will say, `yes, but the Word of punishment has ben realised against the unbelievers'.
|39|72|
It will be said, `enter the gates of Hell to dwell therein forever; how evil is the lodging of the arrogant|!
|39|73|
And those that feared their Lord shall be driven to Paradise in companies; until when they have come there, and its gates are opened, and its Keepers say to them, `Peace be upon you; you have fared well; enter to dwell therein forever'.
|39|74|
And they will say, `praise be to God who is true to His promise to us, and has bequeathed on us the earth, to make our dwelling in Paradise wherever we will; So how excellent is the wage of the workers.
|39|75|
And thou shalt see the angels going about the Throne, celebrating the praise of their Lord; and it will be decided between them on truth, and it will be said, `praise be to God, the Lord of the world.'
|40|1|
Ha Mim (H.M.).
|40|2|
The sending down of the Book is from God the Mighty, the Knowing,
|40|3|
the Forgiver of sins, the Accepter of repentance Terrible in retribution, the Bountiful; there is no god but He; unto Him is the destination.
|40|4|
None disputes concerning the signs of God except the unbelievers, but let not their going to and fro in the land delude thee.
|40|5|
Before them, the people of Noah, and many factions after them, gave lies; and every community purposed to seize their Messenger, and they disputed by means of falsehood to rebut the truth thereby, then I seized them __ so how was My retribution!
|40|6|
And thus the Word of thy Lord was realized against the unbelievers that they are the people of the Fire.
|40|7|
Those who bear the throne and those round about it, celebrate the praise of their Lord and believe in Him, and they ask forgiveness for the Believers: `our Lord, Thou embracest everything in mercy and knowledge, so forgive those who repented and followed Thy way, and save them from the punishment of Hell.
|40|8|
And our Lord, admit them to the gardens of eternity that thou hast promised them, and also those of their fathers, their wives and their offspring who acted right; surely Thou art the Mighty, the Wise;
|40|9|
and save them from evils; and whomsoever Thou savest from evils on that day, Thou hast had mercy on him; and that is the mighty triumph.'
|40|10|
To the unbelievers it shall be pronounced, `God's abhorrence was greater than your own abhorrence of yourselves, when you were called to belief and you disbelieved'.
|40|11|
They shall say, `Our Lord, Thou hast made us to die twice, and thou hast made us to live twice; now we confess our sins; is there any way to go forth?' __ 
|40|12|
`This is because when God alone was called upon, you disbelieved, but if He was associated with others, you believed; now Judgement belongs to God, the High, the great.'
|40|13|
It is He who shows you His Signs, and sends down from heaven provision for you; yet none pays heed except him who turns to Him.
|40|14|
So call to God, making obedience sincerely His, though the unbelievers be averse.
|40|15|
Exalter of ranks, Lord of the Throne, He casts the Spirit of His Command upon whomsoever of His servants He will, that he may warn (people) of the Day of Meeting,
|40|16|
the day they will come forth; nothing of theirs shall be hidden from God. `Whose is the kingdom today?' __ ``God's, the One, the Omnipotent.
|40|17|
Today, every soul shall be recompensed for what it earned; no wrong today; surely God is swift at the reckoning'.
|40|18|
And warn them of the Approaching Day, when the hearts, choking with anguish, shall be at the throats; and there will be no bosom friend for the wrong-doers, nor any intercessor to be obeyed.
|40|19|
He knows the treachery of the eyes and what the breasts conceal.
|40|20|
And God shall decide on truth; and those they call upon, apart from Him, shall not decide anything; surely God is the Hearing, the Seeing.
|40|21|
And have they not journeyed in the land and seen how was the end of those before them? They were stronger than themselves, in might and in leaving traces in the earth, yet God seized them for their sins; and they had none to save them from God.
|40|22|
That was because their Messengers came to them with the clear signs, but they disbelieved, so God seized them; surely He is Strong and Terrible in Retribution.
|40|23|
And We sent Moses with Our signs and a clear authority
|40|24|
to Pharaoh, Haman and Korah, but they said, `a sorcerer, a big liar'.
|40|25|
And when he came to them with the truth from Us, they said, `kill the sons of those who have believed along with him, and let their women live'. But the guile of the unbelievers always goes astray.
|40|26|
And Pharaoh said, `leave me to kill Moses, and let him call to his Lord; I fear that he may not change your religion, or he may not cause disorder to prevail in the land'.
|40|27|
And Moses said, `I take refuge in my Lord and your Lord from every arrogant man, who does not believe in the Day of Reckoning'.
|40|28|
And a man, a Believer from Pharaoh's folk, who was hiding his belief, said, `will you kill a man because he says, `my Lord is God', and he has brought you the Clear Signs from your Lord? And if he is a liar, his lie shall go against him; and if he is truthful, then some of what he threatens you with, shall befall you; God does not guide him who is extravagant and a liar.
|40|29|
O my people, today yours is the kingdom, you being dominant in the land, but who will help us against the might of God, if it comes upon us?' Pharaoh said, `I show you only what I see, and I guide you only to the way of rectitude'.
|40|30|
And he who believed said, `O my people, I fear for you the like of the day of the factions,
|40|31|
the like of the case of Noah's people, Ad, Thamood, and those after them; and God does not desire wrong for His servants.
|40|32|
O my people, I fear for you the Day of Calling-out,
|40|33|
the day when you will turn back, retreating, there being no defender for you against God; and whomso God send astray, there is no guide for him.
|40|34|
And, of course, Joseph brought you the Clear Signs before, but you did not cease doubting what he brought you; until when he died, you said, `God shall not raise any Messenger after him.' Thus does God sends astray him who is extravagant and a doubter,
|40|35|
those who dispute concerning the Signs of God without any authority having come to them; very hateful is this in the sight of God and in the sight of the Believers; thus God sets a seal on the heart of every arrogant tyrant'.
|40|36|
And Pharaoh said, `O Haman, build for me a tower that I may reach the cords,
|40|37|
the cords of the heavens, and look upon Moses' God, for I think him a liar'. And thus the evil of his deed was adorned for Pharaoh, and he was barred from the way; but Pharaoh's guile was only to perish.
|40|38|
And he who believed said, `O my people, follow me, and I shall guide you to the way of rectitude.
|40|39|
O my people, this present life is only an enjoyment, and surely the Hereafter is the House of stability.
|40|40|
Whoso does an evil deed, he is not recompensed but with the like of it; and whoso, male or female, does a righteous deed, and he is a believer, those shall enter Paradise, wherein they shall be provided without reckoning.
|40|41|
And O my people, how is it with me, that I call you to salvation, and you call me to the Fire?
|40|42|
You call me to disbelieve in God, and to associate with Him that of which I have no knowledge, while I call you to the Mighty, the All-forgiving.
|40|43|
No doubt that what you call me to has no title to be called, in this world or in the Hereafter, and that our return is to God, and that the extravagant are the people of the Fire.
|40|44|
You will remember what I say to you, and I confide my affair to God; surely God sees His servants'.
|40|45|
Then God saved him from the evils of their devising, and there fell on Pharaoh's folk the evil punishment _
|40|46|
the Fire, to which they are presented morning and evening; and on the day the Hour comes: __ `Admit Pharaoh's folk into the most terrible punishment'.
|40|47|
And when they will dispute with one another in the Fire, the weak will say to those who showed arrogance, `we were your followers; will you now avail us against a part of the Fire?'
|40|48|
Those who showed arrogance will say, `we are all in it; God has passed judgement between (His) servants'.
|40|49|
And those in the Fire will say to the Keepers of Hell, `call on your Lord to lessen for us a day of the punishment.'
|40|50|
They will say, `but did not your Messengers bring you the Clear Signs?' They will say, `yes indeed'. They will say, `then call on; but the call of the unbelievers only goes astray'.
|40|51|
We shall surely help Our Messengers and the Believers in the present life, and on the day when the witnesses stand forth,
|40|52|
the day when their excuse shall not profit the wrong-doers, and they shall be cursed and shall have the evil home.
|40|53|
And We gave Moses the Guidance, and We made the Children of Israel heirs to the Book,
|40|54|
for a guidance and an admonition for men of understanding.
|40|55|
So be thou patient, surely God's promise is true; and ask forgiveness for thy mistake, and celebrate the praise of thy Lord at evening and dawn.
|40|56|
As for those who dispute concerning the Signs of God without any authority come to them, in their breasts is only feeling of greatness which they shall never attain; so seek thou refuge in God; surely He is the Hearing, the Seeing.
|40|57|
The creation of the heavens and the earth is greater (a feat) than the creation of mankind, but most men do not know.
|40|58|
And the blind and the seeing man are not equal, nor are the believers, who do righteous deeds, and the evil-doers; yet little heed you pay.
|40|59|
The Hour is surely coming, no doubt in it, though most men do not believe.
|40|60|
And your Lord says, `call upon Me, I will answer you; surely those who show arrogance against serving Me shall enter Hell in all lowliness'.
|40|61|
God is He who made for you the night that you may have rest in it, and the day to see; surely God is bountiful to mankind, though most men are not thankful.
|40|62|
That is God, your Lord, the Creator of everything; there is no god but He; how then are you perverted?
|40|63|
Thus are perverted those who deny the Signs of God.
|40|64|
God is He who made the earth a resting place for you and the heaven for an edifice, and He shaped you and made your shapes handsome, and provided you with good things. That is God, your Lord: so blessed be God, the Lord of the world.
|40|65|
He is the Living, there is no god but He, so call upon Him, making obedience sincerely His; praise be to God, the Lord of the world.
|40|66|
Say, `I am forbidden to serve those you call on, apart from God, since the clear Signs from my Lord have come to me; and I am commanded to surrender to the Lord of the world.
|40|67|
It is He who created you of dust, then of a sperm-drop, then of a blood-clot, then He brings you forth as a child, that you may then attain your full strength, then that you may become old men __ though some of you die before __ and that you may reach a stated term, haply you will understand.
|40|68|
It is He who gives life and makes to die; and when He decrees a thing, He only says to it, `Be', and it is.
|40|69|
Hast thou not seen those who dispute concerning the signs of God; how are they turned about?
|40|70|
Those who give lies to the Book and to that wherewith We sent Our Messengers; but they will soon know; __ 
|40|71|
when the fetters and chains will be about their necks; they will be dragged
|40|72|
into the boiling water, and then, in the Fire they will be poured;
|40|73|
then it will be said to them, `where are those you took as associate-gods,
|40|74|
apart from God?' They will say, `they are lost to us; no, but we never called on anything before'.
|40|75|
Thus does God send astray theunbelievers. `That is because you rejoiced in the earth without right, and because you were exultant.
|40|76|
Enter the gates of Hell to dwell therein forever; and how evil is the resort of the arrogant!'
|40|77|
So, be thou patient; surely God's promise is true; whether We show thee a part of that We promise them, or We call thee to Us, to Us they shall be returned.
|40|78|
And We sent Messengers before thee, some of them We have related to thee, and some of them We have not related to thee. And it was not for a Messenger to bring a Sign, except by God's leave; and when God's command comes, it is decided on truth, and there the vain-doers are the losers.
|40|79|
God is He who made for you the cattle, so that you ride some of them and eat some;
|40|80|
and you have in them other uses, and through them you attain a need that is in your breasts, and upon them and upon the ships you are carried.
|40|81|
And He shows you His Signs; then which of God's Signs will you deny?
|40|82|
Have they not journeyed in the land and seen how was the end of those before them? They were more numerous and stronger in might and in leaving traces in the earth than these people, but what they earned did not avail them.
|40|83|
So when their Messengers came to them with the Clear Signs, they rejoiced in what knowledge they had, and what they mocked at encompassed upon them.
|40|84|
Then, when they saw Our might, they said, `we believe in God alone, and we disbelieve in that we were associating with Him.'
|40|85|
But their belief, when they saw Our might, could not profit them; it is God's tradition that has passed before among His servants; and there the unbelievers were losers.
|41|1|
Ha Mim (H.M.);
|41|2|
a sending down from the Merciful,
|41|3|
the All merciful; a Book, whose signs are well-explained, as an Arabic Reading for a people who have knowledge,
|41|4|
a bearer of good news and a warner; yet most of them have turned aside, and do not give ear.
|41|5|
And they say, `our hearts are under coverings against that thou callest us to, and in our ears is heaviness, and between us and thee is a veil; so act, we are also acting!'
|41|6|
Say, `I am only a mortal like you, and to me is revealed that your god is only One God; so remain firm by Him, and ask for His forgiveness. And woe to the idolaters,
|41|7|
who do not pay the Due _ alms, and who disbelieve in the Hereafter'.
|41|8|
Surely those who believe and do righteous deeds shall have an unfailing wage.
|41|9|
Say, `do you disbelieve in Him who created the earth in two days, and do you set up compeers to Him? That is the Lord of the world.
|41|10|
And He set therein firm mountains over it, and placed blessings in it, and determined in it its sustenance in four days; equal to all those who ask.
|41|11|
Then He turned to the heaven, and it was smoke, and He said to it and to the earth, `come willingly or unwillingly!'
|41|12|
They said, `we come willingly'. So He determined them as seven heavens in two days, and inspired in every heaven its mandate;' and We adorned the nearer heaven with lamps, and for a guard; that is the ordaining of the Mighty, the Knowing.
|41|13|
Now if they turn away, then say, `I have warned you of a thunderbolt, like the thunderbolt of Ad and Thamood.'
|41|14|
When the Messengers came to them from before them and from behind them, saying `Serve not but God', they said, `if our Lord had willed, He would have sent down angels, so we disbelieve in that you have been sent with'.
|41|15|
Then, as for Ad, they showed arrogance in the land without right, and said, `who is stronger than we in power?' What; did they not see that God who created them was stronger than they in power; but they denied Our signs.
|41|16|
So We loosed upon them a clamorous wind in days of ill fortune, that We let them taste the punishment of humiliation in the present life; and the punishment of the Hereafter shall be more humiliating, and they shall not find any help.
|41|17|
And as for Thamood, We guided them, but they preferred blindness to guidance; so the thunderbolt of the punishment of humiliation seized them for that they have been earning.
|41|18|
And We saved those who believed and were godfearing.
|41|19|
And on the day, when the enemies of God are mustered to the Fire, and they are duly disposed.
|41|20|
Till, when they come to it, their ears, their eyes and their skins shall bear witness against them, concerning what they have been doing.
|41|21|
And they will say to their skins, `why did you bear witness against us?' They will say, `God has given us speech, as He has given speech to everything; and it is He who created you the first time, and to Him you have been returned.
|41|22|
And you did not cover yourselves that your ears, your eyes and your skins should not bear witness against you, but you thought that God did not know much of what you were doing.
|41|23|
And that thought of yours, that you had about your Lord, ruined you, and so you have become of the losers?'
|41|24|
Now if they endure, the Fire shall be their resort; and if they ask for favour, they are not of those whom favour is shown.
|41|25|
And We had assigned to them comrades who adorned for them what was before them and what was behind them, so the Word against them has been realized as it was for the communities of men and the jinn that passed away before them; surely they were the losers.
|41|26|
And the unbelievers say, `do not listen to this Reading (Qur'an), but talk non-sense during it, that you may win'.
|41|27|
So We shall make the unbelievers taste terrible punishment, and shall recompense them for the worst that they were doing.
|41|28|
That is the recompense of God's enemies __ the Fire; for them therein will be the eternal home; a recompense for that they denied Our Signs.
|41|29|
And the unbelievers shall say, `our Lord, show us the jinn and the men that led us astray, and we shall trample them under our feet that they may be among the lowest'.
|41|30|
Those who say, `our Lord is God', then they stand firm on it, the angels descend on them, (saying), `do not fear, nor grieve, and have good news of Paradise that has been promised to you.
|41|31|
We are your friends in the present life and in the Hereafter; and for you therein shall be whatever your souls desire, and for you therein shall be whatever you call for __
|41|32|
a hospitality from One Forgiving, Merciful.'
|41|33|
And who speaks fairer than he who calls to God and does righteousness, and says,' I am of those that surrender?'
|41|34|
And the good and the evil are not equal; repel with that which is the fairest, and the one between whom and thee is enmity shall be as if he were a bosom friend.
|41|35|
But none is given it except those who are patient, and none is given it except one having big fortune.
|41|36|
And if a provocation from the Devil provokes thee, seek refuge in God; He is the Hearing, the Knowing.
|41|37|
And of His Signs are the night and the day, and the sun and the moon; do not prostrate yourselves to the sun or to the moon, but prostrate yourselves to God who created them, if Him you serve.
|41|38|
And if they show arrogance, then those who are with thy Lord extol Him day and night, and do not grow weary.
|41|39|
And of His Signs is that thou seest the earth humble; then when We send down water upon it, it quivers and swells; surely He who quickens it shall quicken the dead; He is powerful over everything.
|41|40|
Those who blaspheme Our signs are not hidden from Us. Is then he who shall be cast into the Fire better or he who shall come secure on the Day of Resurrection? Do what you will, He sees what you do.
|41|41|
Those who disbelieve in the Remembrance, when it has come to them __ and it is surely a Mighty Book,
|41|42|
to which falsehood does not come from before it nor from behind it; it is a sending down from One Wise, Praiseworthy.
|41|43|
Nothing is being said to thee, except what has been said to the Messengers before thee; surely thy Lord is the One who forgives and who gives painful retribution.
|41|44|
And had We made it a Reading (Qur'an) in a foreign language, they would have surely said, `why are not its signs explained? What! a foreign language and an Arab?' Say, `it is a guidance and a healing to the Believers; but those who do not believe, in their ears is heaviness, and to them it is a blindness; those are called from a distant place.
|41|45|
And We gave Moses the Book, but differences were created in it; and if a Word from thy Lord had not gone forth, it would have been decided between them; and they are surely in a disquieting doubt about it.
|41|46|
Whoso does righteousness, it is for himself, and whoso does evil, it is against him; and thy Lord is no tyrant to (His) servants.
|41|47|
To Him is referred the knowledge of the Hour. And no fruit comes forth from its sheaths, and no female bears or delivers, but it is in His knowledge. And on the day when He shall call to them, `where are My associates,' they shall say, `we declare to Thee, there is no witness among us.'
|41|48|
And those whom they called upon before shall be lost to them, and they will think they have no place of escape. 
|41|49|
Man is not tired of praying for good, and if evil touches him, he is despaired, desperate.
|41|50|
And if We let him taste mercy from Us after hardship has touched him, he will surely say, `this is for me and I do not think the Hour will be coming, and even if I am returned to my Lord, I will surely have the best reward with Him.' But We will surely tell the unbelievers what they did, and We will let them taste a harsh punishment.
|41|51|
And when We bless man, he turns away and withdraws aside; and when evil touches him, lo, he is full of long prayers.
|41|52|
Say, `have you considered, if it is from God, then you disbelieve in it, who is more astray than he who is in far opposition?'
|41|53|
We shall show them Our Signs in the horizons and in themselves, till it is clear to them that it is the truth; but does it not suffice regarding thy Lord, that He is witness over everything?
|41|54|
Behold, they are in doubt regarding the meeting with their Lord. Behold, He encompasses everything.
|42|1|
Ha Mim; (H.M.)
|42|2|
Ain Sin Qaf (A.S.Q.)
|42|3|
So reveals to thee, and to those before thee,
|42|4|
God, the Mighty, the Wise. To Him belongs whatsoever is in the heavens and whatsoever is in the earth, and He is the High, the Mighty.
|42|5|
The heavens would almost be rent above them, but the angels celebrate the praise of their Lord, and ask forgiveness for those on earth. Behold! God __ He is the Forgiving, the Merciful.
|42|6|
And those who have taken to them protectors apart from Him, God is guard over them, and thou art no caretaker for them.
|42|7|
And so We have revealed to thee an Arabic Reading (Qur'an), that thou mayest warn the Mother-City and those (living) about it, and thou mayest warn of the Day of Gathering, wherein is no doubt; a party will be in Paradise and a party in the Blaze.
|42|8|
And if God had willed, He would have made them one community, but He admits to His mercy whom He will; and the wrongdoers, they have no protector, nor a helper.
|42|9|
Or have they taken protectors apart from Him? But God __ He is the Protector, and He quickens the dead, and He is powerful over every-thing.
|42|10|
And in whatever you differ, its judgement belongs to God. That is God, my Lord, in whom I put my trust, and to whom I turn.
|42|11|
The Originator of the heavens and the earth, He has made for you out of yourselves pairs, and out of the cattle pairs, whereby He multiples you. Nothing is like Him, and He is the Hearing, the Seeing.
|42|12|
To Him belong the keys of the heavens and the earth; He outspreads and straitens the provision for whom He will; surely He knows every-thing.
|42|13|
He has laid down for you of the religion, as He charged Noah with, and that We have revealed to thee, and that We charged Abraham, Moses and Jesus with: `Establish the Religion and be not divided in it'. Hard upon the idolaters is to which thou callest them; God chooses to Himself whom He will, and He guides to Himself who turns to him.
|42|14|
And they divided not but after the knowledge had come to them, being insolent to one another; and if a Word had not gone forth from thy Lord until a stated term, it would have been decided between them; those who were made to inherit the Book after them are surely in a disquieting doubt about it.
|42|15|
So, to this thou call, and stand firm, as thou art commanded; and do not follow their caprices; and say, `I believe in what God has sent down of the Book, and I have been commanded to do justice between you; God is our Lord and your Lord; for us are our deeds and for you are your deeds; there is no argument between us and you; God will bring us together; and to Him is the destination.'
|42|16|
And those who argue concerning God after His call has been answered, their argument is null and void in the sight of their Lord, and they are under wrath, and for them shall be a terrible punishment.
|42|17|
God is He who has sent down the Book and the Balance, with the truth; and what shall make thee know if the Hour is nearby!
|42|18|
Those who do not believe in it, seek to hasten it, but those who believe are fearful of it, for they know that it is the truth. Behold, those who doubt the Hour, they are astray far away.
|42|19|
God is courteous to His servants, provides to whom He will; and He is the Strong, the Mighty.
|42|20|
Whoso desires the tillage of the Hereafter, We shall give him increase in his tillage, and whoso desires the tillage of this world, We shall give him some of it, but he will have no share in the Hereafter.
|42|21|
Or do they have associate-gods who have laid down for them some religion which God has not permitted? But for the Word of Decision, it would have been decided between them; and for the wrong-doers, there shall be a painful punishment.
|42|22|
Thou shalt see the wrong-doers fearful because of what they have earned, but it shall fall on them. And those who believe and do righteous deeds shall be in meadows of the gardens; they shall have, whatever they will, with their Lord; that is the great bounty.
|42|23|
That indeed is the good news that God gives to His servants, who believe and do righteous deeds. Say, `I do not ask of you a wage for this, except love of the kinship'. And Whoso earns a good deed We shall give them increase in goodness; surely God is Forgiving, Thankful.
|42|24|
Or do they say, `he has forged a lie against God'? But if God will, He may set a seal on thy heart; and God blots out the falsehood, and verifies the truth by His Words; surely He knows the thoughts in the breasts.
|42|25|
And it is He who accepts repentance from His servants, and pardons the evils; and He knows what you do;
|42|26|
and He answers those who believe and do righteous deeds, and gives them increase of His bounty; and the unbelievers, for them shall be a terrible punishment.
|42|27|
And if God had expanded the provision for His servants, they would have rebelled in the earth; but He sends down in measure what He will; He is aware of and sees His servants.
|42|28|
And it is He who sends down the rain, after they have despaired, and spreads out His mercy; and He is the Protector, the Praiseworthy.
|42|29|
And of His Signs is the creation of the heavens and the earth, and such creatures that He has scattered abroad in them; and He is powerful to gather them when He will.
|42|30|
And whatever affliction befalls you, it is due to what your hands have earned, and He pardons much.
|42|31|
And you cannot frustrate (Him) in the earth; and you have, apart from God, no protector or helper.
|42|32|
And of His Signs are the ships like banners on the sea.
|42|33|
If He will, He would still the wind and they would be motionless on its back; in that are surely Signs for every steadfast, thankful man;
|42|34|
or He would wreck them for what they have earned, but He pardons much;
|42|35|
and He knows those who dispute regarding Our signs; they have no place of escape.
|42|36|
So whatever thing you are given is the comfort of the present life, but what is with God is better and more lasting for those who believe and put their trust in their Lord;
|42|37|
and those who avoid major sins and indecencies, and when they are angry, forgive;
|42|38|
and those who answer their Lord, and establish the Prayer; and their affair is by counsel between them;
|42|39|
and they expend of that We have provided them; and those who, when aggression is made against them, avenge themselves.
|42|40|
And the recompense of an evil is a like evil, yet whoso pardons and makes amends, his wage is upon God; surely He does not love the wrong-doers.
|42|41|
And whoso avenges himself after he has been wronged, those__ there is no way open against them.
|42|42|
The way is open only against those who do wrong to the people, and transgress in the earth without right; those, for them shall be a painful punishment.
|42|43|
And whoso shows patience and forgives, that is surely an act of resolution in the affairs.
|42|44|
And whomso God sends astray he has no protector after Him; and thou shalt see the wrong-doers, when they see the punishment, saying, `is there any way to return?'
|42|45|
And thou shalt see them brought before it, humbled due to abasement, looking with a stealthy glance. And the Believers shall say, `the losers are those who gave loss to themselves and their families on the Day of Resurrection.' Behold, the wrong-doers are in a lasting punishment.
|42|46|
And they have no protectors, apart from God, to help them; and whomso God sends astray, no way has he.
|42|47|
Answer your Lord, before therecomes from God a day that shall not be turned back; there shall be, on that day, no shelter for you, and no denial by you.
|42|48|
But if they turn away, then We have not sent thee as a guard over them; thine is only to deliver the Message. And when We let man taste mercy from Us, he rejoices in it; and if some evil befalls them because of what their hands have forwarded, then surely man is unthankful.
|42|49|
To God belongs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth; He creates what He will; He gives to whom He will females, and He gives to whom He will males;
|42|50|
or He couples them both males and females; and He makes whom He will barren; He is Knowing, Powerful.
|42|51|
And it is not for a mortal that God should speak to him, except by revelation, or from behind a veil, or should send a messenger, and he reveals by His leave, what He will; surely He is High, Wise.
|42|52|
And like that, We have revealed to thee a Spirit of Our Command. Thou knewest not what the Book was, nor the Belief; but We have made it a light whereby We guide whom We will of Our servants; and surely thou guidest to a straight path,
|42|53|
the path of God, to whom belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is in the earth. Behold, to God are destined all affairs.
|43|1|
Ha Mim (H.M.).
|43|2|
By the clear Book,
|43|3|
We have made it an Arabic Reading (Qur'an) that you may understand;
|43|4|
and it is in the Mother-Book with Us, exalted
|43|5|
indeed and wise. But shall We take away the Remembrance from you, because you are an extravagant people?
|43|6|
And how many a Prophet did We send among the ancients!
|43|7|
And no Prophet came to them, but that they mocked at him.
|43|8|
Then We destroyed the strongest in valour among them, and the example of the ancients has already passed.
|43|9|
And if thou askest them, `who created the heavens and the earth,' `they will surely say, `the Mighty, the Knowing created them';
|43|10|
He who made the earth a cradle for you, and made in it paths for you, that you may find the way;
|43|11|
and who sent down from heaven water in measure; then We revived thereby a dead land; thus shall you be brought forth.
|43|12|
And who created all kinds of things, and made for you such ships and cattle on which you ride,
|43|13|
that you may be seated on their backs, then, when you are seated on them, remember your Lord's blessing, and say, `Holy be He, who has subjected this to us, for we were not equal to it;
|43|14|
and surely we should be returning to our Lord.'
|43|15|
Yet they have made some of His servants a part of Him; surely man in clearly unthankful.
|43|16|
Or has He taken, from what He has created, daughters for Himself, and chosen for you sons?
|43|17|
But when any of them is given the good news of what he has likened to the All-merciful, his face gets darkened, and he is choked.
|43|18|
What! one who is brought up amid ornaments, and who in altercation is not clear?
|43|19|
And they have made the angels, who are the servants of the All-merciful, females. Did they witness their creation? Their witness shall be written down, and they shall be questioned.
|43|20|
And they say, `had the All-merciful willed, we would not have served them.' They have no knowledge of that; they only conjecture.
|43|21|
Or did We give them a Book before this, and they are holding fast to it?
|43|22|
No, but they say, `we found our fathers on a system, and we are guided on their foot-prints.'
|43|23|
And similarly, We did not send before thee any warner to a city but its affluent men said, `we found our fathers on a system, and we are following on their foot-prints.'
|43|24|
He said, `even if I should bring you a better guidance than you found your fathers on?' They said, `we disbelieve in what you have been sent with.'
|43|25|
Then We took vengeance upon them, and see how was the end of those who cried lies.
|43|26|
And when Abraham said to his father and his people, `I am quit of that you serve,
|43|27|
except Him who originated me, and He will guide me.'
|43|28|
And he made it a word to last in his posterity, that they might return.
|43|29|
No, but I gave these and their fathers comforts, until there came to them the truth and a manifest Messenger.
|43|30|
But when the truth came to them, they said, `this is sorcery, and we disbelieve in it.'
|43|31|
And they said, `why have this Qur'an not been sent down on some great man of the two cities!'
|43|32|
Is it they who divide the mercy of thy Lord? It is We who have divided between them their livelihood in the present life, and have raised some of them above others in rank, so that some of them may take others in service; and the mercy of thy Lord is better than what they amass.
|43|33|
And were it not that mankind would become one community, We would have made for those who disbelieve in the All-merciful, the roofs of their houses, and the stairs whereon they mount,
|43|34|
and doors of their houses and the couches whereon they recline,
|43|35|
of silver and ornamental; and but all that is only the comfort of the present life; and the Hereafter with thy Lord is for the godfearing.
|43|36|
And he who blinds himself to the Remembrance of the All-merciful, We assign to him a devil and he becomes his comrade.
|43|37|
And they bar them from the way, yet they think that they are guided.
|43|38|
Until, when he comes to Us, he will say (to the comrade), `would that there had been between me and thee the distance of the two Easts!' How evil is the comrade!
|43|39|
`But since you committed wrong, it shall not profit you today; you are partners in the punishment.'
|43|40|
Wilt thou then make the deaf to hear, or guide the blind and him who is clearly astray?
|43|41|
Whether We take thee away, We shall take vengeance upon them;
|43|42|
or We shall show thee what We have promised them, for We have power over them.
|43|43|
So hold thou fast to that revealed to thee; surely thou art on a straight path.
|43|44|
And it is surely a Reminder to thee and to thy people; and you shall soon be questioned.
|43|45|
And ask those of Our Messengers that We sent before thee, `have We appointed, apart from the All-merciful, any gods to be served?'
|43|46|
And We sent Moses with Our Signs to Pharaoh and his chiefs and he said, `I am a Messenger of the Lord of the world.'
|43|47|
Then, when he brought them Our Signs, they laughed at them.
|43|48|
And whatever Sign We showed them it was greater than its sister Sign; and We seized them with punishment, that they might return.
|43|49|
But they said, `O sorcerer, pray to thy Lord for us by the covenant He has made with thee, and we shall surely follow guidance.'
|43|50|
But when We removed from them the punishment, they broke the pledge.
|43|51|
And Pharaoh announced to his people, `my people, is not the kingdom of Egypt and these rivers flowing beneath me, mine? Do you not see?
|43|52|
Or am I not better than this one, who is contemptible and can hardly express clearly?
|43|53|
And why have the bracelets of gold not been given to him, or angels come with him conjoined?'
|43|54|
Thus he made his people unsteady, and they obeyed him; surely they were a people of trangressors.
|43|55|
So, when they displeased Us, We took vengeance on them, and drowned them all together;
|43|56|
and We made them a thing of the past, and an example for the later people.
|43|57|
And when the son of Mary is mentioned as an example, thy people cry out against him.
|43|58|
And they say, `are our gods better or he?' They cite him to thee only for a dispute; no, they are a quarrelsome people.
|43|59|
He was only a servant whom We blessed and made him an example for the Children of Israel.
|43|60|
And if We will, We would surely make some of you as angels to be successors in the earth.
|43|61|
But indeed it is a knowledge of the Hour, so do not have doubt concerning it, and follow me; this is a straight path.
|43|62|
And let not the Devil bar you; he is a clear enemy to you.
|43|63|
And when Jesus came with the clear Signs, he said, `I have brought you Wisdom, and that I may make clear to you some of that in which you differ; so fear God and obey me.
|43|64|
Surely God, He is my Lord and your Lord, so serve Him; this is a straight path.'
|43|65|
But the factions among them differed; so woe to the wrongdoers because of punishment of a painful day.
|43|66|
Are they looking only for the Hour, that it should come upon them suddenly, when they do not perceive?
|43|67|
The friends on that day shall be enemies to one another, except the godfearing.
|43|68|
`O My servants, today there is no fear on you nor will you grieve __
|43|69|
you who believed in Our signs and surrendered __
|43|70|
Enter Paradise you and your wives, joyfully.'
|43|71|
There shall be passed around them plates and cups made of gold and therein shall be all that the souls desire and the eyes delight. `And you shall dwell therein forever;
|43|72|
and this is the Paradise that you have been given in inheritance for that you were doing.
|43|73|
Here you have fruits in plenty whereof you will eat.'
|43|74|
As for the sinners, they shall dwell in the punishment of Hell forever;
|43|75|
it shall not be relaxed for them, and they shall despair there.
|43|76|
And We wronged them not, instead they themselves were the wrongdoers.
|43|77|
And they shall call, `O malik (master), let thy Lord make an end of us'; he shall say, `you shall be staying.'
|43|78|
We have brought you the truth but most of you are averse to the truth.
|43|79|
Or have they settled some affair? Then we are also settling?
|43|80|
Or do they think that We do not hear their secret and their conspiracy? No, Our messengers with them are writing it down.
|43|81|
Say, `if the All-merciful had a son, I would be the first to serve.
|43|82|
Holy be the Lord of the heavens and the earth, the Lord of the Throne, above that they describe.
|43|83|
So leave them to chat and play, till they meet their day which they are promised.
|43|84|
And it is He who is God in the heaven and God in the earth; and He is the Wise, the Knowing.
|43|85|
And blessed be He, to whom belongs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth and what is between them; and with Him is the knowledge of the Hour, and to Him you shall be returned.
|43|86|
And those whom they call upon, apart from Him, have no power of intercession, except him who testifies to the truth and that knowingly.
|43|87|
And if thou askest them as to who created them, they will surely say, `God'; then how are they perverted!
|43|88|
And his saying is, `my Lord, these are a people who will not believe'. __
|43|89|
But overlook them, and say, `peace'; they will soon know.
|44|1|
Ha Mim (H.M.);
|44|2|
By the Manifest Book,
|44|3|
We have sent it down in a blessed night __ we were surely warning.
|44|4|
Therein are determined all matters of wisdom,
|44|5|
as a bidding from Us __ We were surely sending it,
|44|6|
as a mercy from thy Lord; He is the Hearing, the Knowing,
|44|7|
the Lord of the heavens and the earth and what between them is __ if you would have faith.
|44|8|
There is no god but He; He gives life and death; your Lord and the Lord of your ancient fathers.
|44|9|
No, but they are playing in doubt.
|44|10|
So watch for the day when the heaven shall bring a manifest smoke,
|44|11|
covering the people; __ this is a painful punishment.
|44|12|
`Our Lord, remove the punishment from us, we are Believers.'
|44|13|
How can they have the admonition when a clear Messenger has come to them,
|44|14|
yet they have turned away from him, and said, `a man tutored, possessed.'
|44|15|
`We are removing the punishment a little, but you will revert.'
|44|16|
On the day when We shall assault most violently, We shall be taking the vengeance.
|44|17|
And We tried the people of Pharaoh before them, and a noble Messenger came to them __
|44|18|
`Deliver to me the servants of God, I am to you a trusted Messenger;
|44|19|
and do not rise against God, I have come to you with a clear authority;
|44|20|
and I take refuge in my Lord and your Lord, lest you should stone me;
|44|21|
and if you do not believe me, go apart from me.
|44|22|
' Then he called to his Lord, `these are a sinful people!' __
|44|23|
`Set thou forth with My servants by night, you shall be followed;
|44|24|
and leave the sea becalmed; they are a host to be drowned.'
|44|25|
How many gardens and fountains they left,
|44|26|
and sown fields and a noble
|44|27|
station, and comforts in which they rejoiced!
|44|28|
Thus it was; and We made another people to inherit them.
|44|29|
And the heaven and the earth did not weep for them, nor were they respited.
|44|30|
And We delivered the Children of Israel from the humiliating punishment,
|44|31|
from Pharaoh; he was a high one, among the extravagant.
|44|32|
And We chose them above all people on knowledge,
|44|33|
and We gave them Signs wherein was a clear trial.
|44|34|
Now these people indeed say,
|44|35|
`it is only our first death, and we shall not be raised.
|44|36|
Bring us our fathers, if you are truthful.'
|44|37|
Are they better or the people of Tubba and those before them? We destroyed them; they were surely sinners.
|44|38|
And We have not created the heavens and the earth and what is between them in play.
|44|39|
We have not created them but with truth, but most of them do not know.
|44|40|
Surely the Day of Decision is their appointed time, all together,
|44|41|
the day when a friend shall not avail a friend in the least, nor shall they be helped,
|44|42|
except him on whom God has mercy; surely He is the Mighty, the Merciful.
|44|43|
The tree of cactus
|44|44|
is the food of the sinner;
|44|45|
like molten copper it shall bubble in the bellies,
|44|46|
as the bubbling of the boiling water.
|44|47|
`Take him and thrust him into the midst of Hell;
|44|48|
then pour over his head punishment of boiling water!'
|44|49|
`Taste, surely thou art the mighty, the noble.
|44|50|
This is that which you were doubting.'
|44|51|
The godfearing shall be in a secure station,
|44|52|
amidst gardens and fountains,
|44|53|
wearing silk and brocade, sitting face to face;
|44|54|
so it will be; and We shall wed them to wide-eyed damsels.
|44|55|
They, in security, shall call therein for every fruit;
|44|56|
they shall not taste therein death, except the first death; and He shall save them from the punishment of Hell,
|44|57|
as a bounty from thy Lord; that indeed is the mighty triumph.
|44|58|
Now We have surely made it easy in thy language, that they may pay heed.
|44|59|
So wait; they are waiting too.
|45|1|
Ha Mim (H.M.). 
|45|2|
The sending down of the Book is from God, the Mighty, the Wise.
|45|3|
Surely in the heavens and the earth there are Signs for the Believers.
|45|4|
And in your creation and the creatures that He scatters, there are Signs for a people who have faith.
|45|5|
And in the alternation of night and day, and the provision that God sends down from the heaven wherewith He revives the earth after it is dead and the turning about of winds, there are Signs for a people who understand.
|45|6|
Those are the Signs of God that We recite to thee with truth; in what discourse, after God and His Signs, will they believe?
|45|7|
Woe to every impostor, sinner,
|45|8|
who hears the Signs of God recited to him, yet persists in arrogance, as if he has not heard them; so give him good news of a painful punishment.
|45|9|
And when he learns anything of Our Signs, he takes them in mockery; those shall have a humiliating punishment.
|45|10|
Beyond them is Hell; and what they earned shall not avail them in the least, nor those whom they took as protectors apart from God; and for them shall be a big punishment.
|45|11|
This is a guidance; and those who disbelieve in the Signs of their Lord, shall have a painful punishment of scourge.
|45|12|
God is He who has subjected to you the sea, that the ships may sail on it by His command, and that you may seek His bounty, and you might be thankful.
|45|13|
And He has subjected to you whatever is in the heavens and whatever is in the earth, all from Him; in that are surely Signs for a people who ponder.
|45|14|
Say to the Believers to forgive those who do not look for the days of God, that He may recompense a people for what they were earning.
|45|15|
Whoso does righteousness, it is for himself, and whoso does evil, it is against him; then to your Lord you will be returned.
|45|16|
And We gave the Children of Israel the Book, the Judgement, and the Prophethood, and We provided them with good things, and We exalted them over all people.
|45|17|
And We gave them Clear Signs of the Affair and they differed not, but after the knowledge had come to them, aggressing against one another; surely thy Lord shall decide between them on the Day of Resurrection in what they differed.
|45|18|
Then We put thee on an open way of the Affair, so follow it, and follow not the caprices of those who have no knowledge.
|45|19|
They shall not avail thee against God in the least; and surely the wrong-doers are the friends of one another; and God is the friend of the godfearing.
|45|20|
These are clear evidences for men, and a guidance and a mercy for a people who have firm faith.
|45|21|
Or do those who commit evil deeds think that We shall make them as those who believe and do righteous deeds __ their living and their dying equal? How ill they judge!
|45|22|
And God has created the heavens and the earth with truth, and that every soul may be recompensed for what it earned, and they are not wronged.
|45|23|
Hast thou seen him who has taken his caprice to be his god, and God has led him astray, in spite of knowledge, and has set a seal upon his ears and his heart, and has laid a covering on his eyes? Now who shall guide him after God? Will you not then pay heed?
|45|24|
And they say, `it is only our present life that we die and live, and nothing but Time destroys us; but they have no knowledge of that; they only conjecture.
|45|25|
And when Our Clear Signs are recited to them, their only argument is that they say, `bring our fathers, if you are truthful.'
|45|26|
Say, `God gives you life, then makes you to die, then He shall gather you to the Day of Resurrection, whereof is no doubt, but most men do not know.'
|45|27|
And to God belongs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth; and on the day when the Hour comes, that day the vain-doers shall lose.
|45|28|
And thou shalt see every community on the knees, every community shall be called to its Book. -Today you shall be recompensed for what you were doing.
|45|29|
This is Our Book that speaks against you with truth; and We have been recording what you were doing.'
|45|30|
Now as for those who believed and did righteous deeds, their Lord shall admit them to His mercy; that is the clear triumph.
|45|31|
And as for those who disbelieved; __ `were not My Signs recited to you, but you showed arrogance and you were a sinful people?'
|45|32|
And when it was said, `God's promise is true, and there is no doubt in the Hour', you said, `we do not know what the Hour is; we think it only a surmise, and we are not at all certain.'
|45|33|
And the evils of what they did shall appear to them, and what they used to mock at shall encompass them.
|45|34|
And it shall be said, `today We forget you as you forgot the meeting of this day of yours, and your resort is the Fire, and you have no helpers.
|45|35|
That is because you took God's Signs in mockery, and the worldly life deluded you'. So to-day they shall not be brought out of it, nor shallthey be permitted to make amends.
|45|36|
So to God belongs the praise, the Lord of the heavens and the earth, the Lord of the whole world.
|45|37|
And His is the domination in the heavens and the earth, and He is the Mighty, the Wise.
|46|1|
Ha Mim (H.M.). 
|46|2|
The sending down of the Book is from God, the Mighty, the Wise.
|46|3|
We have not created the heavens and the earth and what between them is but with the truth, and for a stated term; but the unbelievers are turning away from what they are warned of.
|46|4|
Say, `have you considered those you call upon, apart from God? Show me what they have created of the earth, or have they any association in the heavens? Bring me a Book (sent) before this, or any trace of knowledge, if you are truthful?
|46|5|
And who is further astray than he who calls, apart from God, upon him who shall not answer him till the Day of Resurrection, and they are unaware of their calling.
|46|6|
And when mankind are mustered, they shall be enemies to them, and shall deny their service.
|46|7|
And when Our clear signs are recited to them, the unbelievers say of the truth, when it has come to them, `this is a clear sorcery.'
|46|8|
Or do they say, `he has forged it?' Say, `if I have forged it, you do not have any power to help me against God; He very well knows what you are pressing on; He suffices as a witness between me and you; and He is the Forgiving, the Merciful.'
|46|9|
Say, `I am not an innovation among the Messengers, and I do not know what shall be done with me or with you; I only follow what is revealed to me, and I am not but a clear warner.'
|46|10|
Say, `have you considered, if it be from God, and you disbelieve in it, and a witness from among the Children of Israel bears witness to its like and believes in it, and you show arrogance? Surely God does not guide a wrong-doing people.' 
|46|11|
And the unbelievers say of the Believers, `if it had been good, they would not have preceded us to it.' And since they are not guided by it, they will say, `this is an old lie.'
|46|12|
And before it was the Book of Moses for a guide and a mercy; and this is a Book confirming, in Arabic language, that it may warn the wrong-doers, and be a good news for the good-doers.
|46|13|
Those who say, `our Lord is God,' and then stand firm by it, there shall be no fear on them, nor shall they grieve.
|46|14|
Those are the people of Paradise, dwelling therein forever, as a recompense for that they have been doing.
|46|15|
And We have charged man to be good to his parents; his mother bears him with pain, and gives birth to him with pain; and his bearing and his weaning is for thirty moths; until, when he reaches his full strength, and reaches forty years, he says, `my Lord, dispose me that I may be thankful for Thy blessing with which Thou hast blessed me and my parents, and that I may do righteousness that pleases thee, and make for me my offspring righteous; I turn to thee and I am of those who have surrendered.'
|46|16|
Those are they from whom We shall accept the best of what they did and pass over their evil deeds; they are among the people of Paradise; it is the promise of the truth, which they are given.
|46|17|
But he who says to his parents, `fie upon you; do you threaten me that I shall be brought forth when many generations have passed away before me?' And they call upon God for help __ `woe to thee! believe; God's promise is surely true.' But he says, `these are only the fables of the ancients.'
|46|18|
Those are the ones against whom the Word has proved true in the communities of the jinn and the men that have passed away before them; they were surely losers.
|46|19|
And all shall have degrees according to what they did, and so that He may pay them in full for their deeds, and they are not wronged.
|46|20|
And on the day the unbelievers are presented before the Fire: `you took your good things in your worldly life and drew benefit from them; and today you shall be recompensed with the humiliating punishment, because you showed arrogance in the earth without right, and because you transgressed.'
|46|21|
And mention the brother of Ad; when he warned his people beside the sand-dunes __ and warners had passed away before him and after him __ (saying) `serve none but God; I fear for you punishment of a mighty day.'
|46|22|
They said, `hast thou come to pervert us from our gods? So bring us what thou threatens us, if thou art of the truthful.'
|46|23|
He said, `the knowledge is only with God, and I deliver to you the Message with which I have been sent, but I see you a people that show ignorance.'
|46|24|
Then, when they saw it as a cloud advancing to their valleys, they said, `this is a cloud that shall give us rain.' __ `No, it is what you sought to hasten, a wind wherein is a painful punishment,
|46|25|
that will destroy everything by the command of its Lord.' Then there remained nothing to be seen except their dwelling-places; thus do We recompense the sinful people.
|46|26|
And We had established them in theway We have not established you, and We had assigned to them the ears, the eyes and the hearts, yet their ears, their eyes and their hearts did not avail them in the least, when they denied the signs of God, and that at which they mocked encompassed them.
|46|27|
And We destroyed the cities about you, and We turned about the Signs that they may return.
|46|28|
Then why did those whom they had taken as gods, apart from God, not help them to bring them near Him? No, they were lost to them; and that was their calumny and what they had been forging.
|46|29|
And when We turned to thee a band of jinn giving ear to the Qur'an; and when they were in its presence, they said, `be silent'; and when it was finished, they went back to their people as warners.
|46|30|
They said, `O our people, we have heard a Book, sent down after Moses, confirming what was before it, and guiding to the truth and to a straight path.
|46|31|
O our people, answer God's Summoner and believe in Him; He will forgive you some of you sins, and protect you from a painful punishment.
|46|32|
And whoso does not answer God's Summoner, he cannot frustrate (God) in the earth, and he has no protectors, apart from Him; they are clearly astray.'
|46|33|
And have they not considered that God, who created the heavens and the earth, and is not wearied by their creation, is powerful enough to give life to the dead? Yes indeed; He is powerful over everything.
|46|34|
And on the day when the unbelievers are presented before the Fire: `is not this the truth?' They shall say, `yes, by our Lord.' He shall say, `so taste the punishment, for you disbelieved'.
|46|35|
So have thou patience, as the Messengers of resolute determi-nation showed patience, and do not seek to hasten it for them. On the day they see what they are promised, it shall be as if they had not stayed but an hour of the day. Message is delivered. Shall any be destroyed except the transgressing people?'
|47|1|
Those who disbelieved and barred from God's way, God has sent their works astray.
|47|2|
And those who believed and did righteous deeds, and believed in what is sent down to Muhammad __ and it is the truth form their Lord __ He has acquitted them of their evils and put right their condition.
|47|3|
That is because those who disbelieved followed falsehood, and those who believed followed the truth from their Lord. Thus does God describe their similitudes for Mankind.
|47|4|
Now when you meet the unbelievers, strike at their necks. Until, when you have slaughtered them sufficiently, tie fast the bonds; then afterwards (set them free) either by grace or by ransom, till the war lays down its loads __ so it shall be. And if God had willed, He could have avenged Himself upon them, but it was so that He may try some of you by others. And those who are killed in the way of God, He will never send their works astray.
|47|5|
He will guide them and put right their condition;
|47|6|
and He will admit them to Paradise, which He has made known to them.
|47|7|
O Believers, if you help God, He will help you, and will make firm your feet.
|47|8|
But the unbelievers __ their fate is to perish, for He has sent their deeds astray.
|47|9|
That is because they are averse to what God has sent down, so He has made their works to go waste.
|47|10|
Have they not journeyed in the land and seen how was the end of those before them? God destroyed them, and the unbelievers shall have the like of it.
|47|11|
That is because God is the Protector of the Believers, and the unbelievers, there is no protector for them.
|47|12|
God shall admit those who believe and do righteous deeds into gardens, underneath which rivers flow. And the unbelievers, they enjoy and eat as the cattle eat, and the Fire is their resort.
|47|13|
And how many a city there was that was stronger than thy city which has expelled thee! We destroyed them, and there was no helper for them.
|47|14|
Is then he who is upon a Clear Sign from his Lord like him for whom his evil deed is adorned, and they followed their caprices?
|47|15|
The similitude of Paradise promised to the godfearing (is this): In it are rivers of unstaling water, and rivers of milk of unchanging taste, and rivers of wine, a delight to the drinkers, and rivers of purified honey; and there they shall have every fruit, and forgiveness from their Lord. (Are they) like him who dwells in the Fire forever, and who are given to drink boiling water that tears their bowels asunder?
|47|16|
And some of them give ear to thee, till, when they go forth from thee, they say to those who have been given knowledge, `what has he said just now?' Those are the ones whose hearts God has sealed and have followed their caprices.
|47|17|
But those who are on guidance, He increases them in guidance, and gives them their piety.
|47|18|
Are they only looking for the Hour that should come upon them suddenly? But its tokens have already come; and when it comes upon them, how shall they have their admonition.
|47|19|
Know that there is no god but God, and ask forgiveness of thy shortcomings, and for the Believing men and women; and God knows your moving about and your resort.
|47|20|
And the Believers say, `why is not a Sura sent down?' But when a well-defined Sura is sent down, and fighting is mentioned therein, thou seest those in whose hearts is sickness, looking at thee with the look of one who faints at death; but preferable for them
|47|21|
was obedience and a desirable word. Then, when the matter is resolved, it would be better for them if they were true to God.
|47|22|
And if you turned away, you are likely to cause disorder in the land, and cut off your bonds of blood?
|47|23|
Those are the ones whom God has cursed, then made them deaf, and blinded their eyes.
|47|24|
Do they not ponder over the Qur'an, or is it that there are locks on their hearts?
|47|25|
Those who have turned on their backs, after the guidance has become clear to them, the Devil tempted them and gave them hopes.
|47|26|
That is because they said to those who are averse to what God has sent down, `we will obey you in some of the affair;' and God knows their secrets.
|47|27|
But how shall it be, when the angels take them, beating their faces and backs?
|47|28|
That is because they have followed what angered God, and were averse to His pleasure; so He has made their deeds to go waste.
|47|29|
Or did those in whose hearts is sickness think that God would not bring to light their malice?
|47|30|
But if We will, We would show them to thee, then thou wouldst recognise them by their mark; and thou wouldst surely recognise them by the twist of their speech; and God knows your works.
|47|31|
And We shall surely test you, till We know those of you who struggle and are steadfast and We shall try the news about you.
|47|32|
Those who disbelieved and barred from God's way, and opposed the Messenger after the guidance had become clear to them, they will not hurt God in the least; and He will make their works to go waste. 
|47|33|
O Believers, obey God and obey the Messenger, and do not make your works to go vain.
|47|34|
Those who disbelieved and barred from God's way, then died as unbelievers, God will never forgive them.
|47|35|
So be not slack and do not call for peace; and you shall be the most high, for God is with you, and He will not deprive you of your works.
|47|36|
The present life is only a sport and a diversion; and if you believe and be godfearing, He will give you your wages, and will not ask of you your wealth.
|47|37|
If He asks you for it, and presses you, you would be niggardly, and He will bring forth your malice.
|47|38|
Ha, you are those who are called upon to expend in the way of God, then some of you are niggardly. Whoso is niggardly, he is niggardly only to himself; and God is the All-sufficient and you are the poor. And if you turn away, He will substitute another people, in place of you, then they will not be like you.
|48|1|
We have given thee a clear victory,
|48|2|
that God may forgive thy shortcomings, both former and later, and complete His blessing upon thee, and guide thee to a straight path,
|48|3|
and God may help thee with a mighty help.
|48|4|
It is He who sent down tranquility in the hearts of the Believers that they may add faith to their faith __ and to God belong the hosts of the heavens and the earth; and God is Knowing, Wise __
|48|5|
that He may admit the Believers, men and women, to gardens underneath which rivers flow, to dwell therein forever, and remove their evils from them __ and that is, in God's sight, a mighty triumph __
|48|6|
and that He may punish the hypocrites, men and women, and the idolaters, men and women, who think evil thoughts about God. Against them shall be the evil turn of fortune, for God is angry with them, and has cursed them, and has prepared for them Hell, and it is an evil destination!
|48|7|
And to God belong the hosts of the heavens and the earth; and God is Mighty, Wise.
|48|8|
We have sent thee as a witness, and a bearer of good news and a warner,
|48|9|
that you may believe in God and His Messenger, and assist him, and revere him; and that you may extol God at the dawn and in the evening.
|48|10|
Those who swear allegiance to thee, they swear allegiance indeed to God; God's hand is over their hands; then whoso breaks his oath breaks it against himself; and whoso fulfils his covenant made with God, He will give him a big wage.
|48|11|
The Bedouins who lagged behind shall say to thee, `our properties and our families kept us occupied, so pray forgiveness for us.' They say with their tongues what is not in their hearts. Say, `who will avail you against God, in the least, if He desires hurt for you or desires profit for you? No, God is aware of what you do.
|48|12|
No, but you thought that the Messenger and the Believers would never return to their families, and that seemed fair in your hearts, and you thought evil thoughts, and you became a people doomed to perish.'
|48|13|
And whoso does not believe in God and His Messenger, for such unbelievers We have prepared a Blaze.
|48|14|
And to God belongs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth; He forgives whom He will, and punishes whom He will; and God is surely Forgiving, Merciful.
|48|15|
Those who lagged behind will say __ when you set forth after spoils, to take them __ `let us follow you'; they desire to change God's Word. Say, `you shall not follow us; so God said before'. Then they will say, `no, but you are jealous of us'. No, they have not understood except a little.
|48|16|
Say to the Bedouins who lagged behind, `you shall be called against a people of great might, and you will fight them or they will surrender; then if you obey, God will give you a good wage; and if you turn back as you turned back before, He will give you a painful punishment.'
|48|17|
There is no blame on the blind, and there is no blame on the lame, and there is no blame on the sick; and whoso obeys God and His Messenger, He will admit him to gardens underneath which rivers flow; and if any turns back, He will give him a painful punishment.
|48|18|
God was pleased with the Believers, when they were swearing allegiance to thee under the tree, and He knew what was in their hearts, so He sent down tranquility upon them, and rewarded them with a near victory
|48|19|
and many spoils, that they will take; and God is Mighty, Wise.
|48|20|
God promised you many spoils which you will take, so He hastened this to you and restrained the hands of men from you, and that it may be a Sign for the Believers, and He may guide you to a straight path.
|48|21|
And the other over which you had no power, but God had encompassed it; and God is surely powerful over everything.
|48|22|
And if the unbelievers had fought you, they would have turned their backs, and then would not find any protector or helper.
|48|23|
It is God's tradition that has passed before, and thou shalt not find any change in God's tradition.
|48|24|
And it is He who restrained their hands from you, and your hands from them, in the valley of Mecca, after He had given you victory over them; and surely God sees the things you do.
|48|25|
They are those who disbelieved and barred you from the Sacred Mosque and detained the Offering, so as not to reach its place of sacrifice. And if it had not been for Believers, men and women, whom you did not know, lest you should trample them and guilt may unwittingly befall you on their account __ that God may admit to His mercy whom He will __ if they had been separated clearly,We would have punished the unbelievers among them with a painful punishment.
|48|26|
When the unbelievers set up in their hearts fierceness, the fierceness of Days of Ignorance, then God sent down His tranquility upon His Messenger and the Believers, and made them adhere firmly to the word of piety, for they had a better right to it and were worthy of it; and God knows everything.
|48|27|
Surely God has fulfilled His Messenger's vision with truth; you shall enter the Sacred Mosque, if God will, in security, without fear, your heads shaved and hair cut short. He knew what you did not know, so He assigned, apart from that, a near victory.
|48|28|
It is He who has sent His Messenger with Guidance and the Religion of Truth, that He may cause it to prevail over all religions; and God suffices as a witness.
|48|29|
Muhammad is a Messenger of God; and those who are with him are hard against the unbelievers and merciful among themselves; thou seest them bowing, prostrating, seeking bounty and pleasure of God; their mark is on their faces, being the trace of prostration. That is their likeness in the Torah and their likeness in the Gospel; as a seed that puts forth its shoot, then strengthens it, then it becomes stout, then it rises straight on its stalk, pleasing the sowers that, through them, He may enrage the unbelievers; God promises those, who believe and who, out of them, do righteous deeds, forgiveness and a big wage.
|49|1|
O Believers, do not advance before God and His Messenger, and fear God; God is Hearing, Knowing.
|49|2|
O Believers, do not raise your voices above the Prophet's voice, nor be loud in your speech to him, as you are loud to one another, lest your works go waste and you do not perceive.
|49|3|
Those who keep their voices low in the presence of God's Messenger, those are the ones whose hearts God has tested for godfearing; for them shall be forgiveness and a big wage.
|49|4|
Those who call to thee from behind the apartments, most of them do not understand.
|49|5|
And if they had shown patience, till thou comes out to them, it would have been better for them; and God is Forgiving, Merciful.
|49|6|
O Believers, if a transgressor comes to you with a news, make clear, lest you afflict a people in ignorance, and then repent on what you have done.
|49|7|
And know that among you is the Messenger of God; if he obeys you in much of the affair, you would fall in trouble; but God has endeared to you belief and has adorned it in your hearts, and He has made hateful to you unbelief, transgression and disobedience; those are the right-minded people,
|49|8|
by God's favour and blessing; God is Knowing, Wise.
|49|9|
And if two groups of the Believers fight together, put things right between them; then if one of the two aggresses against the other, fight the one that aggresses till it reverts to God's command; then if it reverts, put things right between the two equitably and be just; surely God loves the just.
|49|10|
The Believes are but brothers; so put things right between your two brothers, and fear God that you may find mercy.
|49|11|
O Believers, let not a people scoff at another people, it may be they are better than they, nor let women (scoff) at other women, it may be they are better than they. And do not find fault with one another, nor call by nicknames. Giving bad names is transgression after belief, and those who do not repent, they are the wrong-doers.
|49|12|
O Believers, avoid much of suspicion; some suspicion is a sin; and do not spy, nor backbite one another; does any of you like to eat the flesh of his dead brother; you would hate it; and fear God; God is All-returning, Merciful.
|49|13|
O mankind, We have created you from a male and a female, and made you races and tribes, that you may know one another; the noblest among you, in the sight of God, is the one most godfearing of you; God is Knowing, Aware.
|49|14|
The Bedouins say, `we believe.' Say `you do not believe; rather say, `we surrender, for belief has yet not entered your hearts; but if you obey God and His Messenger, He will not diminish you anything of your works; God is Forgiving, Merciful'.
|49|15|
The Believers are only those who believe in God and His Messenger, then doubt not, and struggle with their possessions and their selves in the way of God; those are the truthful ones.
|49|16|
Say, `would you teach God about your religion; and God knows whatever is in the heavens and whatever is in the earth; and God has knowledge of everything?'
|49|17|
They count it as a favour to thee that they have surrendered. Say, `do not count your surrender as a favour to me; no, but God confers favour upon you, that He has guided you to Belief, if you are truthful.'
|49|18|
God knows the unseen of the heavens and the earth; and God sees what you do.
|50|1|
Qaf __ by the Glorious Qur'an; but they wonder that a warner
|50|2|
has come to them from among themselves, and the unbelievers say, `this is a wonderful thing!
|50|3|
What! when we are dead and become dust __ that is a far returning!'
|50|4|
We know what the earth diminishes of them, and with Us is a guarding Book.
|50|5|
No, they gave lies to the truth when it came to them, and are now in a state of confusion.
|50|6|
But have they not observed the heaven above them, how We built it, and adorned it, and it has no fissures?
|50|7|
And the earth, We have spread it out, and cast firm mountains in it, and made to grow in it all kinds of lovely things
|50|8|
for an insight and an admonition to every penitent servant.
|50|9|
And We sent down from the heaven blessed water, then made to grow thereby gardens and grain of harvest,
|50|10|
and tall palm-trees with compact spathes,
|50|11|
for a provision for the servants; and We revived thereby a dead land __ thus shall is the coming forth.
|50|12|
Cried lies before them, people of Noah, and the men of Rass, and Thamood,
|50|13|
and Ad, and Pharaoh, and the brothers of Lot,
|50|14|
and the men of the Wood, and the people of Tubba; all Cried lies to the Messengers, so My threat was realised.
|50|15|
Were We wearied by the first creation? NO, but they are in doubt regarding a new creation.
|50|16|
And surely, We created man and We know what his soul whispers to him, and We are nearer to him than the jugular vein.
|50|17|
When the two receivers sitting on the right and on the left, receive.
|50|18|
Not a word he utters, but by him is a ready observer.
|50|19|
And the stupor of death will comes in truth; this is what thou wast shunning!
|50|20|
And the Trumpet is blown __ this is the Day of Threat.
|50|21|
And every soul comes with a driver and a witness;
|50|22|
`Thou wast heedless of this; now We have removed thy covering from thee, so thy sight today is sharp.
|50|23|
' And his comrade says `this is what is ready with me.' __
|50|24|
`Cast into Hell, (you two) every ungrateful froward,
|50|25|
hinderer of good, transgressor, doubter,
|50|26|
who set up with God another god; cast him into the terrible punishment.'
|50|27|
His comrade says, `our Lord, I did not make him to rebel, but he himselfwas far astray.'
|50|28|
God will say, `do not dispute before Me, for I sent you the threat before hand.
|50|29|
The Word is not changed with Me, and I am no tyrant over My servants.'
|50|30|
On that day We shall say to Hell `art thou filled up?' And it shall say, `are there any more?'
|50|31|
And Paradise shall be brought forward to the godfearing, not far off:
|50|32|
`This is what was promised to you, for every mindful penitent,
|50|33|
who feared the All-merciful in the unseen, and came with a penitent heart __
|50|34|
`Enter it in peace! This is the Day of Eternity.'
|50|35|
For them therein shall be what they will, and with Us shall be yet more.
|50|36|
And how many a generation We destroyed before them, that was stronger in valour than they, then they searched about in the land: `Is there a place to escape?'
|50|37|
Surely in this is an admonition for him who has a heart, or gives ear and is observant.
|50|38|
And We created the heavens and the earth and what between them is in six days, and no weariness touched Us.
|50|39|
So be thou patient on what they say, and celebrate the praise of thy Lord before the rising of the sun, and before the setting;
|50|40|
and extol Him during night and at the ends of the prostrations.
|50|41|
And listen for the day when the caller will call from a nearby place,
|50|42|
on the day they hear the Cry in truth; this is the Day of Coming Forth.
|50|43|
It is We who give life and make to die, and to Us is the destination.
|50|44|
On the day when the earth is split asunder from about them, hastily; that mustering is easy for Us.
|50|45|
We very well know what they say, and thou art no compeller over them; so remind, by the Qur'an, him who fears My threat.
|51|1|
By the forces that scatter wide apart,
|51|2|
then carry the burden,
|51|3|
then run with ease,
|51|4|
then apportion the thing ordained,
|51|5|
surely that you are promised is true,
|51|6|
and the Recompense must come to pass.
|51|7|
By the heaven of the tracks,
|51|8|
you are at variance in speech,
|51|9|
and perverted from it is the one perverted.
|51|10|
Perish the conjecturers,
|51|11|
who in confusion are forgetful __
|51|12|
they ask, `when shall be the Day of Recompense?'
|51|13|
`On the day when they shall be tried at the Fire: 
|51|14|
`Taste your trial! This is what you have been seeking to hasten'.
|51|15|
The godfearing shall be amidst gardens and fountains,
|51|16|
taking what their Lord would give them; they were surely good-doers before that.
|51|17|
Little of the night would they sleep;
|51|18|
and at dawns they would pray for forgiveness.
|51|19|
And in their wealth was a right for the beggar and the destitute.
|51|20|
And in the earth are Signs for those who have faith
|51|21|
and also in your selves; will you not see?
|51|22|
And in the heaven is your provision, and that which you are promised.
|51|23|
So by the Lord of the heaven and the earth, it is as surely true as that you speak.
|51|24|
Hast the story of the honoured guests of Abraham come to thee?
|51|25|
When they entered to him, they said, `peace'; he said, `peace; a people unknown!'
|51|26|
Then he turned to his household and brought a fattened calf,
|51|27|
and laid it before them, saying, `will you not eat?'
|51|28|
Then he conceived fear of them. They said, `fear not'. And they gave him good news of a learned boy.
|51|29|
Then came forward his wife clamouring, and she struck her face, and said, `a barren old woman!'
|51|30|
They said, `so has thy Lord said; surely He is the Wise, the Knowing.'
|51|31|
He said, `what is your business, O envoys?
|51|32|
They said, `We have been sent to a people of sinners
|51|33|
that We may loose upon them stones of clay,
|51|34|
marked with thy Lord for the extravagant'.
|51|35|
Then We brought forth whoso was a Believer in it,
|51|36|
and We did not find in it another house of those that had surrendered.
|51|37|
And We left in it a Sign for those who fear the painful punishment.
|51|38|
And also in Moses, when We sent him to Pharaoh with a clear authority.
|51|39|
But he, together with his court, turned back, and said, `a sorcerer or a mad man'.
|51|40|
Then We seized him and his hosts, and cast them into the sea, and he was to blame.
|51|41|
And also in Ad, when We loosed upon them a devastating wind,
|51|42|
which left nothing it came upon, but made it as stuff decayed.
|51|43|
And also in Thamood, when it was said to them, `enjoy for a while!'
|51|44|
But they turned in disdain from the commandment of their Lord. So the thunderbolt took them,
|51|45|
while they looked on. Then they could not stand up, nor could defend themselves.
|51|46|
And the people of Noah before; they were a people of trangressors. 
|51|47|
And the heaven, We built it with might, and We will surely be extending it.
|51|48|
And the earth, We spread it forth, and how excellent are the smoothers!
|51|49|
And of everything We created two kinds that you may heed.
|51|50|
So flee to God; I am from Him a clear warner to you.
|51|51|
And do not set up with God another god; I am from Him a clear warner to you.
|51|52|
Even so no Messenger came to those before them but they said, `a sorcerer or a mad man!'
|51|53|
Have they bequeathed it on? No, they are an insolent people.
|51|54|
So turn thou away from them, for thou art not to blame.
|51|55|
And remind, for the Reminder profits the Believers.
|51|56|
And I have not created jinn and men except that they should serve Me.
|51|57|
I do not desire of them any provision, and I do not desire that they should feed Me.
|51|58|
Surely God is the All-provider, the Strong, the Firm.
|51|59|
The wrong-doers shall have the portion like the portion of their fellows, so let them not seek to hasten Me!
|51|60|
And woe to the unbelievers, for that day of theirs that they are promised.
|52|1|
By the Mount,
|52|2|
and a Book inscribed,
|52|3|
in a parchment unfolded,
|52|4|
and the House inhabited,
|52|5|
and the Roof raised up,
|52|6|
and the Sea poured forth,
|52|7|
thy Lord's punishment is sure to fall;
|52|8|
there is none to avert it.
|52|9|
On the day when the heaven shakes violently,
|52|10|
and the mountains move on;
|52|11|
woe that day to those who cry lies,
|52|12|
who play in vain talk,
|52|13|
the day when they shall be thrust into the Fire of Hell: 
|52|14|
`this is the Fire that you were giving lies to;
|52|15|
is this sorcery, or is it you that did not see? 
|52|16|
Enter it, then have patience or have no patience, it is equal to you; you are being recompensed only for that you were doing.'
|52|17|
The godfearing will be in gardens and bliss,
|52|18|
rejoicing in what their Lord has given them; and their Lord shall save them from the punishment of Hell:
|52|19|
`Eat and drink with wholesome appetite for that you were doing;
|52|20|
reclining on couches placed in rows;' and We shall couple them with wide-eyed maidens.
|52|21|
And those who believed, and their offspring followed them in belief, We will join their offspring with them, and We will diminish not for them anything from their work; every man is pledged for what he earned.
|52|22|
And We will aid them with fruits and flesh, such as their hearts desire.
|52|23|
They will pass therein a cup to one another, no non-sense talk there, no cause of sin.
|52|24|
And there will go round them youths, meant for them, as if they were hidden pearls.
|52|25|
And they will advance to each other, asking questions.
|52|26|
They will say, `we were before this among our families in fear.
|52|27|
Then God was gracious to us, and has saved us from the punishment of the burning wind.
|52|28|
We used to call upon Him before; surely He is the Beneficent, the Merciful.
|52|29|
Therefore remind. and by thy Lord's blessing, thou art not a soothsayer nor a madman.
|52|30|
Or do they say, `he is a poet, for whom we await uncertainty of time?'
|52|31|
Say, `wait, I too am waiting with you'.
|52|32|
Or does their reasoning bid them to this, or are they a people of rebels.
|52|33|
Or do they say, `he has invented it?' No, but they do not believe.
|52|34|
Then let them bring a discourse like this, if they are truthful.
|52|35|
Or were they created out of nothing, or are they the creators?
|52|36|
Or did they create the heavens and the earth?
|52|37|
No, but they have no faith. Or are with them thy Lord's treasures or are they the controllers?
|52|38|
Or have they a ladder to listen through? Then let their listener bring a clear authority.
|52|39|
Or has He daughters, and you sons?
|52|40|
Or dost thou ask them for a wage, and they are weighed down with debt?
|52|41|
Or is the unseen with them, and they are writing it down?
|52|42|
Or do they desire to lay a guile?
|52|43|
But the unbelievers themselves are caught in the guile. Or have they a god other than God? Holy be God, above that they associate!
|52|44|
And if they see a fragment falling from the heaven, they would say `a cloud piled up!'
|52|45|
So leave them, till they meet their day, wherein they shall be thunderstruck;
|52|46|
the day when their guile shall not avail them in the least, nor shall they be helped.
|52|47|
And surely, for the wrong-doers there shall be a punishment besides that, but most of them do not know.
|52|48|
And be thou patient for thy Lord's judgement, for thou art before Our eyes; and celebrate the praise of thy Lord when thou risest;
|52|49|
and extol Him during night, and at the declining of the stars.
|53|1|
By the star when it plunges,
|53|2|
your companion is not astray, nor perverted;
|53|3|
nor does he speak out of caprice.
|53|4|
It is naught but a revelation revealed,
|53|5|
which One mighty in power,
|53|6|
very strong, taught him. He stood poised,
|53|7|
and he was on the highest horizon;
|53|8|
then he drew near and was close by,
|53|9|
and he was two bows' length away, or nearer,
|53|10|
then He revealed to His Servant what He revealed.
|53|11|
The heart did not lie in what he saw.
|53|12|
Will you then dispute with him on what he sees?
|53|13|
And he saw it another time;
|53|14|
by the Lote-tree of the extreme end.
|53|15|
Near it is the Garden of the abode.
|53|16|
When there covers the Lote-tree
|53|17|
that which covers, the eye did not swerve, nor transgressed.
|53|18|
Indeed he saw some of the greatest Signs of his Lord.
|53|19|
Have you then considered Lat and Uzza,
|53|20|
and Manat the third, the other?
|53|21|
Are males for you, and for Him females?
|53|22|
That then is an unfair division.
|53|23|
They are not but names that you have given, you and your fathers, for which God has not sent down any authority. They follow only surmise and what the souls desire, while there has come to them guidance from their Lord.
|53|24|
Or shall man have what he longs for?
|53|25|
But to God belongs the Last and the First.
|53|26|
And how many an angel there is in the heavens, whose intercession does not avail in the least, but after God gives leave to whom He will and is pleased.
|53|27|
Those who do not believe in the Hereafter give the angels female names.
|53|28|
But they have no knowledge thereof; they only follow surmise; and surmise does not avail against the truth in the least.
|53|29|
So turn thou from him who turns away from Our Remembrance, and desires only the life of this world.
|53|30|
That is their ultimate reach in knowledge. Surely Thy Lord very well knows him who has gone astray from His way, and He very well knows him who is guided.
|53|31|
And to God belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is in the earth, that He may recompense those who do evil for what they have done and recompense those who do good with the best reward.
|53|32|
Those who avoid major sins and indecencies, except minor faults; surely thy Lord is All-embracing in forgiveness. He very well know you, when He produced you from the earth, and when you were embryos in your mothers' wombs; so do not ascribe purity to yourselves; He very well knows him who is godfearing.
|53|33|
Now, hast thou seen him who turned away;
|53|34|
and he gave a little, then withheld?
|53|35|
Has he the knowledge of the unseen and so he sees?
|53|36|
Or has he not been told of what is in the Scrolls of Moses,
|53|37|
and of Abraham who fulfilled __ 
|53|38|
that no laden soul bears the load of another,
|53|39|
that there shall be nothing for man except as he laboured, 
|53|40|
and that his labouring shall soon be seen,
|53|41|
then he shall be recompensed for it with the fullest recompense,
|53|42|
and that to thy Lord is the final end;
|53|43|
and that it is He who makes to laugh and makes to weep,
|53|44|
and it is He who makes to die and makes to live,
|53|45|
and it is He who creates two kinds, male and female,
|53|46|
of a sperm-drop when it is spilled,
|53|47|
and that upon Him rests the second growth,
|53|48|
and that it is He who gives riches and contentment,
|53|49|
and that it is He who is the Lord of the Sirius,
|53|50|
and that it is He who destroyed Ad, the ancient,
|53|51|
and Thamood, and spared not,
|53|52|
and Noah's people before; surely they were the biggest wrong-doers and most rebellious.
|53|53|
And the Subverted City, He struck down;
|53|54|
then there covered it that which covered.
|53|55|
Now which of thy Lord's bounties shalt thou dispute?
|53|56|
This is a warner of the warners of old.
|53|57|
The Imminent has drawn near;
|53|58|
there is none, apart from God, to disclose it.
|53|59|
Do you then wonder at this discourse,
|53|60|
and laugh, and weep not,
|53|61|
and you make merry?
|53|62|
But prostrate yourselves to God and serve Him.
|54|1|
The Hour has drawn near, and the moon is split.
|54|2|
