|56|1|
When the Event befalls __
|56|2|
none denying that it shall befall __
|56|3|
abasing, exalting;
|56|4|
when the earth shall be rocked,
|56|5|
and the mountains crumbled,
|56|6|
and become scattered dust,
|56|7|
and you will be three kinds.
|56|8|
So Those on the Right, what of Those on the right!
|56|9|
And Those on the Left, what of Those on the Left!
|56|10|
And the Outstrippers, yes, the Outstrippers __
|56|11|
those shall be the near-stationed,
|56|12|
in the gardens of bliss.
|56|13|
A multitude among the former,
|56|14|
a few among the later.
|56|15|
On jewelled couches,
|56|16|
reclining on them, facing each other.
|56|17|
Ever-abiding youths shall be going round them
|56|18|
with goblets and ewers and a cup from a spring __
|56|19|
no headache they get by it, nor intoxication __
|56|20|
and such fruits as they choose,
|56|21|
and such flesh of fowls as their hearts desire;
|56|22|
and wide-eyed maidens,
|56|23|
as the likeness of covered pearls __
|56|24|
a recompense for that they have been doing.
|56|25|
Therein they shall not hear any non-sense nor any cause of sin,
|56|26|
but the words, `Peace, Peace.'
|56|27|
And Those on the Right, what of Those on the Right __
|56|28|
they shall be amidst thornless lote-trees,
|56|29|
and clustered banana-trees,
|56|30|
spreading shade,
|56|31|
and gushing water,
|56|32|
and plentiful fruits __
|56|33|
neither failing nor forbidden __
|56|34|
