|56|35|
We have formed them perfect,
|56|36|
and made them virgins,
|56|37|
loving, of like age,
|56|38|
for Those on the Right __
|56|39|
a multitude among the former,
|56|40|
a multitude among the later.
|56|41|
And Those on the Left, what of Those on the Left;
|56|42|
they shall be amidst scorching winds and scalding waters,
|56|43|
and the shadow of black smoke __
|56|44|
neither cool nor refreshing.
|56|45|
Before that, they lived at ease,
|56|46|
and persisted in the Great Sin.
|56|47|
And they used to say, `is it that when we are dead and become dust and bones, shall we be raised up,
|56|48|
and our ancient fathers?'
|56|49|
Say, `surely the former and the later folk
|56|50|
shall be gathered to the appointed time of a known day.
|56|51|
Then, O you that have gone astray and cried lies!
|56|52|
you shall eat of a tree of cactus,
|56|53|
and fill your bellies with it;
|56|54|
and, on top of that, you shall drink boiling water,
|56|55|
and drink as drinks the thirsty camel.
|56|56|
This shall be their hospitality on the Day of Recompense.
|56|57|
We have created you, then why do you not confirm?
|56|58|
Have you considered that which you spill?
|56|59|
Do you create it, or are We the Creators?
|56|60|
We have decreed death between you, and We cannot be outstripped,
|56|61|
in that We change your likes, and make you to grow in a form you do not know.
|56|62|
And you have known the first form, then why do you not pay heed?
|56|63|
Have you considered that which you sow?
|56|64|
Do you cause it to grow, or are We the Growers?
|56|65|
If We will, We would make it broken bits, and you would remain bitterly jesting:
|56|66|
`We are debt-loaded;
|56|67|
no, we have been deprived!'
|56|68|
Have you considered the water you drink?
|56|69|
Did you send it down from the clouds, or are We the Senders?
|56|70|
If We will, We would make it bitter; then why do you not give thanks?
|56|71|
Have you considered the fire that you kindle?
|56|72|
Did you make its tree to grow, or are We the Growers?
|56|73|
We Ourselves have made it a reminder and a comfort for the desert-dwellers.
|56|74|
So extol the Name of thy Mighty Lord.
|56|75|
But no, I swear by the sites of the stars __
|56|76|
and that is indeed a mighty oath if you but knew__ 
|56|77|
it is surely a Noble Reading (Qur'an),
|56|78|
in a Hidden Book,
|56|79|
