|56|95|
Surely this is the Truth of Certainty.
|56|96|
So extol the Name of thy Mighty Lord.
|57|1|
All that is in the heavens and the earth extols God; and He is the Mighty, the Wise.
|57|2|
His is the Kingdom of the heavens and the earth; He gives life and makes to die; and He is powerful over everything.
|57|3|
He is the First and the Last, the Manifest and the Hidden, and He has knowledge of everything.
|57|4|
It is He who created the heavens and the earth in six days, then took over the Throne; He knows what enters into the earth and what comes out of it; what comes down from heaven and what goes up into it; He is with you wherever you may be; and God sees what you do.
|57|5|
His is the kingdom of the heavens and the earth; and to Him all matters are returned.
|57|6|
He makes the night to enter into the day, and makes the day to enter into the night; and He knows the thoughts in the breasts.
|57|7|
Have faith in God and His Messenger, and expend of that to which He has made you heirs. And those of you who have faith and expend shall have a mighty wage.
|57|8|
And how is it with you, that you do not have faith in God, when the Messenger calls you to have faith in your Lord, and He has indeed taken compact with you, if you are Believers?
|57|9|
It is He who sends down upon His Servant clear signs that he may take you out of darkness into the light; and God is surely Kind and Merciful to you.
|57|10|
And how is it with you, that you do not expend in the way of God, when to God belongs the heritage of the heavens and the earth? Not equal are those among you who expended and fought before the victory; those are greater in rank than those who expended and fought afterwards. And to all God has promised the best reward; and God is aware of what you do.
|57|11|
Who is he that will lend to God a good loan, then He will multiply it for him, and for him shall be a generous wage.
|57|12|
On the day when thou seest the Believers, men and women, their light running before them and on their right: `Good news for you today __ gardens underneath which rivers flow, to dwell therein forever; that is the mighty triumph'.
|57|13|
On the day when the hypocrites, men and women, shall say to the Believers, `wait for us that we may borrow from you some light;' it will be said, `return to your rear and seek for a light.' And there shall be set up between them a wall having a door; on its inside shall be mercy, and along its outer side punishment.
|57|14|
They shall call on them, `were we not with you?' They shall say, `yes, but you tempted yourselves, and waited, and doubted, and fancies deluded you, and the Deluder deluded you about God, until God's command came.
|57|15|
So today, no ransom shall be taken from you, nor from the unbelievers; your abode is the Fire; that is your comrade; and it is an evil destination!'
|57|16|
Has not the time for the Believers come that their hearts should be humbled to the Remembrance of God and to the Truth that He has sent down, and that they should not be like those who were given the Book before, then the term became long over them, so their hearts became hard; and many of them are transgressors?
|57|17|
Know that it is God who revives the earth after it is dead. We have explained the Signs for you that you might understand.
|57|18|
Those men and women who make offerings and lend God a good loan, it shall be multiplied for them, and they shall have a generous wage.
|57|19|
And those who have faith in God and His Messenger, they are the Truthful and the Witnesses in the sight of their Lord; they shall have their wage and their light. But those who disbelieve and give lies to Our Signs, they are the people of Hell.
|57|20|
Know that the present life is only a sport and a diversion, and an adornment and a cause for boasting among you, and a rivalry in wealth and children. It is like rain whose vegetation pleases the husbandmen; then it withers and thou seest it turning yellow, then it becomes broken bits. And in the Hereafter, there shall be a terrible punishment, and also forgiveness and pleasure from God; and the present life is not but the stuff of delusion.
|57|21|
Race to forgiveness of your Lord and a Garden whose breadth is as the breadth of the heaven and the earth, and is prepared for those who believe in God and His Messengers; that is the bounty of God; He gives it to whomsoever He will; and God is Highly Bounteous.
|57|22|
No affliction befalls in the earth or in yourselves, but it is in a Book before We create it; surely that is easy for God.
|57|23|
This is so that you may not grieve for what escaped you, nor rejoice in what He has given you; and God does not love any proud, boastful man,
|57|24|
those who are niggardly and bid men to be niggardly. And if any turns away, then surely God is the All-sufficient, the Praiseworthy.
|57|25|
We sent Our Messengers with the Clear Signs, and sent down with them the Book and the Balance, that men should stand by justice; and We sent down iron wherein is terrible might and other uses for mankind, and that God may know him who helps Him and His Messengers in the unseen; surely God is Strong and Mighty.
|57|26|
And We sent Noah and Abraham, and We kept the Prophethood and the Book in their offspring; now some of them are on right lines, but most of them are transgressors.
|57|27|
Then, following in their footsteps, We sent Our Messengers, and following them, We sent Jesus, son of Mary, and gave him the Gospel, and We placed in the hearts of his followers tenderness and mercy; but monasticism they invented themselves __ We did not prescribe it for them, except the seeking of God's good pleasure; then they did not observe it as it should be observed; so We gave the Believers among them their wage; but many of them are transgressors.
|57|28|
O Believers, fear God, and believe in His Messenger, and He will give you a twofold portion of His mercy, and He will appoint for you a light whereby you shall walk, and He will forgive you; and God is Forgiving, Merciful.
|57|29|
It is so that the People of the Book may know that they do not have power over anything of God's bounty, that the bounty is in the hand of God, and He gives it to whom He will; and God is Highly Bounteous.
|58|1|
God has heard the talk of her who was disputing with thee concerning her husband, and was complaining to God; and God was hearing your conversation; surely God is Hearing, Seeing.
|58|2|
Those of you who declare their wives as their mothers, they are not their mothers; their mothers are only those who gave them birth; they surely utter disgusting words and falsehood; yet surely God is Pardoning, Forgiving.
|58|3|
And those who declare their wives as their mothers, then retract from what they said, they shall set free a slave before they touch each other; by that you are admonished; and God is Aware of what you do.
|58|4|
But he who does not find it, he shall fast for two successive months, before they touch each other; and he who is not able to do so, let him feed sixty needy persons; this is so that you have faith in God and His Messenger; and these are God's bounds; and for the unbelievers shall be a painful punishment.
|58|5|
Those who oppose God and His Messenger shall be frustrated as those before them were frustrated, and indeed We have sent down Clear Signs; and for the unbelievers shall be a disgraceful punishment;
|58|6|
on the day when God shall raise them up all together, He will tell them what they did; God has numbered it, and they have forgotten it; and God is witness over everything.
|58|7|
Hast thou not seen that God knows whatsoever is in the heavens and whatsoever is in the earth? There is no secret counsel of three but He is the fourth of them, nor of five but He is the sixth of them, nor of fewer than that nor of more but He is with them wherever they may be; then, on the Day of Resurrection, He shall tell them what they did; God knows everything.
|58|8|
Hast thou not seen those who were forbidden to hold secret counsels; yet they return to that they were forbidden, and they confer secretly in sin, enmity and disobedience to the Messenger. And when they come to thee, they greet thee as God has not greeted thee, and say within themselves, `why does God not punish us for what we say?' Sufficient for them shall be Hell, which they shall enter; how evil is the destination!
|58|9|
O Believers, when you confer secretly, do not confer in sin, enmity and disobedience to the Messenger, but confer in virtue and godfearing; and fear God to whom you shall be mustered.
|58|10|
Secret counsel is only of the Devil, that the Believers may be grieved, though he is none to hurt them in the least, except by God's leave; and in God let the Believers put their trust.
|58|11|
O Believers, when it is said to you, `make room in the assemblies', then make room, and God will make room for you. And when it is said, `rise up', then rise up, and God will raise high in rank those among you who have faith and those who have been given knowledge; and God is aware of what you do.
|58|12|
O Believers, when you confer secretly with the Messenger, advance an offering before your conferring; that is better and purer for you; however, if you find it not, then God is Forgiving, Merciful.
|58|13|
Are you afraid to advance offerings before your conferring? Now that you have not done so, and God has also turned to you, establish the Prayer and pay the Due-alms, and obey God and His Messenger; and God is aware of what you do.
|58|14|
Hast thou not seen those who have taken for friends a people upon whom God has been wrathful? They neither belong to you nor to them, and they swear on falsehood and that knowingly.
|58|15|
God has prepared for them a terrible punishment; how evil things they have been doing.
|58|16|
They have taken their oaths as a covering, and have so barred from the way of God, so for them shall be a disgraceful punishment.
|58|17|
Their wealth shall not avail them, nor their children, against God in the least; they are people of the Fire; they shall dwell therein forever.
|58|18|
On the day when God shall raise them up all together, they will swear to Him as they swear to you and think that they are on something. Behold, they are the liars.
|58|19|
The Devil has gained mastery over them, and has made them to forget the remembrance of God; they are the Devil's group. Behold, the Devil's group are the losers.
|58|20|
Those who oppose God and His Messenger, they shall be among the most abject.
|58|21|
God has written, `I and My Messengers shall be the victors;' surely God is Strong and Mighty.
|58|22|
Thou shalt not find a people who believe in God and the Last Day, loving those who oppose God and His Messenger, even thought they were their fathers, their sons, their brothers or their clan. Those __ He has written faith on their hearts, and He has strengthened them with a Spirit from Him; and He shall admit them to gardens underneath which rivers flow to dwell therein forever; God is pleased with them and they are pleased with Him; those are God's group. Behold, God's group are the ones successful.
|59|1|
All that is in the heavens and all that is in the earth extols God; and He is the Mighty, the Wise.
|59|2|
He it is who expelled the unbelievers of the People of the Book from their homes at the first mustering; you did not think that they would go forth, and they thought that their fortresses would defend them against God; but God came upon them whence they had not reckoned, and He cast into their hearts such terror that they destroyed their houses with their own hands, and the hands of the Believers; so learn a lesson, O you who have eyes!
|59|3|
And if God had not prescribed exile for them, He would have punished them in this life. And in the Hereafter they shall have punishment of the Fire.
|59|4|
That is because they apposed God and His Messenger; and if any apposes God, then God is terrible in retribution.
|59|5|
Whatever palm-trees you cut down, or left standing on their roots, it was by God's leave, and that He may humiliate the transgressors.
|59|6|
And whatever spoils God has passed from them to His Messenger, you did not spur any horse or camel against them; but God gives authority to His Messengers over whomsoever He will; and God is powerful over everything.
|59|7|
Whatever spoils God has passed from the people of the townships to His Messenger, it is for God, for the Messenger and for the near kinsman, orphans, the needy and the traveller, so that it may not go in circuits among your rich; and whatever the Messenger gives you, take it, and whatever he forbids you, give over, and fear God; God is terrible in retribution.
|59|8|
It is for the poor emigrants, who were expelled from their homes and their possessions, seeking bounty and good pleasure from God, and helping God and His Messenger; they are the truthful ones.
|59|9|
And those who were settled in the city and in Faith before them, love those who emigrated towards them, and they do not find any need in their breasts for what has been given to them, and prefer them above themselves, though poverty be their lot; and whoso is saved from the greed of his soul __ those are the ones who will prosper.
|59|10|
And for those who came after them, they say, `Our Lord, forgive us and our brothers who preceded us in Belief, and do not put in our hearts any rancour for the Believers; our Lord, Thou art Kind, Merciful.'
|59|11|
Hast thou not seen the hypocrites, saying to their brothers __ the unbelievers of the People of the Book __ `if you are expelled, we will go forth with you, and we will never obey anyone in your case; and if you are fought against, we will surely help you'. But God bears witness that they are liars.
|59|12|
If they are expelled, they will not go forth with them, and if they are fought against, they will not help them; and even if they helped them, they would surely turn their backs, then they would not be helped.
|59|13|
In fact you arouse greater awe in their hearts than God; it is because they are a people who do not understand.
|59|14|
They will not fight against you all together, except in fortified towns or from behind the walls; their fighting among themselves is great; thou thinkest them together, but their hearts are scattered; that is because they are a people who have no sense.
|59|15|
Like those who, shortly before them, tasted the penalty of their affair; and for them was a painful punishment.
|59|16|
Like the Devil, when he said to Man, `disbelieve'; and when he disbelieved, he said, `I am quit of thee; I fear God, the Lord of the world'.
|59|17|
So the end of the two was that they are in the Fire, to dwell therein forever; and that is the recompense of the wrongdoers.
|59|18|
O Believers, fear God, and let a person look to what it has forwarded for the morrow, and fear God; surely God is aware of the things you do.
|59|19|
And be not as those who forgot God, then He made them to forget themselves; those are the transgressors.
|59|20|
The inhabitants of the Fire and the inhabitants of Paradise are not equal; the inhabitants of Paradise are the triumphant.
|59|21|
Had We sent down this Qur'an on a mountain, thou wouldst have seen it humbled and split asunder out of the fear of God; and these similitudes We describe for mankind that they may ponder.
|59|22|
He is God, except whom there is no god; the Knower of the unseen and the visible; He is the Merciful, the All-merciful!
|59|23|
He is God, except whom there is no god; the King, the Holy, the Peaceable, the Securer, the Preserver, the Mighty, the Compeller, the Majestic; Holy be God, above that they associate (with Him)!
|59|24|
He is God, the Creator, the Maker, the Shaper, His are the Names most beautiful; all that is in the heavens and the earth extols Him; and He is the Mighty, the Wise.
|60|1|
O Believers, do not take My enemies and your enemies for friends, by offering them love, while they have disbelieved in the truth that has come to you, expelling the Messenger and you, because you believe in God, your Lord. If you go forth to struggle in My way and seek My pleasure, secretly sending them love, and I know what you conceal and what you announce; and whosoever of you does it has indeed gone astray from the even way.
|60|2|
If they come on you, they will be enemies to you, and will stretch their hands and their tongues against you to do you evil, and they wish if you would disbelieve.
|60|3|
Your blood relations shall not profit you, nor your children, on the Day of Resurrection, when He will decide between you; and God sees what you do.
|60|4|
Surely you have a good example in Abraham and those with him, when they said to their people, `we are quit of you and what you serve apart from God; we disagree with you, and enmity and hatred have shown between us and you forever, until you believe in God alone' __ except Abraham's word to his father, `I shall certainly ask forgiveness for thee, though I have no power to do anything for thee against God' __ `Our Lord, in Thee we put our trust, and to Thee we turn, and to Thee is the destination.
|60|5|
Our Lord, do not make us a temptation to the unbelievers and forgive us, our Lord; surely Thou art the Mighty, the Wise.'
|60|6|
There was indeed a good example for you in them __ for him who looks to God and the Last Day. And any who turns away, then God is the All-sufficient, the Praiseworthy.
|60|7|
It may be that God will bring about love between you and those of them with whom you are at enmity; and God is Powerful; and God is Forgiving, Merciful.
|60|8|
God does not forbid you regarding those who have not fought you on account of the Religion, and have not expelled you from your homes, that you should be virtuous to them and be equitable with them; surely God loves the equitable.
|60|9|
God forbids you only regarding those who have fought you on account of Religion, and have expelled you from your homes, and have given support in your expulsion, that you should take them for friends; and whoso takes them for friends, those are the wrong-doers.
|60|10|
O Believers, when Believing women come to you, as emigrants, test them; God very well knows their Belief; then if you know them to be Believers, do not return them to the unbelievers; they are not lawful to them, nor are they (the unbelievers) lawful to them; and give them what they have expended. And there is no blame on you if you marry them, when you have given them their dowries. And do not hold to the ties of the unbelieving women, and ask for what you expended; and let them also ask what they expended; that is God's decision; He decides between you; and God is Knowing, Wise.
|60|11|
And if any of your wives has slipped away from you to the unbelievers, and then you retaliate, give those whose wives have gone away, the like of what they expended; and fear God in whom you believe.
|60|12|
O Prophet, when Believing women come to thee and take oath of allegiance to thee __ that they will not associate anything with God, nor steal, nor commit fornication, nor kill their children, nor bring a calumny, forging it between their hands and their feet, nor disobey thee in desirable things __ take their oath of allegiance and pray God for their forgiveness; surely God is Forgiving, Merciful.
|60|13|
O Believers, do not take for friends a people with whom God is wrathful; they have despaired of the Hereafter, as the unbelievers despair of the people in the tombs.
|61|1|
All that is in the heavens and all that is in the earth extols God; and He is the Mighty, the Wise.
|61|2|
O Believers, why do you say what you do not do?
|61|3|
Very hateful is it to God that you say what you do not do.
|61|4|
Surely God loves those who fight in His way in ranks, as if they were a compact building.
|61|5|
And when Moses said to his people, `O my people, why do you hurt me, when you know that I am God's Messenger to you?' So when they swerved, God made their hearts to swerve; and God does not guide the transgressing people.
|61|6|
And when Jesus, son of Mary, said, `O Children of Israel, I am God's Messenger to you, confirming what is before me of the Torah, and giving good news of a Messenger who shall come after me, whose name shall be Ahmad'; but when he brought them the Clear Signs, they said, `this is a manifest sorcery.'
|61|7|
But who does greater wrong then he who forges falsehood against God, while he is called to surrender (Islam)? But God does not guide the wrong-doing people.
|61|8|
They desire to extinguish the Light of God with their mouths, but God will perfect His Light, though the unbelievers be averse.
|61|9|
It is He who has sent His Messenger with the Guidance and the Religion of Truth, that He may make it to prevail over all religions, though the idolaters be averse.
|61|10|
O Believers, shall I point out to you a commerce that shall save you from a painful punishment?
|61|11|
You shall believe in God and His Messenger, and struggle in the way of God with your wealth and your selves; that is better for you if you knew;
|61|12|
He will forgive you your sins, and admit you to gardens underneath which rivers flow, and to fine residences in the gardens of eternity; that is the mighty triumph;
|61|13|
and the other thing that you love __ help from God and a near victory; and give thou good news to the Believers.
|61|14|
O Believers, be God's helpers, as Jesus, son of Mary, said to the disciples, `who will be my helpers towards God?' The disciples said, `we are the helpers of God'; then a group of the Children of Israel believed and a group disbelieved; then We aided the believers against their enemies, and they prevailed.
|62|1|
All that is in the heavens and all that is in the earth extols God, the King, the Holy, the Mighty, the Wise.
|62|2|
It is He who has raised among the unlettered people a Messenger from among them, to recite to them His signs, to purify them, and to teach them the Book and the Wisdom; __ and before that, they were clearly astray; __
|62|3|
and to others of them who have not yet joined them; and He is the Mighty, the Wise.
|62|4|
That is the bounty of God, which He gives it to whom He will; and God is Highly Bounteous.
|62|5|
The likeness of those who were given to carry the Torah, then they did not carry it, is as the likeness of an ass that carries books. Evil is the likeness of the people who gave lies to the signs of God; and God does not guide the wrong-doing people.
|62|6|
Say, `O you Jews, if you assert that you are the friends of God, apart from other men, then long for death, if you are truthful.'
|62|7|
But they will never long for it because of what their hands have forwarded; and God knows the wrong-doers.
|62|8|
Say, `the death from which you flee shall be meeting you, then you shall be returned to the Knower of the unseen and the visible, then He will tell you what you have been doing.'
|62|9|
O Believers, when the Call to the Prayer of the Day of Congregation is made, hasten to the remembrance of God and leave trafficking; that is better for you, if you knew.
|62|10|
Then, when the Prayer is finished, disperse in the land, and seek God's bounty, and remember God much that you may prosper.
|62|11|
But when they see some merchandise or diversion, they scatter off to it and leave thee standing. Say, `that which is with God is better than diversion and merchandise; and God is the best of providers.'
|63|1|
When the hypocrites come to thee, they say, `we bear witness that thou art God's Messenger', and God knows that thou art indeed His Messenger; but God bears witness that the hypocrites are surely liars.
|63|2|
They have taken their oaths as a covering, and so bar from the way of God; surely evil is that they do.
|63|3|
That is because they believed, then disbelieved, then a seal was set on their hearts, so they do not understand.
|63|4|
And when thou seest them, their bodies please thee; and if they speak, thou listenest to their speech; they are like propped-up timber; they think every Cry is against them; they are the enemy, so beware of them; God perish them; how perverted they are!
|63|5|
And when it is said to them, `come, God's Messenger will pray for your forgiveness', they twist their heads, and thou seest them holding back in arrogance.
|63|6|
It is all alike for them whether thou prayest for their forgiveness or dost not pray for their forgiveness; God will never forgive them; surely God does not guide the transgressing people.
|63|7|
They are those who say, `do not expend on those who are with God's Messenger, till they scatter off;' yet to God belong the treasures of the heavens and the earth, but the hypocrites do not understand.
|63|8|
They say, `if we return to the City, the mightier will expel from there the more abased; yet the might belongs to God and to His Messenger and to the Believers, but the hypocrites do not know.
|63|9|
O Believers, let not your wealth or your children divert you from Cod's remembrance; and whoso does that, they are the losers.
|63|10|
And expend of that We have provided you, before death comes upon any of you, and he says, `my Lord, if only Thou wouldst defer me to a near term, I would make offerings and be among the righteous.'
|63|11|
But God will not defer a soul, when its term comes; and God is aware of what you do?
|64|1|
All that is in the heavens, and all that is in the earth oxtols God; His is the kingdom and His is the praise; and He is powerful over everything.
|64|2|
It is He who created you, then one of you is an unbeliever and one of you is a believer; and God sees what you do.
|64|3|
He created the heavens and the earth with the truth, and He shaped you, then made your shapes handsome, and to Him is the destination.
|64|4|
He knows whatever is in the heavens and the earth, and knows what you conceal and what you make public; and God knows the thoughts in the breasts.
|64|5|
Has there not come to you the news of those who disbelieved before, then tasted the penalty of their affair, and for them shall be a painful punishment.
|64|6|
That is because their Messengers came to them with Clear Signs but they said, `shall mortals guide us?' So they disbelieved, and turned away, but God did not care; and God is All-sufficient, Praiseworthy.
|64|7|
The unbelievers assert that they will never be raised up. Say, `yes indeed, by my Lord, you shall surely be raised up, then you shall be told what you did; and that is easy for God.'
|64|8|
So believe in God, and His Messenger, and the Light that We have sent down; and God is aware of what you do.
|64|9|
On the day when He shall gather you for the Day of Gathering, that shall be the Day of Mutual Loss and Gain; and whoso believes in God and does righteousness, He shall acquit him of his evils, and admit him to gardens underneath which rivers flow, to dwell therein forever and ever; that is the mighty triumph.
|64|10|
And those who disbelieved and gave lies to Our signs, they shall be the inhabitants of the Fire, to dwell therein forever; and it is an evil destination.
|64|11|
No affliction befalls but it is by the leave of God; and whoso believes in God, He guides his heart; and God knows everything.
|64|12|
And obey God and obey the Messenger; but if you turn away, then Our Messenger's (duty) is only to deliver the Clear Message.
|64|13|
God, there is no god but He; and in God let the Believers put their trust.
|64|14|
O Believers, among your wives and your children, some are enemies to you, so beware of them; yet if you pardon, and overlook, and forgive, then God is Forgiving, Merciful.
|64|15|
Your wealth and your children are only a trial; and with God is a mighty wage.
|64|16|
So fear God as much as you can, and listen and obey and expend, it will be good for yourselves; and whoso is saved from the avarice of his soul, those shall be prosperers.
|64|17|
If you lend God a good loan, He shall multiply it for you, and forgive you; and God is Thankful, Clement,
|64|18|
the Knower of the unseen and the visible, the Mighty, the Wise.
|65|1|
O Prophet, when you people divorce women, divorce them for their period and count the period; and fear God, your Lord; do not expel them from their homes, nor should they go forth, except when they commit flagrant indecency. And those are God's bounds; and he who transgresses God's bounds, has done wrong to himself; thou dost not know that God after that may bring something new to the matter.
|65|2|
Then, when they have reached their term, retain them desirably or part with them desirably, and call in to witness two just men out of you, and perform the witnessing to God; thus is admonished he who believes in God and the Last Day. And whoso fears God, He will make for him a way out,
|65|3|
and He will provide him whence he does not imagine; and whoso puts his trust in God, He shall suffice him; God does attain His purpose; God has indeed appointed a measure for everything.
|65|4|
And those of your women who have despaired of menstruation, and those who have not yet menstruated, their period, if you are in doubt, shall be three months; and for the pregnant women their term shall be that they lay down their burden; and whoso fears God, He will make his affair easy for him.
|65|5|
That is God's command that He has sent down to you; and whoso fears God, He will acquit him of His evils, and add to his wage.
|65|6|
Lodge them where you lodge yourself according to your means, and do not press them so as to straiten their life. And if they are pregnant, expend upon them till they lay down their burden; and if they suckle for you, give them their wages, and decide together desirably; and if you have mutual difficulties, then another woman may suckle for him.
|65|7|
Let the man of plenty expend of his plenty; and he whose provision is straitend to him, let him expend of what God has given him; God does not charge a soul, except for what He has given him; God will make things easy after hardship.
|65|8|
And how many a city turned in disdain from the commandment of its Lord and His Messengers, then We made a terrible reckoning with it, and We gave it a horrible punishment.
|65|9|
So it tasted the penalty of its affair, and the end of its affair was loss.
|65|10|
God prepared for them a terrible punishment, so fear God, O men of understanding __ those who have believed; God has sent down to you a Reminder;
|65|11|
a Messenger recites to you God's Clarifying Signs that He may bring forth those who believe and do righteous deeds from darkness to light; and whoso believes in God and does righteous deeds, He will admit him to gardens underneath which rivers flow, to dwell therein for ever and ever. God has indeed made for him a handsome provision.
|65|12|
God is He who created seven heavens, and of the earth their like; the command comes down between them that you may know that God is powerful over everything, and that God has encompassed everything in knowledge.
|66|1|
O Prophet, why dost thou forbid what God has made lawful to thee; thou seekest the good pleasure of thy wives; and God is Forgiving, Merciful.
|66|2|
God has indeed ordained for you the absolution of your oaths; and God is your Protector; and He is the Knowing, the Wise.
|66|3|
And when the Prophet confided to one of his wives a certain matter; then, when she told of it, and God informed him about it, he made known part of it and turned aside from a part; so when he told her of it, she said, `who told thee of this'; he said, `the One Knowing, the Aware has told me'.
|66|4|
If you (two) turn to God, for your hearts had inclined; but if you support each other against him, then God is his Protector, and also Gabriel and the righteous among the Believers; and, thereafter, the angels are his supporters.
|66|5|
It may be that if he divorces you, his Lord may give him in exchange wives better than you __ surrendering, believing, obedient, penitent, serving, journeying, previously married and virgins.
|66|6|
O Believers, save yourselves and your families from a Fire whose fuel are men and stones, and over which are set harsh, terrible angels, who do not disobey God in what He commands them, and they do what they are commanded.
|66|7|
`O unbelievers, do not make excuses for yourselves today; you are only being recompensed for what you have been doing.'
|66|8|
O Believers, turn to God in sincere repentance; it may be that your Lord will acquit you of your evils, and admit you to gardens underneath which rivers flow, on a day when God will not humiliate the Prophet and those who have believed with him; their light shall run before them and on their right; they shall say, `our Lord, perfect for us our light and forgive us; surely Thou art powerful over everything.'
|66|9|
O Prophet, struggle against the unbelievers and the hypocrites, and be hard with them; and their resort is Hell; and how evil is the destination!
|66|10|
God gives an example for the unbelievers __ the wife of Noah and the wife of Lot; they were under two of Our righteous servants, but they betrayed them, so they availed them nothing against God, and it was said, `enter the Fire with those who enter.'
|66|11|
And God gives an example for the Believers __ the wife of Pharaoh; when she said, `my Lord, build for me a house in Thy presence in Paradise, and save me from Pharaoh and his work, and save me from the wrong-doing people.'
|66|12|
And Mary, daughter of Imran, who guarded her virginity, so We breathed into it of Our Spirit; and she confirmed the Words of her Lord and His Books, and she was one of the obedient.
|67|1|
Blessed be He in whose hand is the kingdom, and He is powerful over everything;
|67|2|
who created death and life, that He may try you which of you is fairest in works; and He is the Mighty, the Forgiving,
|67|3|
who created seven heavens in regions; thou dost not see any disparity in the creation of the All-merciful; return thy gaze; dost thou see any fissure?
|67|4|
Return thy gaze second time; and thy gaze shall come back to thee, repelled and aweary.
|67|5|
And We have adorned the nearer heaven with lamps, and made them means to stone the devils, and We have prepared for them the punishment of the Blaze.
|67|6|
And for those who disbelieve in their Lord will be the punishment of Hell; and how evil is the destination!
|67|7|
When they are cast into it, they will hear it roaring, while it boils,
|67|8|
as if it would burst with fury. Whenever a troop is cast into it, its keepers ask them, `did not a warner come to you?'
|67|9|
They say, `yes indeed, a warner did come to us, but we cried lies, and said, `God has not sent down anything; you are only gravely astray.'
|67|10|
And they say, `if we had only listened or had understood, we would not have been among the inhabitants of the Blaze.'
|67|11|
So they confess their sins; cursed be the inhabitants of the Blaze!
|67|12|
Surely those who fear their Lord in the unseen, for them shall be forgiveness and a big wage.
|67|13|
And be you secret in your speech or talk it aloud, He knows the thoughts in the breasts.
|67|14|
Shall He who created not know? And He is the Subtle, the Aware.
|67|15|
It is He who made the earth subdued to you, so walk about in its tracts, and eat of His provision; and to Him is the Uprising.
|67|16|
Do you feel secure that He who is in the heaven will not cause the earth to sink with you, while it shakes?
|67|17|
Do you feel secure that He who is in the heaven will not loose a storm of gravel against you,? Then you will know how My warning was?
|67|18|
And indeed those before them also cried lies, then how was My denial?
|67|19|
And have they not seen the birds above them spreading and closing their wings? Naght holds them except the All-merciful? Surely He sees everything.
|67|20|
Or who is this that shall be your host, apart from the All-merciful, to help you? The unbelievers are only in delusion.
|67|21|
Or who is this that shall provide for you, if He withholds His provision? No, but they persist in disdain and aversion.
|67|22|
Is he who walks prone on his face better guided or he who walks upright on a straight path?
|67|23|
Say, `it is He who produced you, and made for you ears, eyes and hearts; little thanks you show.'
|67|24|
Say, `it is He who spread you abroad in the earth and to Him you shall be mustered'.
|67|25|
And they say, `when shall this promise be fulfilled, if you are truthful?'
|67|26|
Say, `the knowledge is only with God, and I am only a clear warner.'
|67|27|
But when they see it near at hand, the faces of the unbelievers will be in distress, and it will be said, `this is what you have been calling to.'
|67|28|
Say, `have you considered, if God destroys me and those that are with me, or has mercy on us, who will protect the unbelievers from a painful punishment?'
|67|29|
Say, `He is the All-merciful; in Him we believe, and in Him we put our trust; and you shall soon know as to who is clearly astray?'
|67|30|
Say, `have you considered, if your water sinks into the earth, then who would bring you gushing spring water?'
|68|1|
Nun (N), by the pen and what they write,
|68|2|
thou art not, by the blessing of thy Lord, a man possessed;
|68|3|
and for thee is surely an unfailing wage;
|68|4|
and thou art surely of a magnificent character.
|68|5|
Now thou shalt see and they shall see,
|68|6|
which of you is the demented.
|68|7|
It is thy Lord who very well knows as to who has gone astray from His way, and it is He who very well knows those who are guided.
|68|8|
So obey thou not those who cry lies.
|68|9|
They wish that thou shouldst compromise, then they would compromise.
|68|10|
And do not obey every mean swearer,
|68|11|
back-biter, one going about with slander,
|68|12|
hinderer of good, transgressor, sinner,
|68|13|
rough, thereafter of doubtful birth,
|68|14|
because he has wealth and sons.
|68|15|
When Our signs are recited to him, he says, `fables of the ancients'.
|68|16|
We shall brand him upon the snout!
|68|17|
We have tried them, as We tried the owners of the garden; when they swore that they would pluck by morning,
|68|18|
and they made no exception.
|68|19|
Then a visitant from thy Lord visited it while they were asleep,
|68|20|
and it was like a garden plucked.
|68|21|
Now they called to one another in the morning,
|68|22|
`move early to your tillage, if you would pluck'.
|68|23|
So they departed, whispering to one another,
|68|24|
`no needy man should enter it today against your will;'
|68|25|
and they proceeded early, determined on the purpose.
|68|26|
Then when they saw it, they said, `we are surely lost;
|68|27|
no, we have been deprived!'
|68|28|
The moderate among them said, `did I not say to you, why do you not extol God?'
|68|29|
They said, `Holy be our Lord; we were wrong-doers'.
|68|30|
Then they turned, some against others, blaming each other.
|68|31|
They said, `woe to us, we were surely transgressors.
|68|32|
May be our Lord will give us better in exchange than it; to our Lord We humbly turn.'
|68|33|
Such is the punishment; and the punishment of the Hereafter is greater; would that they knew.
|68|34|
Surely for the godfearing shall be gardens of bliss with their Lord.
|68|35|
What! shall We make those who surrender like the sinners?
|68|36|
What ails you, how you judge?
|68|37|
Or have you a Book in which you study,
|68|38|
that you shall have therein what you choose?
|68|39|
Or have you oaths binding on Us, till the Day of Resurrection, that you shall have what you judge?
|68|40|
Ask them, which of them will guarantee that!
|68|41|
Or do they have associate-gods? Then let them bring their associate-gods, if they are truthful!
|68|42|
On the day when the leg shall be bared, and they shall be called to prostrate themselves, and they will not be able;
|68|43|
humbled their eyes, abasement shall over-spread them; and indeed they were called to prostrate themselves when they were all well.
|68|44|
So leave Me and him who gives lies to this discourse; We will draw them on, step by step, whence they do not know;
|68|45|
but I respite them; my guile is sure.
|68|46|
Or dost thou ask them for a wage, and they are weighed down with debt?
|68|47|
Or is the unseen with them, and they are writing it down?
|68|48|
So be thou patient for the judgment of thy Lord, and be not like the Man of the Fish; when he cried, and he was all-choked.
|68|49|
Had a blessing from his Lord not reached him, he would have been cast upon the wilderness, being blamed.
|68|50|
But his Lord chose him, and placed him among the righteous.
|68|51|
And the unbelievers almost strike thee down with their glances, when they hear the Reminder, and they say, `he is surely a man possessed.'
|68|52|
But it is not but a Reminder for the whole world.
|69|1|
The Inevitable;
|69|2|
what is the Inevitable;
|69|3|
and what will teach thee what is the Inevitable!
|69|4|
Thamood and Ad gave lies to the Clatterer!
|69|5|
Then as for Thamood, they were destroyed by the Screamer.
|69|6|
And as for Ad, they were destroyed by a violent clamorous wind,
|69|7|
which He imposed on them for seven nights and eight days uninterrup-tedly, so that thou wouldst see the people lying prostrate in it, as if they were stumps of fallen down palm-trees.
|69|8|
Now dost thou see any remnant of them?
|69|9|
And Pharaoh, and those before him, and the subverted cities, committed wrong things.
|69|10|
They disobeyed the Messenger of their Lord, so He seized them with a surpassing grip.
|69|11|
When the waters rose high, We carried you in the running ship,
|69|12|
that We make it a reminder for you, and that retaining ears may retain it.
|69|13|
So, when the Trumpet is blown with a single blast,
|69|14|
and the earth and the mountains are lifted up and crushed with a single crash,
|69|15|
that day the Event shall befall,
|69|16|
and that day the heaven shall be split, and it shall be frail,
|69|17|
and the angels shall be on its borders; and that day, eight shall carry above them the Throne of thy Lord.
|69|18|
That day you shall be presented, no secret of yours hidden.
|69|19|
Then, as for him who is given his Book in his right hand, he will say, `here, take and read my Book;
|69|20|
I thought that I should meet my reckoning'.
|69|21|
So he shall be in a pleasing life,
|69|22|
in a lofty garden,
|69|23|
its clusters at hand: 
|69|24|
`Eat and drink with wholesome appetite for what you did long ago, in days gone-by'.
|69|25|
And as for him who is given his Book in his left hand, he shall say, `would that I had not been given my Book;
|69|26|
and I had not learnt my reckoning!
|69|27|
Would that it had been the end!
|69|28|
My wealth has not availed me;
|69|29|
my authority is gone from me'__
|69|30|
`Take him, and fetter him,
|69|31|
then cast him in Hell,
|69|32|
then in a chain of seventy cubits' length insert him.
|69|33|
Surely he never believed in God, the Mighty,
|69|34|
and he never urged the feeding of the needy;
|69|35|
so today, there is no loyal friend for him,
|69|36|
nor any food except foul pus,
|69|37|
which none except the guilty eat.'
|69|38|
No, I swear by what you see,
|69|39|
and by what you do not see,
|69|40|
it is surely the Word of a Noble Messenger,
|69|41|
and it is not the word of a poet; little do you believe;
|69|42|
nor the word of a soothsayer; little do you heed.
|69|43|
It is a sending down from the Lord of the world.
|69|44|
Had he invented any sayings against us,
|69|45|
We would have seized him by the right hand,
|69|46|
then We would have cut his life-artery;
|69|47|
then none of you could have defended him.
|69|48|
And surely it is a Reminder for the godfearing.
|69|49|
And We surely know that some of you give lies.
|69|50|
And it is surely a (cause of) sorrow to the unbelievers.
|69|51|
And it is surely the Truth of Certainty.
|69|52|
So extol the Name of thy Mighty Lord.
|70|1|
A questioner asked of a punishment about to befall
|70|2|
the unbelievers, which none will avert,
|70|3|
from God, the Lord of the Stairways.
|70|4|
The angels and the Spirit go up to Him in a day whose measure is fifty thousand years;
|70|5|
so be thou patient with a sweet patience.
|70|6|
They see it far off,
|70|7|
but We see it nearby. 
|70|8|
On the day when the heaven shall be as molten copper,
|70|9|
and the mountains shall be as wool,
|70|10|
and no bosom friend shall question a bosom friend,
|70|11|
shown by them. The sinner will wish if he would ransom himself from the punishment of that day by his sons,
|70|12|
and his companion wife, and his brother,
|70|13|
and his kin that shelters him,
|70|14|
and whosoever is on the earth all together, so that then it might save him.
|70|15|
No indeed, it is a flaming Fire,
|70|16|
that strips off the scalp,
|70|17|
calls him who retreated and turned away,
|70|18|
and who gathered, then hoarded.
|70|19|
Surely Man is created impatient;
|70|20|
when evil visits him, fretful;
|70|21|
when good visits him, niggardly;
|70|22|
except those that pray,
|70|23|
those who are regular at their Prayer;
|70|24|
and those in whose wealth is a known right,
|70|25|
for the beggar and the destitute;
|70|26|
and those who confirm the Day of Recompense;
|70|27|
and those who are fearful of the punishment of their Lord;
|70|28|
surely none is secure from their Lord's punishment; and those
|70|29|
who guard their private parts,
|70|30|
except from their wives and what their right hands own, for then, they are not to be blamed,
|70|31|
but whoso seeks beyond that, those are the transgressors;
|70|32|
and those who are watchful of their trusts and their covenant,
|70|33|
and those who stand by their testimonies,
|70|34|
and those who guard their Prayer __
|70|35|
those shall be in the gardens, highly honoured.
|70|36|
What ails the unbelievers, running towards thee with outstretched necks,
|70|37|
from the right and from the left, in groups?
|70|38|
Is everyone of them eager to be admitted to a garden of bliss?
|70|39|
NO indeed; We created them of what they know.
|70|40|
NO, I swear by the Lord of the Easts and the Wests, that We have the power
|70|41|
to substitute a better one than they, and We cannot be outstripped.
|70|42|
So leave them to talk vain and play, till they meet their day that they are promised;
|70|43|
the day they shall come forth from tombs hastily as if they were hurrying to a target,
|70|44|
their eyes humbled, humiliation covering them. That is the Day which they are promised.
|71|1|
We sent Noah to his people: `warn thy people before there comes on them a painful punishment'.
|71|2|
He said, `O my people, I am a clear warner to you, (to say)
|71|3|
`serve God and fear Him and obey me;
|71|4|
He will forgive you your sins and defer you to a stated term. Surely God's term, when it comes, cannot be deferred, if you but knew'.
|71|5|
He said, `my Lord, I called my people by night and by day,
|71|6|
but my calling has only increased them in flight.
|71|7|
And whenever I called them that Thou mightest forgive them, they put their fingers in their ears, wrapped them in their garments, became stubborn, and showed great arrogance.
|71|8|
Then I called them openly,
|71|9|
then I spoke to them in public, and also made secret talks with them;
|71|10|
and I said, `ask forgiveness of your Lord; He is surely All-forgiving,
|71|11|
He will loose heaven upon you in torrents,
|71|12|
and He will aid you with wealth and sons, and appoint for you gardens, and appoint for you rivers.
|71|13|
What ails you, that you do not look for dignity with God,
|71|14|
and He has created you in different states?
|71|15|
Have you not seen how God created seven heavens in regions,
|71|16|
and set the moon therein for a light, and set the sun for a lamp?
|71|17|
And God caused you to grow out of the earth,
|71|18|
then He will return you into it, and will bring you forth.
|71|19|
And God made for you the earth as a wide expanse,
|71|20|
that you may traverse in its wide paths'.
|71|21|
Noah said, `my Lord, they have disobeyed me, and have followed him whose wealth and children have added only to his loss;
|71|22|
and they have devised a mighty device.
|71|23|
And they have said, `do not leave your gods and do not leave Wadd, nor Suwa, nor Yaghuth, Ya`uq and Nasr'.
|71|24|
And they have indeed led many astray, and added not to the wrong-doers but straying'.
|71|25|
Because of their sins, they were drowned and admitted into the Fire, then they did not find for them any helpers, apart from God.
|71|26|
And Noah said, `my Lord, do not leave any of the unbelievers to dwell on the land.
|71|27|
If Thou leavest them, they will lead Thy servants astray, and they will not beget any but ungrateful law-breakers.
|71|28|
My Lord, forgive me, and my parents, and whoso enters my house as a believer, and the believing men and women; and do not increase the wrong-doers except in ruin'.
|72|1|
Say: it has been revealed to me that a section of the jinn gave ear, and they said, `we have heard a wonderful Reading (Qur'an),
|72|2|
that guides to rectitude, so we have believed in it; and we will not associate with our Lord anyone;
|72|3|
and that exalted be our Lord's Majesty, who has not taken to Himself any consort or son;
|72|4|
and that the fool among us spoke outrage against God;
|72|5|
and that we had thought that men and jinn will never speak against God a lie;
|72|6|
but that some men of mankind would take refuge with some men of the jinn, and they increased them in vileness,
|72|7|
and that they thought, as you also thought, that God will not raise up anyone;
|72|8|
and that we touched the heaven, and found it filled with terrible guards and meteors;
|72|9|
and that we used to sit on its listening posts; __ but any who listens now shall find a meteor in wait for him __
|72|10|
and that we do not know whether harm is desired for those on the earth, or their Lord desires the rectitude for them;
|72|11|
and that some of us are the righteous, and some of us are otherwise __ we are on different ways __
|72|12|
and that we thought that we should never frustrate God in the earth, nor frustrate Him by flight;
|72|13|
and that when we heard the Guidance, we believed in it; and whosoever believes in his Lord, shall not fear any loss nor vileness,
|72|14|
and that some of us have surrendered to God, and some of us ascribe equals (to Him); now whoso has surrendered, those have aimed at the right way;
|72|15|
and as for those who ascribe equals, they are the fire-wood for Hell.'
|72|16|
And (it has been revealed to me) that if they go straight on the way, We would give them plenty of water to drink,
|72|17|
that We may thereby try them; and whoso turns away from the remembrance of his Lord, He will drive him into severe punishment;
|72|18|
and that the places of worship belong to God, so do not call upon anyone along with God;
|72|19|
and that when God's Servant stood to call on Him, they almost came upon him in swarms.
|72|20|
Say, `I call only on my Lord, and I do not associate anyone with Him'.
|72|21|
Say, `I possess no power over you for hurt or rectitude.'
|72|22|
Say, `none shall protect me from God, and I shall not find, apart from Him,
|72|23|
any refuge, excepting a Deliverance from God and His Messages; and whoso disobeys God and His Messenger, for him shall be the Fire of Hell, wherein they shall dwell forever and ever.
|72|24|
Until when they see that which they are promised, they will know who is weaker in helpers and fewer in numbers'.
|72|25|
Say, `I do not know whether that which you are promised is near, or my Lord is keeping it at a distance.
|72|26|
The Knower of the unseen, He does not disclose His unseen to anyone,
|72|27|
except to a Messenger with whom He is pleased; and then He puts observers before him and behind him,
|72|28|
that He may know that they have delivered the Messages of their Lord; and He encompasses all that is with them, and has counted everything in numbers'.
|73|1|
O thou enwarpped in robes!
|73|2|
rise at night but a little,
|73|3|
a half of it, or diminish thereof a little,
|73|4|
or add to it, and chant the Qur'an distinctly.
|73|5|
We shall soon cast upon thee a weighty Word.
|73|6|
Surely rising by night is very heavy in treading the soul and very effective in speech.
|73|7|
Surely Thou hast a lengthy occupation during day.
|73|8|
And remember the Name of thy Lord, and devote thyself to Him devoutly.
|73|9|
Lord of the East and the West, there is no god but He; so take Him for a Care-taker.
|73|10|
And bear patiently what they say, and forsake them with grace.
|73|11|
And leave Me and holders of comforts, those who cry lies, and respite them a little.
|73|12|
Surely with Us are fetters, and a furnace,
|73|13|
and food that chokes, and a painful punishment, __
|73|14|
on the day when the earth and the mountains shall quake, and the mountains shall be a slipping heap of sand.
|73|15|
Surely We have sent to you a Messenger, as a witness over you, as We sent to Pharaoh a Messenger;
|73|16|
but Pharaoh disobeyed the Messenger, so We seized him with a terrible seizing.
|73|17|
Now, if you disbelieve, how will you fear the day that shall make the children grey-headed,
|73|18|
and whereby the heaven shall be split? His promise is sure to be fulfilled.
|73|19|
Surely this is a Reminder; so whoso will, let him take his way to his Lord.
|73|20|
Thy Lord knows that thou risest for nearly two thirds of the night, and a half of it, and a third of it, and so also do a group of those with thee; but God determines the night and the day; He knows that you cannot keep it up; He has therefor turned towards you, therefore read so much of the Qur'an as is easy. He knows that some of you will fall sick, and others will journey in the land seeking God's bounty, and others will fight in the way of God; so, read so much of it as is easy, and establish the Prayer, and pay the Due-alms, and lend to God a goodly loan; and whatever good you advance for yourselves, you shall find it with God as better and mightier a reward; and ask God's forgiveness; surely God is Forgiving, Merciful. 
|74|1|
O thou cloaked!
|74|2|
arise and warn,
|74|3|
and magnify thy Lord,
|74|4|
and clean thy clothes,
|74|5|
and shun abomination,
|74|6|
and do not favour to seek more,
|74|7|
and be patient for the sake of thy Lord.
|74|8|
For when the Trumpet is sounded,
|74|9|
that day will be a hard day,
|74|10|
not easy for the unbelievers.
|74|11|
Leave Me and him whom I created alone,
|74|12|
and gave him ample wealth
|74|13|
and ever-present sons,
|74|14|
and made all things smooth for him;
|74|15|
yet he is eager that I should give more.
|74|16|
No indeed; he is froward to Our signs.
|74|17|
I shall constrain him to a hard climb.
|74|18|
He pondered and determined;
|74|19|
perish he, how he determined;
|74|20|
again, perish he, how he determined;
|74|21|
then he looked,
|74|22|
then he frowned and scowled,
|74|23|
then he turned back and showed arrogance;
|74|24|
and he said, `this is not but a sorcery handed down;
|74|25|
this is not but the speech of man'.
|74|26|
I shall cast him in Saqar;
|74|27|
and what will teach thee what Saqar is?
|74|28|
It spares nothing, nor leaves any;
|74|29|
it scorches the mortal;
|74|30|
over it are Nineteen.
|74|31|
And We have appointed only angels to be the masters of the Fire, and We have appointed their number only to be as a trial for the unbelievers, and that those who were given the Book may become sure, and that the Believers may increase in belief, and that those who were given the Book and the Believers may not doubt, and that those in whose hearts is sickness and the unbelievers may say, `what does God desire by this similitude?' Thus God sends astray whom He will, and guides whom He will. And none knows the hosts of thy Lord but He. And it is not but a Reminder for the mortals.
|74|32|
No indeed; by the moon,
|74|33|
and by the night when it retreats,
|74|34|
and by the dawn when it shines,
|74|35|
it is surely one of the gravest things,
|74|36|
a warning for mortals,
|74|37|
for him among you who wills to advance or lag behind.
|74|38|
Every soul is pledged to what it has earned,
|74|39|
except the Companions of the Right.
|74|40|
In the gardens, they shall question
|74|41|
concerning the sinners: 
|74|42|
`what put you in the Saqar?'
|74|43|
They shall say, `we were not of those who prayed,
|74|44|
and we were not such as feed the needy,
|74|45|
and we used to indulge in vain talk with those who indulged in it,
|74|46|
and we gave lies to the Day of Recompense,
|74|47|
till the Certain came to us.'
|74|48|
Now the intercession of the intercessors shall not profit them.
|74|49|
But what ails them, that they turn away from the Reminder,
|74|50|
as if they are startled asses,
|74|51|
fleeing from a lion.
|74|52|
