|88|1|
Has there come to thee the news of the Enveloper?
|88|2|
Some faces, on that day, shall be downcast,
|88|3|
toiling, and weary;
|88|4|
they shall enter a blazing Fire,
|88|5|
given to drink from a boiling spring.
|88|6|
There will be no food for them except bitter thorny fruit,
|88|7|
that neither fattens, nor appeases hunger.
|88|8|
Some faces, on that day, shall be joyful,
|88|9|
pleased with their striving,
|88|10|
in a lofty garden,
|88|11|
not hearing therein any non-sense.
|88|12|
Therein shall be a running spring.
|88|13|
There-in shall be raised couches,
|88|14|
and goblets well-set,
|88|15|
and cushions arranged,
|88|16|
and carpets spread-out.
|88|17|
Do they not look at the camel, how it is created;
|88|18|
and at the heaven, how it is raised up;
|88|19|
and at the mountains, how they are fixed;
|88|20|
and at the earth, how it is spread out?
|88|21|
So admonish, thou art only an admonisher.
|88|22|
Thou art not an overseer over them.
|88|23|
But whoso turns away and disbelieves,
